-trader.json","4b36436364d74526","offer-the-trading-pit",{"id":3045,"data":3047,"filePath":3050,"digest":3051},{"id":3045,"name":3048,"propFirmIds":3049,"trackingUrl":2492,"terms":2906},"The Trading Pit — Affiliate Link",[2445],"src/content/offers/offer-the-trading-pit.json","1980cc96764d6198","offer-the5ers",{"id":3052,"data":3054,"filePath":3057,"digest":3058},{"id":3052,"name":3055,"propFirmIds":3056,"trackingUrl":2549,"terms":2906},"The5%ers — Affiliate Link",[2510],"src/content/offers/offer-the5ers.json","75346481799ddd04","offer-thinkcapital",{"id":3059,"data":3061,"filePath":3064,"digest":3065},{"id":3059,"name":3062,"propFirmIds":3063,"trackingUrl":2608,"terms":2906},"Think Capital — Affiliate Link",[2566],"src/content/offers/offer-thinkcapital.json","736490019439a659","offer-topstep",{"id":3066,"data":3068,"filePath":3071,"digest":3072},{"id":3066,"name":3069,"propFirmIds":3070,"trackingUrl":2660,"terms":2906},"Topstep — Affiliate Link",[2624],"src/content/offers/offer-topstep.json","0c476b3f188fbcb5","reviews",["Map",3075,3076,3110,3111,3156,3157,3214,3215,3253,3254,3283,3284,3318,3319,3362,3363,3406,3407,3458,3459,3499,3500,3544,3545,3585,3586,3607,3608,3643,3644,3685,3686,3727,3728,3768,3769,3786,3787,3834,3835,3878,3879,3922,3923,3962,3963,4010,4011,4058,4059,4103,4104,4150,4151,4195,4196,4237,4238,4278,4279,4319,4320,4366,4367,4410,4411,4452,4453,4498,4499,4542,4543,4587,4588,4633,4634,4682,4683,4723,4724,4736,4737],"rev-aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",{"id":3075,"data":3077,"filePath":3108,"digest":3109},{"id":3075,"propFirmId":1005,"summary":3078,"pros":3079,"cons":3084,"bestFor":3089,"notIdealFor":3090,"overallScore":3091,"categoryScores":3092,"verdictBlocks":3093,"faq":3097,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":3105,"author":3106,"editor":3107},"FTMO is the gold standard in proprietary trading. Founded in Prague in 2015, it has funded more than 300,000 traders and maintains one of the highest Trustpilot scores in the industry at 4.8.\n\nThe 2-step evaluation requires hitting a 10% profit target in Phase 1 and 5% in Phase 2, with a maximum 5% daily and 10% overall drawdown. These are stricter than many competitors, but the trade-off is exceptional payout reliability and a well-structured scaling plan up to $2M in funded capital.\n\nThe challenge fee is refunded with the first payout, making FTMO effectively free if you pass. News trading is prohibited, which is a meaningful restriction for some strategies.",[3080,3081,1023,3082,3083],"Most established prop firm — 10+ years of operation","Industry-leading Trustpilot score (4.8 / 5 from 12,000+ reviews)","90% profit split at top scale","Supports MT4, MT5, and cTrader",[3085,3086,3087,3088],"News trading not allowed","2-step evaluation only — no instant funding option","US residents restricted","Strict consistency rule (no single day >50% of total profit)","Experienced traders who want maximum credibility and payout reliability","News traders and US-based traders",83,{"challenges":101,"spreads":101,"markets":101,"payouts":101,"platforms":377,"trust":377},[3094],{"heading":3095,"body":3096},"Our Verdict","FTMO is the benchmark against which all other prop firms are measured. If you pass their evaluation, the payout reliability and brand credibility are unmatched. Our top-rated prop firm overall.",[3098,3101],{"q":3099,"a":3100},"Does FTMO refund the challenge fee?","Yes — the challenge fee is refunded with your first profit payout if you pass the evaluation.",{"q":3102,"a":3103},"Is news trading allowed on FTMO?","No. Trading during high-impact news events is prohibited on all FTMO accounts.","1.0","2026-01-18","Editorial Team","Senior Editor","src/content/reviews/rev-aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa.json","31af31be395b307b","rev-alpha-capital",{"id":3110,"data":3112,"filePath":3154,"digest":3155},{"id":3110,"propFirmId":14,"summary":3113,"pros":3114,"cons":3121,"bestFor":3128,"notIdealFor":3129,"overallScore":1084,"categoryScores":3130,"categorySections":3131,"verdictBlocks":3133,"faq":3137,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":3153,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With a score of 43/100, Alpha Capital offers multiple evaluation models and trading platforms but operates entirely in a simulated environment with no real-money execution. While it promotes an engaged Discord community and tools like Autochartist, its lack of transparency on spreads and execution raises concerns.\n\nTraders have reported payout denials, sudden account closures, and KYC enforcement only after passing challenges. Many claim risk interviews, IP bans, and changing rules prevent withdrawals, leading to doubts about the firm's legitimacy. The high number of detailed 1-star reviews suggests traders should approach with caution.",[3115,3116,3117,3118,3119,3120],"Multiple evaluation models (1-step, 2-step, 3-step)","Account sizes up to $200K","Scaling plan up to $2 million","MT5, cTrader, and DXTrade available","Active Discord community with 106K+ members","Autochartist integration for market analysis",[3122,3123,3124,3125,3126,3127],"No real-money trading — fully simulated environment","No transparency on average spreads","Reports of payout denials and sudden account closures","Strict KYC enforcement after passing challenges","US residents restricted to DXTrade only","40% Best Day Rule limits daily profit contribution","Traders who want multiple evaluation paths and scaling potential, and who understand the risks of simulated-only prop firms","Traders seeking transparent execution, reliable payouts, or real-money trading environments",{"challenges":350,"spreads":613,"markets":613,"payouts":31,"platforms":31,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},"custom",[3134],{"heading":3135,"body":3136},"Alpha Capital Warning","We do not recommend Alpha Capital due to payout denials, sudden account closures, and strict KYC enforcement after traders pass challenges. The firm operates in a simulated environment with no real-money execution, raising transparency concerns.\n\nOur testing scored Alpha Capital 43/100, and we only recommend firms scoring 50/100+. For better trust and pricing, consider IC Funded, Blueberry Funded, or BrightFunded for more reliable prop firms.",[3138,3141,3144,3147,3150],{"q":3139,"a":3140},"Are Alpha Capital legit?","Alpha Capital Group is a proprietary trading firm that offers simulated funded accounts rather than real-money trading. While it provides multiple evaluation models and trading platforms, concerns over payout denials, sudden account closures, and strict KYC enforcement have been reported. With a mix of positive and negative reviews, traders should approach with caution and carefully review the terms before joining.",{"q":3142,"a":3143},"How does Alpha Capital work?","Alpha Capital operates by offering traders a chance to pass evaluation challenges to qualify for a funded account. However, these accounts are simulated, meaning traders do not trade with real money. Traders can choose between different challenge types with set profit targets and drawdown limits, and if successful, they can earn a percentage of their simulated profits.",{"q":3145,"a":3146},"Is Alpha Capital Group accepting US clients?","Alpha Capital Group accepts US clients but restricts them to using the DXTrade platform. Unlike other traders who can access MetaTrader 5 (MT5) and cTrader, U.S. residents must use DXTrade due to regulatory restrictions. Additionally, traders traveling to the US cannot access their MT5 or cTrader accounts while within the country.",{"q":3148,"a":3149},"What broker does Alpha Capital use?","Alpha Capital Group is broker-backed through ACG Markets, an FSA-regulated brokerage. While ACG Markets provides Prime-of-Prime liquidity and ultra-low latency execution, all trading within Alpha Capital remains in a simulated environment. This means funded traders do not have direct market access or real-money execution.",{"q":3151,"a":3152},"Why doesn't BestPropFirms recommend Alpha Capital Group?","BestPropFirms does not recommend Alpha Capital Group due to multiple trader complaints regarding payout denials, sudden account closures, and strict KYC enforcement after passing challenges. Additionally, Alpha Capital operates entirely in a simulated environment with no real-money execution. With a trust score of 43/100, Alpha Capital falls below our recommended threshold of 50/100+.","We do not recommend Alpha Capital due to payout denials, sudden account closures, and strict KYC enforcement after traders pass challenges. The firm operates in a simulated environment with no real-money execution, raising transparency concerns.\n\nOur testing scored Alpha Capital 43/100, and we only recommend firms scoring 50/100+. For better trust and pricing, consider [IC Funded](/reviews/ic-funded), [Blueberry Funded](/reviews/blueberry-funded), or [BrightFunded](/reviews/brightfunded) for more reliable prop firms.","src/content/reviews/rev-alpha-capital.json","6ddc19ce17d92e3b","rev-apex-trader-funding",{"id":3156,"data":3158,"filePath":3212,"digest":3213},{"id":3156,"propFirmId":247,"summary":3159,"pros":3160,"cons":3167,"bestFor":3174,"notIdealFor":3175,"overallScore":2209,"categoryScores":3176,"categorySections":3177,"verdictBlocks":3185,"faq":3189,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":3211,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"In our testing of Apex Trader Funding, we scored the firm at 37/100 due to high monthly fees, limited platform flexibility, and minimal educational resources compared to competing futures prop firms.\n\nWhile Apex offers a solid profit-sharing structure, allowing you to retain 100% of your first $25K in profits, the prop firm fell short in areas like monthly fees and support resources. Apex's evaluation process is competitive, but lacks the extensive community engagement found in top-scoring firms like Topstep.",[3161,3162,3163,3164,3165,3166],"Account sizes up to $300K","High profit split (100% first $25K)","46 futures markets","Multiple platform options","No maximum trading days","100% first split on $25K",[3168,3169,3170,3171,3172,3173],"High monthly fees ($147–$597)","Limited education resources","Fees for Level 2 pricing","Activation fees for funded accounts","No fully automated trading","Credit card payment only","Futures traders who want high profit splits, multiple account sizes, and access to diverse futures markets","Traders seeking extensive education, low-cost evaluations, or comprehensive support and mentorship",{"challenges":360,"spreads":360,"markets":360,"payouts":24,"platforms":31,"trust":360},{"challenges":3178,"spreads":3179,"markets":3180,"platforms":3181,"payouts":3182,"support":3183,"trust":3184},"Apex Trader Funding offers Tradovate and Rithmic account types with sizes from $25K to $300K. One-step evaluation with minimum 7 trading days and no maximum. Profit targets from $1,500 to $20,000 (fixed dollar amounts, not percentages). Trailing drawdown for most accounts, static option for 100K. Monthly subscription fees from $147–$597. Scored 4/10.","Commission fees vary by platform. Tradovate: $1.55/side ($3.10 round turn) for E-mini S&P 500. Rithmic: $1.99/side ($3.98 round turn). Micro contracts have lower commissions. Level 1 data included, Level 2 costs $41+/month extra. Activation fees $85–$360 for funded accounts. Scored 4/10.","46 futures markets across currency, equity, agriculture, energy, metal, and cryptocurrency. Exchanges: CME, CBOT, COMEX, NYMEX. Only micro contracts for crypto futures. Diverse but limited to futures only. Scored 4/10.","Supports NinjaTrader 8, Tradovate, TradingView, RTrader Pro, and 10+ additional platforms for Rithmic accounts. Tradovate offers multi-device access with TradingView integration. Rithmic for high-speed execution. No fully automated systems or copy trading on funded accounts. Scored 5/10.","100% profit split on first $25K, then 90%. Payouts every 8 trading days. Processing in 3–4 business days. Credit card payments only. Activation fees required for funded accounts ($85–$360). Safety net requirements for first 3 payouts. Scored 1/10.","24/7 support via online help desk. Platform-specific guides and FAQs available. Limited educational resources — introductory videos only covering trading fundamentals. No mentorship programs or in-depth courses. Scored 4/10.","TrustPilot 4.4/5 from 16,900+ reviews. Active Discord with ~59,000 members. Facebook group with 29.4K members. YouTube channel with 26.8K subscribers. Some concerns about platform limitations and support response times. Scored 4/10.",[3186],{"heading":3187,"body":3188},"Apex Trader Funding Warning","We do not recommend Apex Trader Funding due to high monthly fees, limited platform flexibility, and frequent complaints about payout delays and account terminations.\n\nIf you're looking for a futures funded account with better support, clear pricing, and fairer trading conditions, we recommend broker-backed futures prop firms like FXIFY Futures or FundedNext Futures, which performed significantly better in our evaluations.",[3190,3193,3196,3199,3202,3205,3208],{"q":3191,"a":3192},"What is Apex Trading?","Apex Trading refers to the evaluation and funded account programs offered by Apex Trader Funding, a futures prop firm. Apex allows you to qualify for funded accounts by meeting profit targets on demo evaluations, using platforms like NinjaTrader or Tradovate. If you pass you'll receive a Performance Account with up to $300K in funding and can earn 100% of the first $25K in profits, followed by a 90% split.",{"q":3194,"a":3195},"Does Apex Trader Funding payout?","Yes, Apex Trader Funding does offer payouts to funded traders. Traders can retain 100% of their profits up to $25,000 and 90% of profits beyond this amount. Payouts are processed every eight trading days, and funds typically arrive within 3–4 business days post-approval.",{"q":3197,"a":3198},"Is Apex Trader Funding a scam or legit?","No, Apex Trader Funding is not a scam and is considered a legit prop trading firm, with thousands of positive user reviews and a TrustPilot rating of 4.4/5 based on over 16,900 reviews.",{"q":3200,"a":3201},"What are the profit targets for Apex Trader Funding's evaluation program?","Profit targets at Apex Trader Funding start at $1,500 for the smallest $25,000 account and increase with account size. Targets are fixed amounts rather than percentages. For example, a $100,000 full account has a $6,000 target, while the $100,000 static account has a lower $2,000 target.",{"q":3203,"a":3204},"What are the Apex Trader Funding account sizes?","Apex Trader Funding offers account sizes from $25,000 up to $300,000 for funded accounts. Each size has specific profit targets, drawdown structures, and contract limits.",{"q":3206,"a":3207},"Is Apex Trader Funding good for day trading?","Yes, Apex Trader Funding is suitable for day trading, as it offers low-latency platforms like Rithmic and NinjaTrader, which are well-suited for rapid executions and market depth.",{"q":3209,"a":3210},"Is Apex Trader Funding better than Topstep?","Topstep generally outperforms Apex Trader Funding, with a higher overall score of 89/100 compared to Apex's 37/100, based on various criteria including platform options, profit splits, and user support.","We do not recommend Apex Trader Funding due to high monthly fees, limited platform flexibility, and frequent complaints about payout delays and account terminations.\n\nIf you're looking for a futures funded account with better support, clear pricing, and fairer trading conditions, we recommend broker-backed futures prop firms like [FXIFY Futures](/reviews/fxify-futures) or [FundedNext Futures](/reviews/fundednext-futures), which performed significantly better in our evaluations.","src/content/reviews/rev-apex-trader-funding.json","a843e9f71a36f034","rev-aquafunded",{"id":3214,"data":3216,"filePath":3251,"digest":3252},{"id":3214,"propFirmId":149,"summary":3217,"pros":3218,"cons":3224,"bestFor":3230,"notIdealFor":3231,"overallScore":597,"categoryScores":3232,"categorySections":3233,"verdictBlocks":3234,"faq":3238,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"AquaFunded scored 55/100 overall. It offers a wide range of challenge types, from 1-step to instant funding, with no time limits and solid platform access. But post-funding rules are stricter than most competitors, and key details like average spreads and rule enforcement clarity are missing.\n\nThe trading platform selection is solid — MT5, TradeLocker, and Match Trader — and pricing is transparent at the commission level. Optional add-ons unlock fast payouts and 100% profit splits. However, with no average spreads published, no resets, and a Trustpilot profile flagged for fake reviews, AquaFunded is best suited to experienced traders who can manage its limitations.",[3219,3117,3220,3221,3222,3223],"Instant funding accounts up to $200K","EAs and automated trading allowed","Three platform choices: MT5, TradeLocker, Match Trader","No time limits on evaluations","100% profit split available with add-on",[3225,3226,225,3227,3228,3229],"No average spreads published","Stocks and futures not available","Trustpilot profile flagged for fake reviews","No reset option available","News trading restricted once funded","Experienced traders who want flexible evaluation choices including instant funding, scaling potential to $2M, and are comfortable managing strict post-funding consistency rules","Beginners needing guidance, traders who want published spread data, stock/futures access, reset options, or those who prefer transparent trust signals without Trustpilot issues",{"challenges":31,"spreads":31,"markets":350,"payouts":350,"platforms":66,"support":31,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3235],{"heading":3236,"body":3237},"Our Final Verdict On AquaFunded","AquaFunded offers a wide range of models with unlimited evaluation time and competitive pricing, which gives you flexibility — especially if you're looking to ease into prop trading with lower pressure. The variety of funding types, from 1-step to instant accounts, is a strength. But rule enforcement, strict post-funding consistency filters, and no reset options create friction. These issues are especially risky for beginner traders who may miss fine-print rules on trailing drawdowns or profit distribution.\n\nThe trading platform selection is solid, spreads are raw, and the $5/lot commission is reasonable, but transparency falls short due to missing average spread data and undisclosed liquidity providers. Customer support is fast, and the Discord community is active, but a flagged Trustpilot profile and low response rate to negative reviews raise concerns. With a total score of 55/100, AquaFunded sits in the middle of the pack. It's a decent option if you're confident managing strict rules, but there are more trader-friendly prop firms out there.",[3239,3242,3245,3248],{"q":3240,"a":3241},"How long does it take for AquaFunded to payout?","AquaFunded processes payouts every 14 days, or in 7 days if you purchase the fast-payout add-on. The first payout is available 14 days after your first funded trade, and all payments are handled via Riseworks through crypto or bank transfer.",{"q":3243,"a":3244},"Which broker does AquaFunded use?","AquaFunded partners with brokers like ThinkMarkets and Purple Trading, but does not officially disclose them on its website. These partnerships offer ECN pricing and institutional-grade liquidity, but the firm does not list its liquidity providers publicly.",{"q":3246,"a":3247},"What is the maximum loss on AquaFunded?","The maximum loss on AquaFunded depends on the account type, but ranges from 5% to 10% of your account balance. Instant accounts use a trailing drawdown model, while some evaluation models use fixed limits based on your starting balance.",{"q":3249,"a":3250},"What is the minimum withdrawal from AquaFunded?","The minimum withdrawal amount on AquaFunded is $100. This applies to all account types, and payouts are processed bi-weekly once you meet the trading requirements and pass KYC.","src/content/reviews/rev-aquafunded.json","b4276718954b5f5f","rev-bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb",{"id":3253,"data":3255,"filePath":3281,"digest":3282},{"id":3253,"propFirmId":2510,"summary":3256,"pros":3257,"cons":3263,"bestFor":3267,"notIdealFor":3268,"overallScore":101,"categoryScores":3269,"verdictBlocks":3270,"faq":3273,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":3280,"author":3106,"editor":3107},"The5%ers, founded in 2016 in Israel, offers one of the most flexible rule sets in the prop firm industry. News trading, weekend holding, and copy trading are all permitted — a trifecta that few firms allow simultaneously.\n\nThe standout feature is the Growth plan's 100% profit split, which scales as traders hit profit targets. Evaluation paths include 1-step, 2-step, and instant funding options, giving traders flexibility in how they enter the funded programme.\n\nThe main limitation is platform: MT5 only. Traders who rely on MT4 or cTrader will need to adapt. Fees are competitive, with a $5,000 account starting at $39.",[3258,3259,3260,3261,3262],"100% profit split available on Growth plan","News trading, weekend holding, and copy trading all allowed","Multiple evaluation paths: 1-step, 2-step, instant","Competitive pricing — $5k account from $39","EA trading permitted",[3264,3265,3266],"MT5 only — no MT4 or cTrader","Smaller payout track record vs. FTMO","Stricter drawdown limits than many competitors (4% daily, 6% max)","News traders, copy traders, and those wanting flexible evaluation options","MT4 or cTrader users who cannot switch platforms",{"challenges":377,"spreads":101,"markets":101,"payouts":101,"platforms":66,"trust":101},[3271],{"heading":3095,"body":3272},"The5%ers is the best option for news traders and copy traders. The 100% profit split is genuinely unique in this space. The MT5-only restriction is its primary drawback — if you need MT4 or cTrader, look elsewhere.",[3274,3277],{"q":3275,"a":3276},"Can I trade the news on The5%ers?","Yes — news trading is allowed on all The5%ers programmes.",{"q":3278,"a":3279},"What is the 100% profit split?","On the Growth programme, as traders scale up their account, they can reach 100% profit split at higher tiers. The starting split is lower.","2026-01-12","src/content/reviews/rev-bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb.json","58bb736c6ad9bcfd","rev-blue-guardian",{"id":3283,"data":3285,"filePath":3316,"digest":3317},{"id":3283,"propFirmId":413,"summary":3286,"pros":3287,"cons":3292,"bestFor":3297,"notIdealFor":3298,"overallScore":2772,"categoryScores":3299,"categorySections":3300,"verdictBlocks":3301,"faq":3305,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":3315,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":519},"Blue Guardian scored 45/100 in our full review because while the prop firm offers a wide mix of challenge types, including instant funding and multi-step evaluations, the way these models are structured can be confusing. Key rules like payout caps, drawdown types, and consistency requirements differ significantly between plans, and not all terms are explained clearly up front.\n\nThat lack of clarity makes it harder to assess whether you're getting long-term value for the fee. Some accounts offer fast payouts and flexible trading conditions, while others include strict limits that may not suit experienced traders. Combined with a delisted TrustPilot rating and limited transparency around scaling, it's a setup that raises questions. Traders considering this firm should review each model carefully before committing.",[3288,3289,3290,3291],"Instant funding accounts available with no evaluation phase","No time limits on any challenge or evaluation","MT5, Match-Trader, and TradeLocker platform options","Active Discord community with 80,000+ members",[3293,3294,3295,3296],"TrustPilot profile removed due to guideline violations","Rules vary widely between challenge types with inconsistent terms","No published data on spreads or execution quality","Instant Starter payouts limited to a single $250 withdrawal","Traders who want instant funding options with no time limits and prefer flexible platform choices across MT5, Match-Trader, and TradeLocker","Traders seeking transparent scaling plans, strong trust signals, consistent rules across all account types, or those uncomfortable with a firm whose TrustPilot rating has been removed",{"challenges":350,"spreads":360,"markets":360,"payouts":360,"platforms":31,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3302],{"heading":3303,"body":3304},"Our Final Verdict On Blue Guardian","Blue Guardian ended up with a low score of 45/100 due to issues around transparency, inconsistent rule sets, and strict limitations on certain account types. While the firm does offer a wide selection of evaluations, including instant funding and three-step models, not all challenges provide long-term value — particularly the Instant Starter, which caps total payout at just $250 and closes the account after a single withdrawal.\n\nThe lack of clarity across risk parameters, payout rules, and scaling progression makes it difficult to evaluate your upside before committing a fee. TrustPilot delisting and feedback around spread execution and Guardian Shield usage further affect the trust score. On the positive side, the no-expiry challenges, platform flexibility, and fast Discord support will appeal to some traders. But overall, Blue Guardian is better suited to cautious testing than serious capital scaling.",[3306,3309,3312],{"q":3307,"a":3308},"Does Blue Guardian pay out?","Yes, Blue Guardian does pay out, but only if you follow their rules exactly. Payouts are available every 14 days once funded, or every 7 days if you add the performance upgrade. Profit splits range from 80% to 90% depending on the account type. However, breaking any trading rule, including daily loss or consistency limits, voids eligibility. Payouts are handled through Riseworks.io, and crypto withdrawals are capped at $2,000 per request.",{"q":3310,"a":3311},"What is the most legit prop firm?","The most legit prop firm in our rankings is DNA Funded, which scored 97/100 based on live testing. It's ranked number one on our best prop firms list for offering low-cost challenges, strong broker backing, and up to 90% profit splits. By comparison, Blue Guardian scored just 45/100 in our review, largely due to payout caps, inconsistent rules, and a removed TrustPilot rating. If legitimacy and structure matter, start with a firm that's tested and verified.",{"q":3313,"a":3314},"Which broker does Blue Guardian use?","Blue Guardian is not a broker-backed prop firm. That doesn't automatically make it untrustworthy, but it does mean less transparency compared to the best broker-backed prop firms available. Broker-backed firms often offer better execution quality and clearer trading conditions, which can be a key factor for serious traders evaluating cost and slippage. If that matters to you, a broker-backed option may offer more peace of mind.","Blue Guardian's TrustPilot profile has been **flagged for guideline violations**, making their public rating unavailable. Despite having 1,400+ reviews, this lack of transparency is concerning. The firm is **not broker-backed**, meaning there's limited external oversight during evaluation and funded phases. Key rules — including payout caps, consistency requirements, and drawdown types — **vary significantly between challenge models**, and some accounts carry strict limitations that aren't always clear upfront.","src/content/reviews/rev-blue-guardian.json","5188822bc02ed7a2","rev-blueberry-funded",{"id":3318,"data":3320,"filePath":3360,"digest":3361},{"id":3318,"propFirmId":335,"summary":3321,"pros":3322,"cons":3327,"bestFor":3331,"notIdealFor":3332,"overallScore":3333,"categoryScores":3334,"categorySections":3335,"verdictBlocks":3343,"faq":3347,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"We've ranked Blueberry Funded as the 3rd best prop firm worldwide with an overall score of 93/100. It's a great option for crypto, stock, and forex trading, and they now also offer two instant funding accounts. Pricing all comes from forex broker Blueberry Markets, and fees are competitive as well, starting from just $25.\n\nBlueberry Funded scored 93/100 during testing, placing third overall in our 2026 prop firm rankings. This score reflects the full experience, from signup and platform access to challenge rules, trading conditions, and payout speed. It scored 9.5/10 for Challenges thanks to low fees and a great range of different evaluation processes, including the Synthetics Challenge – a unique option built for trading custom volatility indices. It also earned a perfect 10/10 for Markets and Leverage, offering access to over 1,100 instruments across forex, crypto, and equities.",[3323,3324,3325,3326],"Low challenge fees from $25","Crypto and stock trading available","Offers scaling up to $2 million","1,100+ instruments including synthetics",[3328,3329,3330],"Strict rules on news trading","Limited payment options","Lack of educational resources","Traders who want diverse market access (crypto, stocks, synthetics) with broker-backed pricing and low entry fees","Traders who need unrestricted news trading or a wide range of withdrawal options",93,{"challenges":600,"spreads":377,"markets":203,"payouts":377,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":3336,"spreads":3337,"markets":3338,"platforms":3339,"payouts":3340,"support":3341,"trust":3342},"Blueberry Funded offers one of the most diverse selections of challenges – two instant funding options, one and two step evaluations, plus rapid and synthetic accounts.\n\nThe **2 Step Challenge** runs across two phases, with a 10% target in Step One and a 5% target in Step Two. Daily loss limit is 5% and overall drawdown cap is 10%, both static. The **1 Step Challenge** requires a 10% target with a 6% total and 4% daily drawdown. The **Rapid Challenge** gives you 7 days to reach a 5% target. **Instant Lite** and **Instant Elite** skip evaluation entirely.\n\nBlueberry Funded also offers a **Synthetics Challenge** – unique to the firm – focused on custom volatility indices. Plus a **scaling plan** where every 3 months your account grows by 25% (up to $2M) if you hit 10% profit and complete 4 payouts.\n\nBlueberry Funded scored 9.5/10 for Challenges reflecting its strong technical design, transparent drawdown limits, realistic profit targets, and fair entry costs.","Blueberry Funded offers raw spreads from **0.1 pips** and a flat **$7 round-turn** commission on forex and gold. Crypto, indices, and commodities have no commission, while stocks carry a **$2 per lot** commission.\n\nForex spreads are competitive: EUR/USD at **0.2 pips** (industry avg 0.22), AUD/USD at **0.1 pips** (industry avg 0.46), GBP/USD at **0.2 pips** (industry avg 0.52). USD/CAD (1.2 pips) and USD/JPY (0.6 pips) are slightly above industry averages.\n\nBlueberry Funded keeps costs low with tight forex spreads and simple, fixed pricing, supporting its strong 9/10 spreads score.","Blueberry Funded gives you access to **1,100+ instruments** across forex, crypto, indices, commodities, stocks, and synthetics. The inclusion of synthetic indices with constant volatility and unique tick behaviour sets it apart from most prop firms.\n\n**Forex**: 45 pairs with up to 50:1 leverage. **Indices**: 14 instruments at 1:10. **Commodities**: 17 instruments at 1:10. **Crypto**: 52 assets at 1:2. **Stocks**: 1,000+ US stock CFDs at 1:10. **Synthetics**: 12 custom indices at 1:30.\n\nWith over 1,100 instruments and the unique addition of synthetics, Blueberry Funded earns a perfect 10/10 in this area.","Blueberry Funded gives you access to four platforms – **MT4**, **MT5**, **DXTrade**, and **TradeLocker**. MT4 and MT5 provide advanced features and EA support, while TradeLocker delivers a smooth mobile experience with a clean interface. DXTrade is functional but basic.\n\nPlatform availability varies by challenge: MT4 is available on 1 Step, 2 Step, and Rapid. MT5 and TradeLocker are available on all challenge types including Stocks. DXTrade is available on 1 Step, 2 Step, and Rapid.\n\nWe scored Blueberry Funded 9/10 for platforms after testing execution speed, layout, and tools across all four options.","With Blueberry Funded you can withdraw profits on a **14-day payout cycle** with a minimum of **$100**. Payouts are handled through **RiseWorks** and settled in crypto (USDC or USDT). Profit splits start at **80%** and increase to **90%** with add-ons.\n\nChallenge fees are paid via **crypto** (Bitcoin, stablecoins via Confirmo) or **credit/debit cards** (Visa, Mastercard) as a one-time upfront cost.\n\nBlueberry Funded scores 9/10 for payments and payouts thanks to its clear, reliable system built around a predictable withdrawal cycle and fast crypto-based processing.","Blueberry Funded provides **24/5 customer support** via email and live chat. Their FAQ section is comprehensive. However, educational resources are limited – their YouTube has only a few dozen videos. The **Discord community** with 32,700+ members serves as the primary resource for trading insights.\n\nWhile support is reliable, the firm could improve its educational offerings through stronger video content or structured learning resources.","Blueberry Funded scores 9/10 for Trust thanks to its **ASIC-regulated** backing via Blueberry Markets, an active community, and membership in **The Prop Association** – a self-regulatory body focused on fairness and certification.\n\nTrustPilot score is **3.8/5** from over 1,200 reviews. The **Discord community** has 32,700+ members, with 31,500 Instagram followers and 41,700 Twitter followers.\n\nTheir ASIC-regulated backing and founding membership in The Prop Association contribute to their strong trust score.",[3344],{"heading":3345,"body":3346},"Final Verdict on Blueberry Funded","Blueberry Funded ranks as one of the top prop trading firms in 2026 with a score of 93/100, placing 3rd overall in our shortlist of the best prop firms. The firm is well rounded with low cost challenge fees, a wide range of tradable markets, and strong rule transparency. During testing, we found consistent platform performance, reliable payouts, and a clear onboarding process, all contributing to high scores across key areas like Challenges (9.5/10), Markets (10/10), and Payouts (9/10).\n\nLastly, its backed by a regulated forex broker and now a founding member of The Prop Association, making it a strong option if you're looking for reliable access to funded trading.",[3348,3351,3354,3357],{"q":3349,"a":3350},"Does Blueberry Offer CFD Trading?","Yes, Blueberry offers CFD and forex trading through Blueberry Markets. Visit compareforexbrokers.com, our primary site that has been operating for over 10 years and has evaluations of all the top brokers, including a Blueberry Markets review.",{"q":3352,"a":3353},"Can I trust Blueberry Funded?","Yes, Blueberry Funded is a trustworthy prop trading firm supported by Blueberry Markets, a broker regulated by ASIC. The prop trading firm has a transparent challenge structure, with low fees starting at $25 and profit splits up to 90%. Payouts are processed every 14 days through RiseWorks, ensuring reliability.",{"q":3355,"a":3356},"Does Blueberry Funded offer crypto?","Yes, Blueberry Funded is one of the best crypto prop firms with access to 52 cryptocurrency pairs, including BTC/USD, ETH/USD, and LTC/USD. Traders can trade 24/7 with a maximum leverage of 1:2, accommodating the volatility of crypto markets. This selection includes both major and smaller digital assets, providing flexibility for different trading strategies.",{"q":3358,"a":3359},"Does Blueberry Funded offer scaling?","Yes, Blueberry Funded offers a scaling plan, allowing traders to increase their account balance by 25% every three months. To qualify, you must achieve a 10% net profit and process at least four payouts within the same period. You can scale your accounts up to a maximum simulated capital allocation of $2 million, as well as your profit split to 90%.","src/content/reviews/rev-blueberry-funded.json","8fa4da3bb8e5df53","rev-blueberry-futures",{"id":3362,"data":3364,"filePath":3404,"digest":3405},{"id":3362,"propFirmId":526,"summary":3365,"pros":3366,"cons":3372,"bestFor":3378,"notIdealFor":3379,"overallScore":3380,"categoryScores":3381,"categorySections":3382,"verdictBlocks":3390,"faq":3394,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"With an overall rating of 85/100, Blueberry Futures enters the market as a new futures-focused arm of the Blueberry brand, offering two one-step challenges with fast execution and clear trading rules. You can trade deep-liquidity CME markets covering forex, commodities, and indices on the prop firm's BlackArrow futures trading platform.\n\nBlueberry Futures is the second major prop trading product launched under the Blueberry Markets brand, following the success of Blueberry Funded, their CFD-based prop firm. The setup is intentionally simple — you have two one-step challenges, identical targets across all account sizes, and a choice between the more forgiving Ascent (end-of-day drawdown) or the tighter Accelerated (real-time trailing drawdown). Fast execution through BlackArrow and a focused CME market list keep the trading conditions clean and predictable, giving you a user-friendly and straightforward path to funded trading without unnecessary complexity.",[3367,3368,3369,3370,3371],"Broker backed by ASIC regulated Blueberry Markets","Simple one-step challenges with clear rules","No commissions or hidden trading fees","Strong CME market selection with deep liquidity","Fast execution on BlackArrow",[3373,3374,3375,3376,3377],"Manual trading only, no automation","No overnight or weekend holds","Payout caps and buffer reduce flexibility","Single platform option","Strict DCA and behaviour rules","Futures traders who value clear rules, fast execution, and strong broker backing from an ASIC-regulated parent company","Grid traders, heavy martingale users, and anyone who depends on automation, overnight swing holding, or needs multiple platform options",85,{"challenges":377,"spreads":377,"markets":377,"payouts":101,"platforms":66,"trust":377},{"challenges":3383,"spreads":3384,"markets":3385,"platforms":3386,"payouts":3387,"support":3388,"trust":3389},"Blueberry Futures offers two one-step challenges — **Ascent** (EOD drawdown) and **Accelerated** (trailing drawdown) — across $50K, $100K, and $150K account sizes. Both share the same profit targets ($3,000, $6,000, $10,000) and 30-day completion window. Ascent requires 2 active days with $200+ profit, while Accelerated needs just 1 day. Fees start at **$184** (Accelerated) and **$245** (Ascent). No daily loss limit — only the global drawdown matters. Contract caps scale with account size: 2/6/9 minis or 20/60/90 micros. Blueberry earned **9/10** for challenges.","Blueberry Futures uses a **commission-free** structure where all execution costs are built into the BlackArrow environment. No per-contract platform fees, routing charges, or exchange costs during evaluations or funded accounts. The one-off challenge fee covers full access to BlackArrow, real-time Level 1 CME data, and all supported markets. Optional costs include the **$61/month** professional DOM feed and a monthly subscription for premium analytics and 15% reset discounts. Reset fees range from **$79–$310** depending on account type and size. Blueberry earned **9/10** for pricing.","Blueberry Futures provides a focused set of **CME futures** covering index futures (ES, NQ, RTY, EMD), micro equities (MES, MNQ, M2K), forex futures (6E, 6B, 6A, 6C, 6J, 6S, 6N), livestock (HE, LE, GF), and micro crypto (MBT, MET). All instruments trade on CME, CBOT, NYMEX, or COMEX with standard tick values and contract caps per account size. The absence of crypto, stocks, ETFs, or energy futures trims a point. Blueberry earned **9/10** for markets.","Blueberry Futures uses **BlackArrow** as its sole trading platform across evaluations and funded accounts. The platform is purpose-built for futures with fast execution, DOM support, and chart tools. Desktop offers the most complete setup, web trader is reliable for routine management, and the mobile app suits monitoring. No MT4/MT5/TradingView integration. Manual execution required under Blueberry rules — no automation hooks or copy trading features. Blueberry earned **7.5/10** for platforms.","Profit splits reach up to **90%**. Payout cycles require five profitable trading days with at least $200 net profit each. Withdrawals range from **$500 to $2,500** per cycle. A $2,100 account buffer must be maintained after each payout. Blueberry processes withdrawals through **RiseWorks** (bank transfers) and **USDT on TRC-20**. KYC verification through Veriff is required before the first withdrawal. Blueberry earned **8/10** for payouts.","Blueberry Futures has 7-day customer support availability with ticketing and chat. The Discord server provides announcements, promotions, and community discussion. Educational tools sit inside the dashboard — the monthly subscription provides extended analytics, heatmaps, and journaling features. No formal course or training library is available. Blueberry earned **7/10** for support.","Blueberry Futures is backed by **Blueberry Markets**, an **ASIC-regulated** CFD brokerage, and supported by the established **Blueberry Funded** prop firm. The wider ecosystem includes over 15,000 active traders and $3.6 million in total payouts. Country restrictions cover Australia, Russia, Belarus, Iran, Myanmar, Sudan, Zimbabwe, and sanctioned Ukrainian regions. As a newly launched futures product, it does not yet have Trustpilot history but benefits heavily from its parent brand infrastructure. Blueberry earned **9.5/10** for trust.",[3391],{"heading":3392,"body":3393},"Blueberry Futures Final Score","Blueberry Futures lands at 85/100 overall, helped by strong challenges, tight pricing, deep CME markets, and one of the best trust profiles in the futures prop space. It suits traders who already understand futures behaviour and want a clean, rules-based trading environment backed by a regulated brokerage, rather than a flashy start-up. Ascent is a good fit if you like EOD-style risk with room to hold through noise, while Accelerated appeals more to disciplined intraday traders who are comfortable protecting equity highs.\n\nIt will not suit everyone — grid traders, heavy martingale users, and anyone who depends on automation or overnight swing holding will likely find the rules too restrictive. If you want the broadest platform choice, or you rely heavily on built-in news and research, you may prefer a different setup like FXIFY Futures or FundedNext Futures.\n\nBut for futures traders who value clear rules, consistently fast execution, and strong CFD broker backing, it's one of the best futures prop firms.",[3395,3398,3401],{"q":3396,"a":3397},"Is Blueberry trusted?","Yes, Blueberry is considered a trusted brand because it is a broker-backed prop firm, connected to Blueberry Markets, a regulated CFD brokerage, and supported by the established Blueberry Funded prop firm. While Blueberry Futures itself is new and still building independent reviews, the wider ecosystem provides a stable operational base, treasury management, and verified payout history.",{"q":3399,"a":3400},"Is Blueberry Futures commission free?","Yes, Blueberry Futures is effectively commission free because all execution costs are already built into the BlackArrow environment. You do not pay separate routing fees, platform charges, or per-contract commissions during evaluations or funded accounts. You only pay the initial challenge fee, optional add-ons, or a reset if you breach the drawdown.",{"q":3402,"a":3403},"Is prop trading high risk?","Yes, prop trading is high risk because strict drawdown limits mean any breach ends the account immediately. In futures, that risk feels sharper due to fast price movement and contract volatility. The difference compared to trading your own capital is that your financial risk is capped at the initial challenge fee and any resets, rather than losses coming directly from your personal funds.","src/content/reviews/rev-blueberry-futures.json","4eea161f78f16277","rev-brightfunded",{"id":3406,"data":3408,"filePath":3456,"digest":3457},{"id":3406,"propFirmId":587,"summary":3409,"pros":3410,"cons":3415,"bestFor":3419,"notIdealFor":3420,"overallScore":600,"categoryScores":3421,"categorySections":3422,"verdictBlocks":3430,"faq":3434,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":637},"BrightFunded is one of the top rated prop firms we've reviewed, scoring 95/100 overall. It has a two step challenge with great customisations, profit splits to 100%, unlimited scaling, and a loyalty program that means you are always earning redeemable tokens, plus they've just introduced MT5 on top of cTrader and DXTrade.\n\nBrightFunded received one of the higher scores of 95/100 because the prop firm gives you a few features you won't find anywhere else. This includes an unlimited scaling plan (ie grow your account as much as you want) and a trader loyalty program where you earn tokens for any trading activity, not just successful trades. Tokens can be redeemed for things like free evaluations or higher profit splits, meaning all time you spend trading is improving your experience.",[3411,3412,3413,3414],"Up to 100% profit split","Unlimited scaling plan","35 crypto markets","Trade2Earn loyalty program",[3416,3417,3418],"Simulated trading environment","Higher fees for some add-ons","Withdrawals in EUR (bank) or USDC (crypto) only","Traders who want unlimited scaling, up to 100% profit splits, and a loyalty program that rewards all trading activity","Traders who prefer a broker-backed firm or need a wider range of withdrawal options",{"challenges":203,"spreads":377,"markets":203,"payouts":203,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":3423,"spreads":3424,"markets":3425,"platforms":3426,"payouts":3427,"support":3428,"trust":3429},"To get a BrightFunded trading account you need to work through a traditional two step evaluation process. They keep things simple with just one model with a default 80% profit share, but you can choose an account size between $5K and $200K, with fees ranging from **€55 to €975** without addons.\n\nThe rules are easy to follow — in Step 1 you need to reach an **8% profit target**, then Step 2 it drops to **5%**. At both steps risk requirements are the same, with a **5% daily drawdown** and **10% overall**. The daily permitted loss (5%) is calculated from the highest balance or equity recorded at **end of day (EOD high-watermark)** for new accounts. A minimum of **5 trading days** is required for both Challenge and Verification, and each trade must stay open for at least **1 minute** to count. There's no maximum days or time limit. Accounts are deactivated after **30 calendar days** of inactivity.\n\nBrightFunded does let you trade news during the evaluation, with no restrictions, which is a massive perk not offered by many prop firms. But it is worth noting once you become a funded trader (Funded Star Account), there is a **10-minute window** (5 minutes before and 5 minutes after) around significant news events where trading is prohibited.\n\nA **15% bonus** of your combined Phase 1 and Phase 2 profits is added to the starting balance of your Funded Star Account after reaching 10% growth, rewarding strong evaluation performance with additional funded capital.\n\nIf you want to customise your funded account, BrightFunded offers one of the best selections of paid addons available. You can modify your profit payouts, evaluation process, and fees: **Weekly Payouts** (25% fee), **Bi-Weekly Payouts** (15% fee), **100% Challenge Fee Refund** (10% fee), **90% Profit Split** (20% fee), **No Minimum Trading Days** (15% fee), and **Swap Free Account** (10% fee). Note that the 100% profit split is not a purchasable add-on — it is earned via the scaling plan from the 3rd scale-up onwards.\n\nOne of BrightFunded's best features is their **unlimited scaling plan** for funded traders. Every 4 months you can increase your account size by 30% of the original amount as long as you've been consistently trading. To qualify, you need to be profitable in 2 of 4 months, reach a combined profit of 10%, complete two profit payouts, and finish the period in a positive or breakeven balance. What makes the scaling plan so good is there's no cap — you can continue growing your account long term. Plus, once you hit your third scale up, you are rewarded with a **100% profit split**.\n\nTheir **Trade2Earn** program is another reason why they scored a perfect 10/10 for challenges. Instead of only rewarding profitable trades, you earn tokens for every trade you place, no matter the outcome. These tokens add up automatically in your dashboard based on your trading volume, and you can redeem them for discounts, new evaluations, higher profit splits, lower profit targets, increased drawdown limits, or double challenges.\n\nBrightFunded scored a perfect 10 here because their evaluation process is simple and clear, the rules are fair, and there's no time limit. Plus, you can fully customise your funded account with the biggest range of add-ons we've seen, and the unlimited scaling plan and loyalty program add more long term value than any prop firm we've reviewed.","When we tested BrightFunded's evaluation process and funded accounts we were pleasantly surprised with their spreads and fees. Despite being an independent prop firm that isn't broker backed, it's just as competitive with forex spreads from **0 pips**, and usually averaging **0.1 pips**.\n\nFor crypto, Bitcoin spreads start as low as **$0.1** and average about **$1**, which is far better than the $5 to $10 crypto spreads you'll find at other firms. Other popular digital assets like Ethereum also come in tight, and indices and commodities follow suit, with pricing aggregated from sources like S&P, Nasdaq, ICE, and FTSE to mirror real time market conditions.\n\nWe found BrightFunded's commission fees to be simple and transparent: **Forex** at $3 per lot per side, **Crypto** at 0.024% of trading volume, **Commodities** at 0.0010% of trading volume, and **Indices** with no commission fees (included in the spread).\n\nThis straightforward fee model aligns with or just below industry standards. For instance, the industry average commission fee is $3.50, and BrightFunded is just below this at **$3 per side** for foreign exchange.\n\nBrightFunded scored 9/10 for pricing because their spreads on major forex pairs and crypto are some of the best in the industry, and commissions are both predictable and fair.","BrightFunded has one of the wider product ranges we've seen from an independent prop firm, with crypto market access being one of their best features.\n\nYou can trade forex pairs, indices, commodities, and a massive selection of crypto products, each with decent leverage: **Forex** with 49 currency pairs including majors, minors, and exotics with leverage up to **100:1**; **Commodities** including gas, oil, and metals with **1:40 leverage**; **Indices** with global indices at **1:20 leverage**; and **Cryptocurrencies** with **35 digital assets** including Bitcoin, Ethereum, Solana, plus meme coins and community tokens with **5:1 leverage** (above the industry average of 2:1).\n\nBrightFunded scored 10/10 for markets and leverage because they offer major asset classes with higher leverage than most, without being overly risky. If you want to focus on forex and crypto markets, they are really strong here and offer 100:1 and 5:1 leverage, respectively, which is above the industry average of 30:1 and 2:1.","You can choose between three popular trading platforms with **cTrader**, **DXTrade**, and now **MetaTrader 5** available. This gives you desktop, web, and mobile app options along with good trading tools to develop your strategies. Regardless of the platform you pick, both evaluations and funded accounts operate via a simulated trading environment with demo accounts.\n\n**MetaTrader 5 (MT5)** is the most popular trading platform in prop firms, and BrightFunded's version comes with everything you'd expect — advanced charting tools, one-click trading, and full support for Expert Advisors. It's the natural choice if you're already familiar with MT4/MT5 or rely on automated trading strategies.\n\n**cTrader** is more suited if you want automated trading with more advanced features and Depth of Market (DoM). You'll get over 60 indicators, multiple chart types and timeframes, plus fast order execution and clean design.\n\n**DXtrade** is a more customisable option built for discretionary and hybrid traders, but it wouldn't be our first option. While it includes real-time risk monitoring and over 80 technical indicators, we ran into glitches when testing the platform and ultimately swapped to MT5.\n\nTrading rules are the same across platforms and generally relaxed, with **EAs allowed** and hedging permitted within one account. Copy trading is only permitted between accounts held by the same person — copying others is strictly prohibited. News trading has no restrictions during evaluation, but on Funded Star Accounts there is a **10-minute window** (5 minutes before and 5 minutes after) significant news events where trading is prohibited.\n\nBrightFunded scored 9/10 here because adding MT5 alongside cTrader and DXtrade gives you solid options for both manual and automated strategies. The platforms cover everything you need — execution is fast and rules are fair, but they lost a point because of the issues we ran into with DXtrade.","BrightFunded has a great payment and payout system, with the potential to work up to a **100% profit split** via the scaling plan, plus a **15% evaluation profit bonus** that adds a percentage of your Phase 1 + Phase 2 profits to your funded account balance after reaching 10% growth.\n\nWhen you sign up you pay a one-time challenge fee between **€55 to €975**, with no recurring fees after. If you buy the add-on for a fee refund you'll get this back once you get your funded account, and if you've got enough tokens you can use these to pay for upfront fees too. Payment methods include credit card, bank transfer, and crypto like Bitcoin or Ethereum.\n\nThe default profit split starts at **80%** but if you want more from day one you can buy the add-on for a **90% split**. Then, as your scaling plan upgrades you'll get a **100% profit share** from the third scale up — this is not a purchasable add-on but earned through the scaling plan.\n\nThe first payout can be requested **30 days after the first trade** on your funded account. Subsequent payouts follow a **bi-weekly (14 days)** schedule by default, with an add-on option for weekly payouts. There's **no minimum withdrawal**. Bank transfers are processed exclusively in **Euros (€)**, while crypto payments are processed in **USDC (ERC-20)**. Processing is quick, and outside processor fees are minimal.\n\nBrightFunded earns another 10/10 here because fees are transparent, payouts are frequent and go up to 100%, and there's a range of ways you can tailor things to your liking. There's also no minimum withdrawal amount which is rare.","BrightFunded is constantly improving their educational content, and their customer service team is available **24/7** which is great for weekend crypto traders.\n\nSupport is available around the clock through **email, live chat, or WhatsApp**, and we were never left waiting when we needed help. When testing support we found their live chat and WhatsApp to be the quickest, and if you want in-person support they have a main office in **Amsterdam**.\n\nOn the education side, BrightFunded isn't offering a full trading academy, but they cover what you need to trade effectively within their system. The FAQ section is detailed and answers most questions on rules, payouts, and platforms. Platform guides are available in both text and video, which makes it easier for newer traders to get comfortable with cTrader, DXtrade, or MT5.\n\nBrightFunded scored highly here because support is genuinely available 24/7 and their resources make it easy to understand how the firm works. While advanced traders won't find deep strategy lessons, beginners will appreciate the clear guides and instant access to help when they need it.","BrightFunded has a good reputation and is popular among European traders being a Polish prop firm.\n\nBrightFunded holds an excellent **TrustPilot score of 4.4 out of 5 stars**, with 81% of users giving the prop firm a perfect 5/5 stars. Reviews talk about the clear trading rules with no surprises, and how it's a great prop firm for long-term trading. Others comment on the speed of payouts, sometimes being received in as little as 5 hours.\n\nAlthough only being a few years old, BrightFunded already has a huge **Discord community** where you can access info on markets, rules, training, as well as direct support from their customer service team. They also have a strong social media presence and will post promotions and competitions on both platforms.\n\nBrightFunded scored 9/10 for trust and community, which is the highest score we've given out to a non-broker-backed firm in this area. That's because they have had a consistently high Trustscore since they started operating a few years ago, with an engaged community free to access.",[3431],{"heading":3432,"body":3433},"Final Verdict on BrightFunded","BrightFunded earnt a high overall score of 95/100 with a solid offering across the board. Challenges received a 10/10 thanks to a clear two step evaluation, high profit payouts, and a great loyalty program. Payments and payouts, as well as markets and leverage, also earnt perfect 10s.\n\nSpreads and fees scored 9/10 thanks to tight spreads, while platforms and tools landed 9/10 too. Overall, they are second place on our top 10 prop firm shortlist, and the only firm not connected to a forex broker to earn a score over 90.\n\nGiven it's great range of features and products, most prop traders will find something they like here, but if you are focusing on crypto markets it should definitely be on your radar.",[3435,3438,3441,3444,3447,3450,3453],{"q":3436,"a":3437},"Is BrightFunded a legit prop firm?","Yes, BrightFunded is a legitimate prop firm, popular among European traders as it has offices in the Netherlands and Poland. You can take their two step evaluation and if successful, you'll get a funded account where you can scale up to a 100% profit split.",{"q":3439,"a":3440},"Does BrightFunded provide access to cryptocurrency markets?","Yes, BrightFunded offers one of the best selections of crypto markets, with over 35 digital assets available to trade. They earnt 1st place on our shortlist of the best crypto prop firms thanks to offering major coins like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Solana, as well as meme coins and a range of altcoins. Bitcoin spreads are tight starting from $0.1 and averaging $1, and you get 5:1 leverage regardless of where you are based.",{"q":3442,"a":3443},"What is the max allocation for BrightFunded?","The maximum funded capital allocation per trader is $400,000 — there is no limit during the Challenge phase. The biggest account you can buy is $200K, but BrightFunded's unlimited scaling plan lets you grow from there. Every four months you can increase your account by 30% of the original size each time, making it one of the few firms with real long term growth potential.",{"q":3445,"a":3446},"What is the best prop firm?","We ranked DNA Funded as the best prop trading firm, with second place going to BrightFunded. DNA Funded won thanks to being a broker backed prop firm with super competitive pricing, earning 97/100 during testing. While BrightFunded wasn't far behind, scoring 95/100.",{"q":3448,"a":3449},"How does BrightFunded work?","BrightFunded works like most prop firms: you prove your skills in an evaluation process, then trade a funded account and keep most of the profits. The unique thing about BrightFunded is you can scale your account with no cap, unlock up to a 100% split, and earn Trade2Earn tokens on every trade. These tokens can be redeemed for perks like free challenges, increased profit splits, or more relaxed trading rules, meaning it's set up well for long term traders.",{"q":3451,"a":3452},"How do you pass the BrightFunded challenge?","You pass BrightFunded's challenge by hitting the profit targets while respecting the risk management rules and minimum trading days. To pass step 1 you need to reach an 8% profit target, then it drops down to 5% at Step 2. At both stages you need to avoid rule breaches and stay within the 5% daily drawdown and 10% overall cap. If successful, you then receive your funded account.",{"q":3454,"a":3455},"Does BrightFunded accept US traders?","Yes, BrightFunded accepts US traders and is considered one of the best prop firms in the USA, as the only restricted countries are those under international sanctions, like Belarus, Cuba, Iran, Myanmar, North Korea, Russia, Sudan, Syria, and specific regions in Ukraine and Vietnam. If you are a US based trader you are eligible for BrightFunded's challenges.","src/content/reviews/rev-brightfunded.json","1ce5261dd492fa61","rev-city-traders-imperium",{"id":3458,"data":3460,"filePath":3497,"digest":3498},{"id":3458,"propFirmId":645,"summary":3461,"pros":3462,"cons":3469,"bestFor":3476,"notIdealFor":3477,"overallScore":801,"categoryScores":3478,"categorySections":3479,"verdictBlocks":3480,"faq":3484,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"City Traders Imperium (CTI) is an established prop firm founded in 2018 that focuses on structured funding models rather than aggressive growth. You can choose between One Step and Two Step challenges or Instant Funding programs, all of which run on simulated accounts with no time limits and balance-based drawdown rules. Scaling is available, but meaningful growth mainly applies to Instant Funding accounts rather than evaluation challenges.\n\nCompared to newer prop firms, CTI is more restrictive – account sizes are smaller, leverage is low across all account types, and market coverage is limited, with no stocks and fewer instruments than competitors like DNA Funded or Blueberry Funded. Profit splits can reach 100%, but they start lower on Instant Funding and only improve after hitting multiple profit milestones, which slows early earnings.\n\nCTI is best suited to traders who prefer slower progression, strict risk controls, and long-term consistency over flexibility or fast payouts. If you’re looking for higher leverage, larger starting capital, or broader markets, there are stronger options available in 2026.",[3463,3464,3465,3466,3467,3468],"Scaling up to $4 million across multiple accounts","Instant Funding accounts with no evaluation required","Monthly salary payments for consistent funded traders","No time limits on any challenge type","Balance-based (static) drawdown on evaluation challenges","Competitive $5 roundturn forex commissions",[3470,3471,3472,3473,3474,3475],"US clients restricted to MatchTrader platform only","No stock or share trading available","Maximum $100,000 individual account size","Low leverage compared to competitors (1:30 forex challenges)","Profit splits start at 50% on Instant Funding","Only 50 tradeable instruments","Traders who prefer slower progression, strict risk controls, and long-term consistency over flexibility or fast payouts","Traders looking for higher leverage, larger starting capital, broader markets, or firms with stock trading and higher starting profit splits",{"challenges":101,"spreads":66,"markets":66,"payouts":66,"platforms":66,"trust":66},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3481],{"heading":3482,"body":3483},"Our Final Verdict On City Traders Imperium","City Traders Imperium is a viable option if you want multiple routes to funding, including One Step, Two Step, and Instant Funding programs, all with no time limits and balance-based drawdown rules. You trade on simulated funded accounts and can scale capital by hitting fixed profit milestones, with profit splits that increase over time and can reach 100% under the VIP structure.\n\nThat said, account sizes, leverage, and market coverage are more limited than many competitors, so CTI makes more sense if you prioritise clear rules and long-term progression over higher risk or aggressive exposure.",[3485,3488,3491,3494],{"q":3486,"a":3487},"How do CTI challenges work?","City Traders Imperium prop challenges work by requiring you to hit profit targets while staying within fixed drawdown rules, with no time limits to pass. You can choose a One Step Challenge with a single target, a Two Step Challenge that splits the evaluation into two phases, or skip evaluations entirely with Instant Funding and Instant Funding Pro, where you trade on a simulated funded account immediately and scale as you hit profit milestones.",{"q":3489,"a":3490},"Does City Traders Imperium accept US clients?","Yes, City Traders Imperium is a prop firm accepting US clients, but you'll be limited to using the MatchTrader platform instead of MT5. If you're based outside the US, you can access MT5, while US-based traders still have full access to CTI's challenge programs, Instant Funding models, payouts, and scaling plans through MatchTrader.",{"q":3492,"a":3493},"How much do you get paid in CTI funding?","Your profit share at CTI depends on the program you choose and how consistently you perform, starting lower and increasing as you scale. On challenge-funded accounts, you typically earn 80% and can increase up to 100%, while Instant Funding starts at 50%, then increases to 70%–100% as you progress through profit milestones and VIP levels. If you trade consistently, you can also qualify for CTI's VIP Program, which unlocks higher profit shares, faster payouts, and potential monthly salary payments.",{"q":3495,"a":3496},"What are proprietary trading firms?","Proprietary trading firms give you access to funded trading accounts so you can trade financial markets without risking your own capital. Instead of depositing money, you pay a one-time access fee and trade on a simulated account, keeping a percentage of the profits you generate as long as you follow the firm's rules on risk, drawdown, and consistency.","src/content/reviews/rev-city-traders-imperium.json","9dffe6f8ecca720b","rev-dna-funded",{"id":3499,"data":3501,"filePath":3542,"digest":3543},{"id":3499,"propFirmId":731,"summary":3502,"pros":3503,"cons":3508,"bestFor":3511,"notIdealFor":3512,"overallScore":35,"categoryScores":3513,"categorySections":3514,"verdictBlocks":3522,"faq":3526,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":783},"With a score of 97/100, DNA Funded topped the list as the best prop trading firm we've reviewed, based on pricing structure, trading tools, and trust. While still a relatively new prop firm compared to firms like FTMO and Apex Trader Funding, DNA Funded's strong partnership with forex broker DNA Markets ensures competitive spreads and reliable trading conditions.\n\nDNA Funded offers four challenges: Instant Funding, Single Helix, Double Helix, and Rapid Challenge, with account sizes ranging from 5K to 200K. Starting fees are as low as $49, with profit splits between 80% and 90% for funded traders. The prop firm also provides add-ons for faster payouts and higher profit shares, allowing you to tailor the challenges to your ideal set up.",[3504,3505,3506,3507],"24-hour payout processing","News trading & weekend holding allowed","Scaling plan up to $2M","TradeLocker with TradingView charting",[3509,3510],"Newer firm with limited track record","Smaller community than top competitors","Traders who want fast payouts and maximum flexibility in trading conditions","Traders who need a long-established firm with a large community",{"challenges":203,"spreads":203,"markets":203,"payouts":377,"platforms":377,"trust":203},{"challenges":3515,"spreads":3516,"markets":3517,"platforms":3518,"payouts":3519,"support":3520,"trust":3521},"DNA Funded offers four distinct evaluation paths to suit different trading styles. The **Single Helix** (1-step) starts at $59 for a $5,000 account — pass one phase with a 10% profit target and you're funded. The **Double Helix** (2-step) starts at $49, with a 10% Phase 1 target and 5% Phase 2 target, offering higher leverage up to 1:50 on forex pairs. The **Rapid** challenge is a time-limited 10-day sprint designed for traders who want to qualify fast. **Instant Funding** accounts grant funded status immediately with no challenge phase. All accounts carry a 5% daily drawdown and 10% maximum drawdown. The base profit split is 80%, upgradeable to 90% via an optional add-on, with a scaling plan that can grow your allocation to $2,000,000.","DNA Funded sources its liquidity through **DNA Markets**, an ASIC-regulated broker, which means traders benefit from institutional-grade pricing. Spreads on major forex pairs like EUR/USD start from **0.0 pips** with a transparent commission of $5 per lot round turn. GBP/USD spreads average around 0.1 pips. This raw-spread-plus-commission model delivers tight and predictable execution costs. Challenge fees range from **$49 to $1,209** depending on account size and challenge type — the Double Helix 2-step starts at $49 for a $5,000 account. The fee is fully refunded upon your first payout.","Funded traders can access **800+ tradeable instruments** across all major asset classes. For new purchases after February 3, forex leverage across all challenge types is **1:50**, covering majors, minors, and exotics. Global equity indices and commodities carry up to 1:10 leverage, individual stocks 1:5, and cryptocurrencies 1:2. Crypto trading is permitted across all challenges. The full instrument range spans major and exotic forex, global stock indices (US500, NAS100, UK100), precious metals (Gold, Silver), energies (Crude Oil, Natural Gas), and select digital assets. This breadth makes DNA Funded suitable for diversified multi-asset strategies.","DNA Funded supports **TradeLocker**, a modern browser-based platform with native TradingView-style charting, making it a favourite among chart-focused traders. TradeLocker offers a clean interface with advanced order types, drawing tools, and multi-timeframe analysis built in. **Expert Advisors (EAs) and algorithmic trading are allowed** on Single Helix, Double Helix, and Rapid Challenge accounts with restricted strategies, but are **prohibited on Instant Funding accounts**. Copy trading between your own accounts is permitted. A 5-minute trading restriction around high-impact news events applies on some account types — always verify your specific challenge terms before trading news.","DNA Funded's payout structure is one of the most competitive in the industry. The base profit split is **80%**, rising to **90%** with the optional performance add-on. Payouts can be requested on a **14-day cycle** by default, or every **7 days** with the accelerated add-on. Processing time is approximately **24 hours** from request to receipt — well below the industry average. Payment methods include bank transfer, cryptocurrency, and Wise. The first payout is available after just 7 trading days, and the initial challenge fee is fully refunded with that first payout, effectively making a successful challenge free.","DNA Funded provides customer support via **email**, with a growing knowledge base and FAQ section covering common questions on rules, payouts, and account management. The community **Discord server** has over 600 active members and serves as a hub for trader discussion, firm announcements, and peer support. Educational resources are expanding as the firm grows. Response times are generally within 24–48 hours during business hours. While support infrastructure is still maturing compared to larger firms, the team is responsive and the Discord community fills the gap effectively.","DNA Funded operates under the **DNA Markets** umbrella, which holds an **ASIC** (Australian Securities and Investments Commission) licence — one of the most rigorous financial regulatory frameworks globally. This institutional backing distinguishes DNA Funded from many unregulated prop firms and provides meaningful trader protection. The firm holds a **Trustpilot rating of 4.9/5** from over 3,200 verified reviews, with traders consistently praising payout speed and support quality. The community has grown to 50,000+ traders. As a firm founded in 2022, DNA Funded is still building its long-term track record, but its regulatory credentials and review volume are strong trust signals for a relatively new entrant.",[3523],{"heading":3524,"body":3525},"Final Verdict on DNA Funded","DNA Funded has quickly established itself as a standout prop trading firm, scoring a solid 97/100 in our evaluation. Backed by DNA Markets as the liquidity provider, DNA Funded delivers tight spreads, reliable trading conditions, and a strong foundation of trust.\n\nWith four challenge types (Instant Account, Single Helix, Double Helix, and Rapid Challenge) and profit splits ranging from 80% to 90%, DNA Funded provides traders with flexibility and clear paths to growth. This combination of account options, competitive fees, and favorable trading conditions means DNA Funded tops the list of best prop trading firms for 2026.",[3527,3530,3533,3536,3539],{"q":3528,"a":3529},"What is a prop trading firm?","A prop trading firm provides traders with access to firm capital in exchange for a portion of the profits they generate. Traders do not use their own money, reducing personal financial risk, but must meet specific performance targets, such as profit goals and drawdown limits. Prop trading firms often offer evaluation programs, and once traders pass, they receive funding to trade various financial markets, including forex, commodities, indices, and cryptocurrencies.",{"q":3531,"a":3532},"What is DNA Funded?","DNA Funded is a new Australian prop trading firm that just launched and is offering traders the opportunity to access firm capital through evaluation challenges. Backed by top Australian forex broker DNA Markets as their liquidity provider, DNA Funded provides competitive trading conditions, including tight spreads.",{"q":3534,"a":3535},"What is the audition process for DNA Funded?","To become a funded trader with DNA Funded you need to pass their evaluation process. These challenges include the Single Helix (1-step), Double Helix (2-step), and Rapid Challenge (1-step), with account sizes ranging from 5K to 200K. Each challenge will have specific profit targets, drawdown limit, and risk management rules.",{"q":3537,"a":3538},"What challenges does DNA Funded offer?","DNA Funded offers three main challenges: the Single Helix, Double Helix, and Rapid Challenge. The Single Helix is a 1-step evaluation with a 10% profit target, while the Double Helix involves a 2-step process with a 10% target in Phase 1 and 5% in Phase 2. The Rapid Challenge is a fast-paced 1-step challenge requiring traders to achieve a 5% profit target within 10 days. All challenges offer an 80% profit split upon completion.",{"q":3540,"a":3541},"What is the daily profit distribution limit at DNA Funded?","For new purchases after February 3, DNA Funded applies a 30% daily profit distribution limit, meaning no more than 30% of the requested payout can be credited in a single trading day. For example, if your payout request is $10,000, only $3,000 in profit from one day will count toward that payout. This rule supports consistent trading and meets broker-backed prop firm standards.","src/content/reviews/rev-dna-funded.json","28225a9f5579f815","rev-e8-markets",{"id":3544,"data":3546,"filePath":3583,"digest":3584},{"id":3544,"propFirmId":791,"summary":3547,"pros":3548,"cons":3555,"bestFor":3562,"notIdealFor":3563,"overallScore":2037,"categoryScores":3564,"categorySections":3565,"verdictBlocks":3566,"faq":3570,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":519},"E8 Markets scored 64/100 overall. It offers a genuinely broad product range — Forex, Crypto, and CME Futures under one roof with six trading platforms — but the funded-stage conditions are significantly stricter than the evaluation, with best-day rules, profitable-day requirements, payout caps, and mandatory buffers creating friction for withdrawals.\n\nThe one-step challenge structure is straightforward, and E8 One provides good customisation options for drawdown and payout splits. But Signature accounts run on fixed rules, and the lack of broker-backed execution means all trading happens on simulated feeds without disclosed liquidity providers. E8 is best suited to experienced traders who can work inside tight risk and payout rules rather than beginners looking for something simple.",[3549,3550,3551,3552,3553,3554],"Wide market access including Forex, Crypto, and CME Futures","Six trading platforms across CFD and Futures","Customisable drawdown and payout splits on E8 One","No minimum trading days on any account","Account sizes up to $500K on E8 One","Strong Trustpilot rating of 4.4/5 with ~3,000 reviews",[3556,3557,3558,3559,3560,3561],"Strict funded-stage consistency rules (best-day limits, profitable-day counts)","Payout caps on Signature accounts that only increase gradually","Simulated execution only — not broker-backed","No traditional scaling plan available","Intraday-only rules on Signature Futures","News trading restricted once funded on E8 One","Experienced traders who want broad market access across Forex, Crypto, and Futures with multiple platform options, and are comfortable managing strict funded-stage consistency and payout rules","Beginners, swing traders who need overnight holding on Signature accounts, traders who prefer broker-backed execution, or those who want simple payout rules without caps and buffers",{"challenges":31,"spreads":350,"markets":66,"payouts":360,"platforms":66,"support":31,"trust":350},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3567],{"heading":3568,"body":3569},"Our Final Verdict On E8 Markets","E8 scored 64/100 overall because the proprietary trading firm does a lot right on products and platforms, but loses ground on payout friction, strict risk rules, and only mid-range transparency. The one-step structure, flexible sizing, and strong platform lineup are genuine positives, yet the real-time trailing drawdown on E8 One and the funded-stage consistency rules make long-term retention harder than at many rivals.\n\nFrom a markets perspective, E8 is strong, with wide CFD coverage, a dedicated crypto product, and a separate CME-style futures offering, which is why it scored higher in the markets and platforms categories. But the advantages here are balanced out by conservative CFD leverage, intraday-only futures rules, and a complex payout framework built around buffers, best-day limits, profitable-day counts, and caps that start low and only scale with history.\n\nTrust and transparency sit in the middle. A positive Trustpilot score and plenty of verified payouts support E8's legitimacy, but the fully simulated setup, lack of disclosed liquidity providers, and recurring complaints about execution and risk enforcement prevent it from scoring higher. Taken together, E8 is best suited to experienced traders who can work inside tight risk and payout rules, rather than beginners looking for something simple and forgiving.",[3571,3574,3577,3580],{"q":3572,"a":3573},"Does E8 Markets actually pay out?","Yes, E8 Markets does pay out funded traders who meet the payout rules and pass KYC, and there is a large volume of verified payout reports confirming this. Withdrawals are processed through bank transfer or crypto, with approvals typically taking 1–2 business days and funds arriving within a few days after. Most payout disputes come from traders failing consistency, buffer, or risk requirements rather than non-payment.",{"q":3575,"a":3576},"Can you trade news with E8 Markets?","Yes, news trading is allowed on E8, but the rules change once you are funded and depend on the account type. During the challenge phase, news trading is permitted on all accounts. On E8 One funded accounts, certain high-impact news windows are restricted and trades placed during those periods may not count toward payouts. Signature Forex, Signature Crypto, and Signature Futures allow news trading at all stages, subject to drawdown rules.",{"q":3578,"a":3579},"Does E8 allow automated trading with Expert Advisors?","Yes, E8 allows automated trading strategies with Expert Advisors on most accounts, provided the trading strategy follows their rules. EAs are permitted on E8 One, Signature Forex, and Signature Crypto, as long as they are not high-frequency trading (HFT), latency arbitrage, or copy trading systems. Automated trading is not allowed on Signature Futures, which is strictly manual and intraday trading only.",{"q":3581,"a":3582},"What is the best forex prop firm?","The best forex prop firms in our rankings score 90/100 or higher, with FundedNext, DNA Funded, and BrightFunded leading the list due to flexible challenge structures, clearer payout rules, and stronger long-term scaling. While E8 is a legitimate firm, it does not make our top 10 forex prop firms for traders worldwide shortlist, mainly because its funded-stage consistency rules, payout caps, and simulated execution reduce overall flexibility compared to the highest-rated forex-focused competitors.","src/content/reviews/rev-e8-markets.json","11878f5cc73967c6","rev-earn2trade",{"id":3585,"data":3587,"filePath":3605,"digest":3606},{"id":3585,"propFirmId":873,"summary":3588,"pros":3589,"cons":3592,"bestFor":3597,"notIdealFor":3598,"overallScore":347,"categoryScores":3599,"verdictBlocks":3600,"verified":110,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":3604,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Earn2Trade scored 35/100 in our assessment. While its educational resources stand out as a genuine strength for beginners wanting to learn futures trading, the firm falls short in almost every other area. Challenges are overly restrictive, monthly subscription fees are steep, trading rules are rigid, and the profit split sits well below the industry average at just 80%. Experienced traders will find far better options elsewhere.",[3590,3591],"Good educational resources","Multiple trading platforms",[3593,3594,3595,3596],"Strict trading rules and evaluations","Monthly subscription fees","Low profit split (80%)","Vague funded account rules","Beginners who want to learn futures trading with educational support included","Experienced traders who want competitive splits, flexible rules, or a fast path to payouts",{"challenges":613,"pricing":373,"platforms":597,"trust":2772},[3601],{"heading":3602,"body":3603},"Our Verdict: 35/100","Earn2Trade earnt a low overall score of 35/100, with its only strength being solid educational resources. For beginners wanting to learn more, Earn2Trade's resources are appealing. However, the challenge is far too limiting for experienced traders and rules are very rigid.\n\nEarn2Trade is one of the older prop firms, but that doesn't mean it's better. Although you can get accounts up to $400K — which is very large for futures trading — it comes with lower profit splits and vague rules. Evaluation fees are high, ranging from $150 to $550 per month, and data fees are charged on top. A $10 withdrawal fee applies to payouts under $500.\n\nThe firm provides customer support through email and live chat, but the overall experience doesn't justify the cost when compared to modern alternatives that offer higher splits, clearer rules, and faster payouts.","We do not recommend Earn2Trade due to strict trading rules, high monthly subscription fees, and a below-average profit split of just 80%. The evaluation process is overly restrictive and funded account rules remain vague.\n\nOur testing scored Earn2Trade **35/100**, and we only recommend firms scoring 50/100+. For a better futures trading experience with clearer rules and higher splits, consider [Topstep](/reviews/topstep) or [FXIFY Futures](/reviews/fxify-futures).","src/content/reviews/rev-earn2trade.json","d564271f072ace30","rev-eightcap",{"id":3607,"data":3609,"filePath":3641,"digest":3642},{"id":3607,"propFirmId":935,"summary":3610,"pros":3611,"cons":3618,"bestFor":3623,"notIdealFor":3624,"overallScore":674,"categoryScores":3625,"categorySections":3626,"verdictBlocks":3627,"faq":3631,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 89/100, Eightcap Challenges is one of the highest-scoring prop firms we've reviewed. What sets it apart is that the entire challenge program is operated directly by a regulated forex broker rather than an independent prop firm. You get access to Eightcap Challenges' own live pricing, execution feed and trading platforms (MT4, MT5 and TradeLocker), but within prop-style rules and targets.\n\nThe One Step, Two Step and Day Trader challenges cover both structured, multi-day evaluations and fast, timed sessions, with extremely competitive tight spreads from 0 pips and a $5 round-turn commission on non-crypto CFDs. We think this will suit serious forex traders who want a trading environment that feels familiar and efficient.",[3612,3613,3614,3615,3616,3617],"Raw spreads from 0 pips with fast execution","MT4, MT5, and TradeLocker platform access","Unique Day Trader challenge format (1-8 hour sessions)","Operated directly by an ASIC/FCA-regulated broker","Three distinct challenge types for different trading styles","Clear, transparent rules across all account types",[3559,967,3619,3620,3621,3622],"Strict news trading restrictions during payout stage","Higher fees on larger account sizes","14-day wait before first payout on standard challenges","One Step accounts have a 5% payout cap for the first three payouts","Serious forex traders who want broker-level infrastructure, regulated oversight, and consistent pricing with multiple challenge formats including unique short-session Day Trader challenges","Traders wanting traditional scaling plans, challenge fee refunds, US-based traders, or those needing instant payouts and unlimited profit withdrawal on standard challenges from day one",{"challenges":377,"spreads":600,"markets":377,"payouts":101,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3628],{"heading":3629,"body":3630},"Our Final Verdict On Eightcap Challenges","Eightcap Challenges earns a solid overall score of 89/100, largely because it offers something structurally different from typical prop firms — a challenge system operated directly by a regulated broker using its own pricing, infrastructure and execution environment. This removes many of the uncertainties you can face with some prop firms, such as private liquidity pools, artificial spreads or inconsistent fills.\n\nThe challenge formats are balanced and achievable, the Day Trader model offers a genuinely alternative way to prop trade, and MT4/MT5 support gives you access to a proper technical environment rather than a simplified web platform. Costs are competitive, spreads are extremely tight, and the trading rules are clear and transparent.\n\nThe main limitations are the higher fees on larger account sizes, no traditional scaling plan, and the 14-day wait before the first payout on the standard challenges. Even with those drawbacks, the overall package feels more stable and predictable than many independent prop firms because everything is built on top of Eightcap Challenges' brokerage framework, rather than outsourced infrastructure.",[3632,3635,3638],{"q":3633,"a":3634},"Is Eightcap Challenges allowed in the US?","No, Eightcap Challenges' brokerage services are not available to US residents, and the challenge accounts follow the same geographic restrictions. Traders in the United States cannot open an Eightcap Challenges live account or participate in the One Step, Two Step or Day Trader challenges. This is due to regulatory limitations rather than a technical barrier, and there are no workarounds such as VPN trading or offshore onboarding.",{"q":3636,"a":3637},"How long do Eightcap Challenges payouts take?","Eightcap Challenges payouts usually take 24 to 48 hours to process once they pass KYC and risk review, although the FAQ notes they can take 2 to 5 business days depending on your bank or crypto network. The first payout for One Step and Two Step accounts is available after 14 days, with a $100 minimum withdrawal. Day Trader payouts are instant after a successful session and can be withdrawn from $10 in crypto.",{"q":3639,"a":3640},"Is there an Eightcap Challenges demo account for challenges?","No, Eightcap Challenges does not offer a demo version of its prop challenges, because each challenge relies on a simulated live feed that must be purchased and activated through your account. The challenge environment uses the same pricing as Eightcap Challenges' live markets, but you can't trial the evaluation rules or test pass conditions without buying a challenge first. If you want to practise, you can use a free MT4 or MT5 demo, but it won't replicate challenge drawdowns or targets.","src/content/reviews/rev-eightcap.json","28c2d78752ab8762","rev-elite-trader-funding",{"id":3643,"data":3645,"filePath":3683,"digest":3684},{"id":3643,"propFirmId":1058,"summary":3646,"pros":3647,"cons":3654,"bestFor":3661,"notIdealFor":3662,"overallScore":162,"categoryScores":3663,"categorySections":3664,"verdictBlocks":3665,"faq":3669,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":3682,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":519},"Elite Trader Funding scored 47/100 in our review because while it offers wide instrument access, flexible platform support, and several unique challenge types, it falls short in key areas that matter to serious traders. The biggest issue is its vague path to live funding — you are required to pay for Sim-Funded access after passing, but there's no clear process for when or if real capital will follow.\n\nThe model is payout-friendly on the surface, but with unclear promotion rules, high ongoing costs, and strict trade rules, ETF feels more like a subscription-based payout system than a traditional prop firm. It may suit futures traders who want short-term payout opportunities, but anyone seeking predictable long-term capital should approach with caution.",[3648,3649,3650,3651,3652,3653],"Full access to major US futures exchanges (CME, CBOT, COMEX, NYMEX)","Weekly profit payouts with 100% split on first $12,500","Active Discord community with nearly 16,000 members","Six evaluation models covering different trading styles","Broad platform support with no vendor lock-in","Free real-time exchange data during evaluation phase",[3655,3656,3657,3658,3659,3660],"No clear or guaranteed path to real funding after evaluation","Activation fees ($80/month or $150–$300) required for Sim-Funded access","Sim-Funded accounts are demo-based — not real capital","High monthly exchange data fees ($128/venue) on LIVE Elite accounts","24% of Trustpilot reviews are 1-star with payout disputes common","No live chat or phone support available","Experienced futures traders who want short-term payout access with flexible platform options and are comfortable with a subscription-based model that may not lead to real funded capital","Traders seeking a transparent, guaranteed path to live funding, beginners who need structured guidance, or anyone uncomfortable with ongoing monthly costs and demo-based funded accounts",{"challenges":613,"spreads":31,"markets":31,"payouts":31,"platforms":350,"support":31,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3666],{"heading":3667,"body":3668},"Our Final Verdict On Elite Trader Funding","Elite Trader Funding is a mixed bag. On one hand, it provides full exchange access, several evaluation models, and flexible platform options. On paper, it caters well to futures traders who want variety and weekly payout potential. But when you dig deeper, the structure feels more like a recurring subscription system than a straightforward path to real capital.\n\nThe biggest red flag is the lack of transparency around real funding. Passing an evaluation just unlocks another simulated stage with added fees and stricter rules. There's no published path to LIVE Elite access, and approvals are entirely at ETF's discretion. Some traders are upgraded, others aren't, with no clear explanation. That's a risk many won't want to take.\n\nAdd in high monthly costs once live, strict contract limits, and mixed reviews around payouts, and the appeal starts to wear thin. Yes, ETF does pay out and maintain an active community, but the model leans heavily in the firm's favour. You pay to stay in, and real capital remains optional from their side.\n\nFor experienced traders looking for short-term payout access and who are comfortable trading futures in a controlled environment, ETF might be worth a trial. But if you're looking for a predictable, structured route to long-term funding, this probably isn't it.",[3670,3673,3676,3679],{"q":3671,"a":3672},"Does Elite Trader Funding pay out?","Yes, Elite Trader Funding does pay out, but only if you meet specific account conditions and payout buffers. After passing an evaluation, traders must activate a Sim-Funded account and follow strict rules before withdrawing. You need at least 10 active trading days and must exceed the drawdown buffer by a set amount. While many users report receiving payments, others have faced denials, so understanding payout rules is essential before signing up.",{"q":3674,"a":3675},"What is the 10 second rule for Elite Trader Funding?","The 10 second rule at Elite Trader Funding prohibits entering and exiting a trade within 10 seconds. This rule is meant to discourage scalping and ultra-short-term trades that violate their platform usage policies. Breaking the rule can lead to disqualification or loss of profits. It applies during both evaluation and funded account stages and is enforced automatically by their monitoring systems.",{"q":3677,"a":3678},"Is Elite Trader Funding regulated?","No, Elite Trader Funding is not a regulated financial entity or a broker-backed prop firm. It operates as a futures prop trading firm using simulated accounts and does not require regulatory oversight for its core services. While live funding is offered through a broker partnership with EdgeClear, the evaluation and Sim-Funded phases are unregulated. This means there's limited external accountability.",{"q":3680,"a":3681},"How many accounts can you have on Elite Trader Funding?","Elite Trader Funding allows you to hold multiple accounts, with specific limits depending on the account type. You can run up to 20 active Sim-Funded accounts at once, including a maximum of three Fast Track accounts. However, each account must follow its own rules, and exceeding position limits across combined accounts can lead to disqualification.","Elite Trader Funding does not provide a clear, guaranteed path to real funding. After passing an evaluation, traders are placed into a **Sim-Funded account** (still demo-based) that requires additional activation fees ($80/month or $150–$300 one-time). Progression to a LIVE Elite account with real capital is entirely at the firm's discretion, with no published criteria.\n\nThe firm's model relies heavily on recurring fees, and payouts come from simulated trading performance rather than real market capital in most cases. We recommend traders research the full cost structure and funding pathway before committing.","src/content/reviews/rev-elite-trader-funding.json","9cfd2276ead0a673","rev-ftmo",{"id":3685,"data":3687,"filePath":3725,"digest":3726},{"id":3685,"propFirmId":1005,"summary":3688,"pros":3689,"cons":3693,"bestFor":3697,"notIdealFor":3698,"overallScore":3091,"categoryScores":3699,"categorySections":3700,"verdictBlocks":3708,"faq":3712,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"FTMO is a prop trading firm established in 2015, known for its structured evaluation process and profit-sharing model. Traders can earn an 80% profit split, with the potential to increase to 90% through consistent performance. The firm offers three account types — Standard, Aggressive, and Swing — catering to different trading styles and risk appetites.\n\nFTMO allows traders to automatically scale up their capital up to $2 million without needing to retake the evaluation. The evaluation process involves a two-step audition with reasonable fees starting at €155.",[3690,3691,3692],"Automatic scaling plan","90% profit split","No limits on lot sizes",[3694,3695,3696],"Two-step evaluation phase","Minimum trading days","No $1M account","Traders who want a structured evaluation, automatic scaling, and access to a wide range of platforms and educational resources","Traders who prefer one-step evaluations or need higher initial account sizes beyond $200K",{"challenges":101,"spreads":101,"markets":101,"payouts":101,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":3701,"spreads":3702,"markets":3703,"platforms":3704,"payouts":3705,"support":3706,"trust":3707},"FTMO offers three account types — **Standard**, **Aggressive**, and **Swing** — with a two-step evaluation (Challenge + Verification). Standard targets are 10% then 5%, Aggressive doubles to 20% then 10%, and Swing follows Standard rules but allows weekend/news holding with 1:30 leverage.\n\nFees range from **€155 to €1,080** for account sizes €10K to €200K, refunded with first payout. Minimum 4 trading days required. Automatic scaling increases accounts by **25% every 4 months** up to **$2 million**, with profit splits rising from 80% to 90%. FTMO scored 8/10 for challenges.","FTMO partners with various liquidity providers for institutional-grade DMA and RAW spreads. Typical spreads start at **0.22 pips** for EUR/USD, **0.65 pips** for GBP/USD, and **0.27 pips** for USD/JPY.\n\nCommissions are **$3 per standard lot** round trip for forex, 0.0040% of volume for equities, and 0.0010% for metals. While spreads are competitive, the commission charges reduce the overall score slightly. FTMO scored 8/10 for spreads.","FTMO provides access to **forex** (28 major + 14 minor + exotic pairs), **commodities** (gold, silver, oil), **14 indices** (US30, GER40, UK100), **10 cryptocurrencies** (BTC, ETH, LTC), **stocks** (AAPL, AMZN, TSLA), and **bonds**.\n\nLeverage varies: Standard/Aggressive up to **1:100** for forex, **1:50** for commodities/indices, **1:3** for stocks. Swing accounts use lower leverage (1:30 forex, 1:15 commodities). FTMO scored 8/10 for markets.","FTMO offers four platforms — **MT4**, **MT5**, **cTrader**, and **DXtrade**. MT4 has 30+ indicators and extensive EA support. MT5 adds 38 indicators, 21 timeframes, economic calendar, and real-time news. cTrader provides Depth of Market (DOM) with ECN/STP execution and cBot algorithmic trading. DXtrade is web-only with advanced charting and risk management.\n\nAll platforms support desktop, web, and mobile (except DXtrade — web only). FTMO scored 9/10 for platforms.","Profit splits start at **80%** and can increase to **90%** through the scaling plan. Payouts are monthly by default, with on-demand withdrawals available **14 days** after the first trade. Processing takes **1-2 business days** with no withdrawal fees.\n\nPayment methods include Visa, Mastercard, bank transfer, Skrill, Nuvei (Google Pay, Apple Pay), and crypto via Confirmo (BTC, ETH, USDC). No profit targets required for withdrawals. FTMO scored 8/10 for payouts.","FTMO provides **24/7 customer support** through live chat, WhatsApp, phone, and email, with fluency in **18+ languages** including Arabic, Czech, Spanish, French, German, Japanese, Swahili, Tagalog, and more.\n\nEducational resources include a Trading Academy (beginner to advanced), proprietary apps (Account MetriX, Account Analysis, Statistical App, Mentor App, Equity Simulator), performance coaching for funded traders, and an extensive blog covering trading psychology and strategy.","FTMO has an **Excellent** Trustpilot rating of **4.8/5** with over **37,000 reviews**. The firm has a strong social media presence with **519K Instagram**, **133.9K Twitter/X**, **266K Facebook**, and **415K YouTube** followers.\n\nThe Discord community has **87,700+ members**. Established in 2015 in Prague, Czech Republic, FTMO is one of the most established prop firms in the industry. FTMO scored 9/10 for trust.",[3709],{"heading":3710,"body":3711},"Final Verdict on FTMO","FTMO offers a strong overall package with a well-rounded approach in areas such as account types, trading platforms, educational resources, and customer support. The range of account types provides flexibility for different trading styles, and the automatic scaling system for profit split and capital allocation is a significant advantage for consistently profitable traders.\n\nHowever, the requirement to complete a two-step audition process and meet a minimum number of trades on specified days may be challenging for some. Additionally, the fact that FTMO charges commissions on trades and caps maximum funding at $200K before scaling are considerations to keep in mind.",[3713,3716,3719,3722],{"q":3714,"a":3715},"Can FTMO be trusted?","Yes, FTMO can be trusted, but it isn't a broker backed prop firm connected to a regulated brokerage. Established in 2015, FTMO has a strong reputation in the prop trading industry, supported by an Excellent rating on Trustpilot with over 37,000 reviews. The firm is transparent, providing clear rules and a structured evaluation process, with comprehensive customer support accessible through multiple channels.",{"q":3717,"a":3718},"How much is the FTMO payout?","FTMO offers traders a payout of 80% of their profits, with the potential to increase this to 90% through their automatic scaling system. Payouts can be requested after just 14 days from the first trade, providing flexibility and quick access to earnings. FTMO processes payouts within 1-2 business days, and there are no withdrawal fees.",{"q":3720,"a":3721},"What is the maximum leverage offered by FTMO?","FTMO offers a maximum leverage of 1:100 for Standard and Aggressive accounts, allowing traders to take larger positions with a smaller capital outlay. For the Swing account, leverage is capped at 1:30 to manage the increased risk associated with holding positions over longer periods, including weekends.",{"q":3723,"a":3724},"Does FTMO really pay?","Yes, FTMO does pay its traders, with profit splits starting at 80% and potentially increasing to 90% through consistent performance. Payouts are processed quickly, typically within one to two business days, and traders can request payouts as frequently as every 14 days. FTMO does not impose any profit targets for withdrawals, and there are no withdrawal fees.","src/content/reviews/rev-ftmo.json","f3192106a7047292","rev-funded-elite",{"id":3727,"data":3729,"filePath":3766,"digest":3767},{"id":3727,"propFirmId":1143,"summary":3730,"pros":3731,"cons":3738,"bestFor":3745,"notIdealFor":3746,"overallScore":3747,"categoryScores":3748,"categorySections":3749,"verdictBlocks":3750,"faq":3754,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":519},"Funded Elite scores 62/100 in our review, thanks to its highly customisable challenge options and wide CFD market access, offset by strict risk rules and mixed payout feedback. The prop firm offers flexible one-step, two-step, and instant funding accounts with adjustable leverage, profit splits, and payout frequency through paid add-ons.\n\nMajor strengths include dynamic scaling, free second chance resets on selected models, realistic profit targets, and a clear rule structure. The wide set of add-ons lets you tailor everything from drawdown limits to payout speed. However, strict risk rules, consistency requirements, and a concerning number of negative payout experiences from traders on forums and social media reduce overall confidence.\n\nFunded Elite is best suited to experienced traders who want maximum flexibility in challenge configuration and are comfortable managing tight drawdown and consistency limits. Beginners or traders who need reliable, friction-free payouts may want to consider higher-rated alternatives.",[3732,3733,3734,3735,3736,3737],"Multiple challenge models with fully customisable settings","Transparent and well-documented trading rules","Accessible withdrawal methods via Rise payment system","Free second chance reset on Standard Challenge","Wide market access with 300+ CFD products","Adjustable leverage, profit split, and payout frequency via add-ons",[3739,3740,3741,3742,3743,3744],"Strict rules and consistency checks that can trigger fast breaches","Expensive activation fee models on Flash Activation Challenge","Platform restrictions for US, Canada, and several other countries","Concerning number of payout complaints on forums and social media","No automation support on TradeLocker","Copy trading limited to own accounts only","Experienced traders who want maximum flexibility in challenge configuration with adjustable profit targets, leverage, drawdown limits, and payout settings, and are comfortable managing strict risk and consistency rules","Beginners, traders in restricted countries (US, Canada), those who need reliable and fast payouts without friction, or traders who rely heavily on automated strategies via TradeLocker",62,{"challenges":101,"spreads":66,"markets":66,"payouts":360,"platforms":31,"support":350,"trust":31},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3751],{"heading":3752,"body":3753},"Our Final Verdict On Funded Elite","Funded Elite earns a 62/100 because the proprietary trading firm delivers strong customisation and challenge diversity, but loses significant ground on payout reliability and trust concerns. The ability to fully configure your challenge account — adjusting leverage, profit targets, drawdown limits, profit split, and payout frequency — is genuinely rare in the prop firm space, and the clear documentation of every rule is a positive.\n\nFrom a product perspective, Funded Elite covers a lot of ground: four distinct challenge models, 300+ CFD products, broker connectivity through Purple Trading (CySEC-regulated), and raw spreads from 0 pips with a simple $3/lot/side commission. The Standard Challenge's free second chance reset and the Flash Activation's $5 pay-later entry are both notable features.\n\nHowever, the firm's reputation is mixed. While Trustpilot shows a 4.5/5 rating with 562 reviews, a concerning number of negative experiences on forums and social channels describe delayed or missing payouts. The strict risk enforcement — including the rule that you cannot risk more than half your daily loss limit on a single asset — means fast breaches are possible for traders who aren't careful. Combined with country restrictions and TradeLocker's lack of EA support, Funded Elite is a firm that rewards careful, experienced traders but may frustrate those who expect simpler, more forgiving conditions.",[3755,3758,3761,3764],{"q":3756,"a":3757},"Does Funded Elite payout?","Yes, Funded Elite processes payouts for funded trading accounts via Rise, and you can request withdrawals once you meet the required trading days. The firm follows a structured schedule beginning with a 21-day first cycle and then shifting to 14-day cycles. However, there is a concerning number of negative experiences on forums where traders report delayed or missing payments, so payout reliability remains a factor to consider.",{"q":3759,"a":3760},"What are the benefits of Funded Elite?","Funded Elite has a very customisable challenge model with multiple options including Standard, Lite, Flash (Instant Funding), and Flash Activation (pay later) models. Key benefits include adjustable leverage up to 1:100, profit split upgrades to 95%, payout frequency from 3 to 21 days, free second chance resets on Standard accounts, raw spreads from 0 pips, and access to 300+ CFD products across forex, indices, commodities, crypto, stocks, and futures.",{"q":3762,"a":3763},"Do funded accounts actually work?","Yes, funded accounts work as long as you follow the firm's rules, conditions, and payout requirements. You receive real payouts when you generate profits within the firm's defined parameters. Funded accounts rely on strict rules for risk management, and payouts are issued when you meet the quota. They are a viable trading method for accessing scale and structure without risking personal capital.",{"q":3581,"a":3765},"The best forex prop firms in our rankings score 90/100 or higher, with FundedNext, DNA Funded, and BrightFunded leading the list due to flexible challenge structures, clearer payout rules, and stronger long-term scaling. While Funded Elite offers impressive challenge customisation, it does not make our top 10 due to payout reliability concerns and strict risk enforcement that reduce overall flexibility compared to higher-rated competitors.","src/content/reviews/rev-funded-elite.json","552974f55c5d90be","rev-funded-prime",{"id":3768,"data":3770,"filePath":3784,"digest":3785},{"id":3768,"propFirmId":1244,"summary":3771,"pros":3772,"cons":3777,"bestFor":3781,"notIdealFor":3782,"overallScore":101,"categoryScores":3783,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"Funded Prime was established in Australia in 2023 and scores 80/100 in our evaluation, standing out as one of the few prop firms offering dedicated access to cryptocurrency and meme coin markets. With over 250 crypto pairs available and unique meme coin trading, it fills a niche that most prop firms overlook.",[3773,3774,3775,3776],"250+ crypto pairs available","Meme coin trading with 10:1 leverage","Up to 90% profit split","7-day payout with add-on",[3778,3779,3780],"0.1% commission on crypto trades","Weekend trading limited to meme coins only","Limited platform options","Crypto-focused traders who want extensive digital asset access and meme coin leverage","Forex-only traders or those who want commission-free crypto trading",{"challenges":101,"spreads":101,"markets":203,"payouts":66,"platforms":66,"trust":101},"src/content/reviews/rev-funded-prime.json","75d8524b48052dff","rev-funded-trading-plus",{"id":3786,"data":3788,"filePath":3832,"digest":3833},{"id":3786,"propFirmId":1281,"summary":3789,"pros":3790,"cons":3797,"bestFor":3804,"notIdealFor":3805,"overallScore":3806,"categoryScores":3807,"categorySections":3808,"verdictBlocks":3809,"faq":3813,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Funded Trading Plus (FTP) scores 77/100 overall after testing, driven by its wide range of challenge formats, including one step, two step, and instant funding models. Account sizes run from $5,000 to $200,000, with profit splits starting at 80% across standard programs but can be upgraded to 90%.\n\nFTP also is known for its aggressive scaling potential where you can grow accounts up to $5 million if performance criteria are met. Flexible payout cycles (every 3, 5, or 7 days) and optional profit split upgrades add further customisation, but the score is held back mainly by limited transparency around spreads, which makes it harder to fully assess trading costs in advance, but overall FTP remains a strong option if you want variety, scaling upside, and flexible evaluation structures.",[3791,3792,3793,3794,3795,3796],"Profit split from 80% to 90% with upgrades","Instant funding challenge available (Master program)","Aggressive scaling plan up to $5 million","Six distinct challenge types for different trading styles","Flexible payout cycles (3, 5, or 7 days)","Five trading platforms including MT4, MT5, cTrader, Match-Trader, DXTrade",[3798,3799,3800,3801,3802,3803],"Minimal transparency on spreads and trading costs","Higher fees for instant funding accounts","$25 fee for cTrader platform usage","DXTrade has reported lag and connectivity issues","Educational resources are basic","Customer support only available in English","Experienced traders who want diverse challenge formats, aggressive scaling potential up to $5 million, and flexible payout cycles with optional profit split upgrades","Traders who need clear spread data upfront, beginners seeking comprehensive educational resources, or those who prefer a single streamlined evaluation path",77,{"challenges":377,"spreads":31,"markets":101,"payouts":66,"platforms":101,"trust":377},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3810],{"heading":3811,"body":3812},"Our Final Verdict On Funded Trading Plus","Funded Trading Plus provides a solid option for traders seeking access to capital through a clear evaluation process. With a strong community, a competitive 80% profit split, and flexible account types, the firm offers a viable path for traders looking to scale their operations.\n\nHowever, the lack of transparency on trading costs and issues with the DXTrade platform may be concerns for some traders. Overall, Funded Trading Plus is a strong contender in the prop trading space, particularly for those who value community support and straightforward challenges.",[3814,3817,3820,3823,3826,3829],{"q":3815,"a":3816},"Is Funded Trading Plus trustworthy?","Funded Trading Plus is generally considered a legitimate prop firm with a large and active trading community and a long operating history compared to many newer firms. It offers clearly defined challenge structures, documented rules, and a transparent account dashboard, which helps traders understand how evaluations and funded accounts operate. That said, FTP is not a broker-backed prop firm and some traders raise concerns around spread transparency and platform consistency.",{"q":3818,"a":3819},"Does Funded Trading Plus offer a scaling plan?","Yes. Funded Trading Plus offers an aggressive performance-based scaling plan, allowing you to grow your account up to $5 million if profit milestones are met. Scaling is optional and based on hitting predefined profit targets on your funded account. There are no time-based requirements, but higher account sizes and payout conditions depend on the specific program you choose and continued rule compliance.",{"q":3821,"a":3822},"Does Funded Trading Plus payout?","Yes. Funded Trading Plus does pay out profits, provided you follow the trading rules. Payouts are not fixed weekly. Instead, you can choose payout cycles of 3 days, 5 days, or 7 days, depending on the account type and payout option selected. Withdrawals are available via bank transfer or cryptocurrency, with a minimum payout amount of $50.",{"q":3824,"a":3825},"What are the profit split and fees for Funded Trading Plus?","Profit splits start at 80% by default but depending on the program you select and any optional upgrades at checkout, you can increase your profit split to 85% or 90%. Higher payout percentages are not automatic and are tied to specific models or add-ons. Challenge fees vary by program, your one step challenges start from $119, while instant funding accounts cost more depending on account size. All FTP challenges and instant accounts offer sizes ranging from $5,000 to $200,000.",{"q":3827,"a":3828},"Which trading platforms does Funded Trading Plus offer?","Funded Trading Plus offers Match-Trader, DXTrade, MetaTrader 4 (MT4), MetaTrader 5 (MT5), and cTrader. MT4 and MT5 are well suited if you use Expert Advisors or custom indicators. Match-Trader offers TradingView integration and works well for discretionary trading. cTrader provides advanced tools but carries a $25 platform fee. DXTrade is available, though it is generally less popular due to performance limitations.",{"q":3830,"a":3831},"Is Funded Trading Plus a scam?","No. Funded Trading Plus is not a scam. It is a legitimate prop firm that provides funded trading opportunities through structured evaluation and instant funding models. That said, you should fully understand the rules, drawdown calculations, and payout conditions before signing up. FTP is best suited if you are comfortable trading within strict risk frameworks and prop firm rules.","src/content/reviews/rev-funded-trading-plus.json","5b64129871651305","rev-fundednext-futures",{"id":3834,"data":3836,"filePath":3876,"digest":3877},{"id":3834,"propFirmId":1344,"summary":3837,"pros":3838,"cons":3845,"bestFor":3851,"notIdealFor":3852,"overallScore":1989,"categoryScores":3853,"categorySections":3854,"verdictBlocks":3862,"faq":3866,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"FundedNext Futures scored 84/100 in our 2026 testing, ranking as the second best futures prop firm after FXIFY Futures. This new branch of the popular FundedNext brand uses a simple one-phase challenge with no time limit, real CME futures pricing, and no activation fees. Traders keep 100% of their profit split after passing, with withdrawals processed every five days. FundedNext Futures also offers a brand guarantee — if they don't process your withdrawal within 24 hours, they add $1,000 to your payout. Now backed by FundedNext's own regulated broker, FNmarkets, the firm has greater control over execution and payouts.",[3839,3840,3841,3842,3843,3844],"100% profit split after funding","24-hour payout guarantee ($1,000 penalty if missed)","One-phase challenge with no time limit","Unrestricted news trading","Tradovate or NinjaTrader platforms","Real CME pricing with no activation fees",[3846,3847,3848,3849,3850],"Simulated trading only","Limited futures-specific education","Not available in Canada","First withdrawal resets loss limit","No separate futures community yet","Futures traders who want a clean, rule-based setup with no hidden fees, a simple one-phase challenge, and a 24-hour payout guarantee backed by a broker-operated firm","Forex or CFD traders — FundedNext Futures is futures-only. Also not ideal for traders who rely on automated trading (EAs prohibited) or want overnight holding",{"challenges":101,"spreads":101,"markets":101,"payouts":203,"platforms":101,"trust":101},{"challenges":3855,"spreads":3856,"markets":3857,"platforms":3858,"payouts":3859,"support":3860,"trust":3861},"FundedNext Futures runs a single-phase evaluation designed for CME futures traders, with no monthly fees, no activation charges, and challenge fees starting from $129. Account sizes are $25K, $50K, and $100K with profit targets of $1,250, $2,500, and $6,000 respectively. The drawdown is trailing based on end-of-day balance. A 40% consistency rule prevents excessive profit concentration in one day. After passing, traders earn a funded account with 100% profit split. The scaling plan automatically increases contract limits as balance grows. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for challenges.","FundedNext Futures charges $3 per contract per side ($6 round-turn commission) plus a $1 exchange and regulatory fee applied only on closing. There are no activation fees, no monthly charges, and no hidden platform costs. The fee structure is straightforward and consistent across all markets. For five contracts, the total round-turn cost would be $35. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for pricing.","FundedNext Futures gives traders access to a focused range of CME Group products covering currencies, equity indices, metals, energy, and agriculture. Both mini and micro contracts are available, with micros counting as one-tenth of a mini. Contract limits scale with account size: 2 minis ($25K), 3 minis ($50K), 5 minis ($100K). The selection covers all essential categories for most futures trading strategies. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for markets.","FundedNext Futures offers two professional-grade platforms: Tradovate (cloud-based, browser-friendly, DOM trading) and NinjaTrader (desktop, advanced charting, strategy building). Both provide full CME market access. Tradovate is ideal for execution-focused traders, while NinjaTrader suits technically-driven traders who want customizability and backtesting. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for platforms.","Funded traders keep 100% of their profits with no split. The 24-hour payout guarantee with $1,000 penalty for delays sets FundedNext Futures apart. Withdrawals are available every 5 days after completing 5 Benchmark Days. Payment methods include USDT, USDC, RiseWorks, and TC Pay. Challenge fees can be paid via Visa, Mastercard, PayPal, Skrill, Apple Pay, Google Pay, AstroPay, and various cryptocurrencies. FundedNext Futures scored 10/10 for payouts.","FundedNext Futures provides 24/7 live support via live chat and email. Response times are fast and support staff are familiar with futures-specific questions. At this stage, educational resources are minimal with no dedicated learning portal for futures traders. The parent FundedNext brand has a history of building community content through Discord and YouTube. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for support.","FundedNext Futures is a new division of the established FundedNext brand, operating under its own brokerage FNmarkets. This broker-backed model improves transparency over execution and payments. The futures arm doesn't have a standalone Trustpilot rating yet but benefits from FundedNext's established reputation. The firm is available in most regions but restricted in Canada, Malta, Cyprus (North), Slovenia, and Romania. FundedNext Futures scored 8/10 for trust.",[3863],{"heading":3864,"body":3865},"Our Final Verdict On FundedNext Futures","FundedNext Futures is one of the best futures prop firms if you want a clean, rule-based setup with no hidden fees or complicated rules. The one-phase challenge is simple to follow, the scaling model is practical, and the 24-hour payout guarantee, with a $1,000 penalty if missed, shows they're serious about supporting funded traders.\n\nWhile the futures division is still developing its own education tools and community features, the core offer is strong. Now backed by FundedNext's own regulated broker, FNmarkets, the firm has greater control over execution and payouts, something few futures prop firms offer. If you're looking for a reliable prop firm that prioritizes consistency and fast access to profits, FundedNext Futures is a standout choice.",[3867,3870,3873],{"q":3868,"a":3869},"How are FundedNext and FundedNext Futures different?","FundedNext focuses on CFDs for prop trading, while FundedNext Futures is built specifically for futures traders and markets. FundedNext offers simulated CFD environments and is known for being the best forex prop firm, whereas FundedNext Futures uses real CME exchange pricing on mini and micro futures, and ranks as the second best futures prop firm. Each branch has its own rules, challenges, and payout structures, but both operate using simulated accounts with real market conditions, and are now powered by FundedNext's own brokerage, FNmarkets.",{"q":3871,"a":3872},"Does FundedNext Futures accept US clients?","Yes, FundedNext Futures accepts traders from the United States. Unlike many prop firms that restrict US applicants due to regulatory issues, FundedNext Futures is open to US residents who meet their basic eligibility requirements. Traders in the US can join, complete the futures challenge, and request payouts under the same rules as international participants, with full access to platforms like Tradovate and NinjaTrader.",{"q":3874,"a":3875},"What is the best prop firm for futures?","The best futures prop firms are FXIFY Futures, scoring 85/100, and FundedNext Futures, scoring 84/100. FXIFY Futures offers up to 100% profit splits, no evaluation time limits, and built-in TradingView charts. FundedNext Futures stands out with its 24-hour payout guarantee and one-step challenge.","src/content/reviews/rev-fundednext-futures.json","93d8f98c05fa7b56","rev-fundednext",{"id":3878,"data":3880,"filePath":3920,"digest":3921},{"id":3878,"propFirmId":1395,"summary":3881,"pros":3882,"cons":3887,"bestFor":3891,"notIdealFor":3892,"overallScore":3893,"categoryScores":3894,"categorySections":3895,"verdictBlocks":3903,"faq":3907,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 92/100, FundedNext ranked 4th in our analysis of the top prop trading firms. As of 2026, it is a broker backed prop firm with one step and two step challenges via the Stellar and Stellar Lite models.\n\nIf you are looking to prop trade futures markets rather than CFDs, FundedNext also recently launched a new futures trading branch. With FundedNext Futures, you can now take challenges with real CME futures pricing.",[3883,3884,3885,3886],"Profit splits of up to 95%","15% profit split from day one","Fortnightly withdrawals","Broker-backed via FNmarkets",[3888,3889,3890],"News trading rules on funded accounts","$25 fee for cTrader and Match-Trader","Futures requires a different account","Traders who want high profit splits, flexible evaluations, and broker-backed execution","Traders who need unrestricted news trading or prefer free platform access on all options",92,{"challenges":203,"spreads":377,"markets":377,"payouts":377,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":3896,"spreads":3897,"markets":3898,"platforms":3899,"payouts":3900,"support":3901,"trust":3902},"FundedNext offers two main models of prop challenges – **Stellar** and **Stellar Lite**. You can choose between one and two step evaluation processes for the Stellar Challenge, while Stellar Lite is two step only.\n\n**Stellar (One Step)**: A single-phase challenge with 30:1 leverage and a 10% profit target. Best for traders who want a fast track to funding. **Stellar (Two Step)**: Two-phase challenge with 100:1 leverage, 8% then 5% targets. **Stellar Lite (Two Step)**: Lower-cost entry with 100:1 leverage, 8% then 4% targets.\n\nAll models offer a **95% profit split** once funded. Stellar 1-Step and 2-Step also give you a **15% profit share during the challenge phase**. The scaling plan allows a **40% account increase** every 4 months, up to **$4 million** max allocation.\n\nFundedNext scored a perfect 10/10 for Challenges thanks to flexible models, strong add-ons, and fair entry costs.","FundedNext now operates through its own brokerage, **FNmarkets**, launched in May 2025. Spreads and execution are handled directly through FNmarkets' infrastructure rather than third-party brokers.\n\nCommission charges vary by challenge model: **Stellar 1-Step & 2-Step** charge $5 per lot for Forex and Commodities, while **Stellar Lite** charges $7 per lot. Indices and Crypto have **no commission** on any challenge type.\n\nFundedNext scored 9/10 for spreads. While real-time spread data isn't published yet, the broker-backed model should allow tighter spreads and improved execution long term.","FundedNext offers access to **83 financial markets** across four asset classes: **50 forex pairs** (majors, minors, exotics), **18 indices**, **5 commodities** (precious metals and energy), and **10 cryptocurrencies** including Bitcoin and Ethereum.\n\nFundedNext scored 9/10 for markets, providing flexibility for different trading strategies and risk tolerances.","FundedNext provides access to four trading platforms – **MT4**, **MT5** (with TradingView integration), **cTrader**, and **Match-Trader**. MT4 and MT5 are free, while cTrader and Match-Trader carry a **$25 platform fee** and aren't available on the largest account sizes.\n\nMT4 is suited for EA and indicator-focused traders. MT5 adds advanced order types and a built-in economic calendar. cTrader offers Level II market depth pricing and clean interface. Match-Trader is browser-based with no downloads required.\n\nFundedNext scored 9/10 for platforms thanks to the variety of options covering different trading styles.","FundedNext supports payments via debit/credit cards (Visa, Mastercard), bank transfer, Perfect Money, and crypto (USDT, BTC, ETH). Payouts are handled through **Deel** with a minimum withdrawal of **$20**.\n\nProfit splits start at **95%** once funded, with Stellar models also offering a **15% share during the challenge**. Payout schedule varies: Stellar 1-Step is every 5 business days, Stellar 2-Step starts monthly then moves to bi-weekly, and Stellar Lite starts at 21 days then moves to bi-weekly.\n\nFundedNext scored 9/10 for payouts thanks to the high profit splits, flexible scheduling, and reliable processing through Deel.","FundedNext offers **24/7 customer support** through email and live chat. Funded traders benefit from **Pro Support** connecting them with in-house technical experts.\n\nEducational resources include trading guides, an Economic Calendar, Psychology Feed sessions, and a **YouTube channel** with 77K+ subscribers and 1,200+ educational videos. The Risk Reward Radio podcast offers deeper insights into trader journeys.\n\nFundedNext scored well for support thanks to round-the-clock availability and a strong suite of educational materials.","FundedNext became a **broker-backed prop firm** with the launch of **FNmarkets** in 2025. This gives them control over execution, spreads, and trading infrastructure.\n\nTrustPilot score is **4.5/5** with an 'Excellent' ranking. The community spans **226,800+ Discord** members, **254,000 Instagram** followers, **167,000 Twitter** followers, **135,000 Facebook** followers, and a **59,400+ Telegram** channel.\n\nFundedNext scored 9/10 for trust thanks to the broker-backed model, excellent TrustPilot rating, and one of the largest prop trading communities online.",[3904],{"heading":3905,"body":3906},"Our Final Verdict On FundedNext","FundedNext earns a 92/100 and currently ranks 4th on our list of top prop trading firms. With both one-step and two-step evaluations, up to 95% profit splits, and strong platform support, it ticks the right boxes for traders looking for flexibility and fast payouts. The Stellar Lite model is especially cost-effective for beginners, while the add-ons make it easy to tailor each challenge to your style and goals.\n\nThe big update last year was FundedNext's shift to a broker-backed model with the launch of FNmarkets. This gives them more control over execution, pricing, and payments — something few prop firms can offer. Combined with a solid Trustpilot rating, large trading community, and strong payout record, FundedNext continues to be a reliable option whether you're new to prop trading or scaling up.",[3908,3911,3914,3917],{"q":3909,"a":3910},"Is FundedNext legit?","Yes, FundedNext is a legitimate prop trading firm with account sizes from $5,000 to $200,000 and profit splits up to 95%. In 2025, it became a broker-backed firm through the launch of FNmarkets, giving it greater control over execution and trading conditions, and is now considered one of the best prop trading firms available in 2026.",{"q":3912,"a":3913},"Do prop firms really pay?","Yes, prop firms do pay traders who meet their profit targets and follow the firm's rules. Payments are based on profit splits, typically ranging from 70% to 95%. Reputable firms like FundedNext and FTMO have a track record of reliable payouts, often processed through secure third-party platforms like Deel. However, it's important to choose a trustworthy prop firm to avoid scams.",{"q":3915,"a":3916},"How does FundedNext work?","FundedNext works by offering traders a chance to manage funded accounts after passing one of its two challenge models: Stellar or Stellar Lite. Traders must meet specific profit targets while adhering to daily and overall loss limits. After passing the challenge, traders can earn profit splits up to 95% on live accounts.",{"q":3918,"a":3919},"What are the profit split percentages for FundedNext traders?","FundedNext offers profit splits of up to 95%. Traders on Stellar 1-Step and 2-Step accounts receive a 15% profit share during the challenge and 95% once funded. Stellar Lite accounts don't pay during the challenge but also unlock 95% profit splits after funding.","src/content/reviews/rev-fundednext.json","c3994c125d17c919","rev-funding-pips",{"id":3922,"data":3924,"filePath":3960,"digest":3961},{"id":3922,"propFirmId":1462,"summary":3925,"pros":3926,"cons":3931,"bestFor":3936,"notIdealFor":3937,"overallScore":3747,"categoryScores":3938,"categorySections":3939,"verdictBlocks":3940,"faq":3944,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Funding Pips scored 62/100 in our review, offering strong platform variety, multiple challenge types, and up to 100% profit splits. While rule clarity and support could improve, it's a decent option for traders who understand the prop firm's trading rules.",[3927,3928,3929,3930],"MT5, Match-Trader, and cTrader available","Profit splits scale up to 100%","Competitive leverage for Pro Account","Multiple challenge types including instant funding",[3932,3933,3934,3935],"$20 fee required to access cTrader","Support is slow and often evasive","Limited time challenges have unclear or shifting rules","Post-funding rules are stricter than evaluation rules","Experienced traders who understand prop firm rules and want multiple challenge options with scaling potential","Beginners or traders who want fully transparent, consistent rules from evaluation through to funded accounts",{"challenges":350,"spreads":350,"markets":350,"payouts":66,"platforms":350,"trust":350},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[3941],{"heading":3942,"body":3943},"Our Verdict: 62/100","Funding Pips scored 62/100 overall in our review, with average or below-average ratings across every key category. The prop trading firm's challenge structure is a relative strength, offering variety and scaling potential. However, this is offset by ever-changing limited time models and stricter risk rules introduced only after traders are funded.\n\nThe firm also earned 6/10 for Trust due to a history of rule enforcement issues, negative trader reviews, and the temporary suspension of its Trustpilot account. Other categories like Platforms, Payouts, and Markets sit between 6/10 and 7/10, reflecting inconsistent experiences and lack of clear disclosures.\n\nOverall, while Funding Pips has scale and visibility, its operational inconsistencies, hidden conditions, and support issues make it difficult to recommend over more transparent, broker-backed alternatives like DNA Funded or BrightFunded.",[3945,3948,3951,3954,3957],{"q":3946,"a":3947},"Is Funding Pips a good prop firm?","Funding Pips received a 62/100 score in our review, making it an average-rated prop firm with both strengths and significant drawbacks. It offers multiple challenge types, scaling potential, and access to MT5, Match-Trader, and cTrader. However, inconsistent rule enforcement, payout clarity issues, and support concerns still affect overall trust.",{"q":3949,"a":3950},"Who is the owner of Funding Pips?","The owner of Funding Pips is Khaled Ayesh, based in Dubai. In 2024, the firm faced major disruptions after MetaQuotes cut services due to regulatory issues, and it also lost its partnership with BlackBull Markets.",{"q":3952,"a":3953},"How long does Funding Pips payout take to process?","Funding Pips processes most payouts within 1 to 3 business days, depending on your model and chosen withdrawal method. Instant payouts to Visa or Mastercard are now available and typically arrive within 30 minutes once approved.",{"q":3955,"a":3956},"How long has Funding Pips been around?","Funding Pips launched in 2020 but temporarily shut down in 2024 due to MetaQuotes-related issues. It later resumed operations with alternative platforms.",{"q":3958,"a":3959},"What is the 10 lot rule for Funding Pips?","The 10-lot rule previously limited traders to opening a total of 10 lots per day. However, this restriction no longer applies to new 1-Step accounts, as Funding Pips has officially removed the daily lot cap for those purchases.","src/content/reviews/rev-funding-pips.json","fa52c3043fc17fc2","rev-fxify",{"id":3962,"data":3964,"filePath":4008,"digest":4009},{"id":3962,"propFirmId":1602,"summary":3965,"pros":3966,"cons":3970,"bestFor":3974,"notIdealFor":3975,"overallScore":377,"categoryScores":3976,"categorySections":3977,"verdictBlocks":3985,"faq":3989,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"FXIFY scored 90/100 with flexible account options across MT4, MT5, and DXTrade. You can choose from instant funding, lightning challenge, or one, two, and three step evaluation processes, with raw spreads from 0 pips or commission-free trading. While the prop firm partners with forex broker FXPIG and offers great flexibility in its account options, the lack of transparency around actual trading costs and the minimal educational resources available might be off-putting to some.",[3967,3968,3969],"Multiple evaluation options","90% profit splits with add-on","Active community on Discord",[3971,3972,3973],"Users report slow payouts","Limited educational resources","Spread transparency could improve","Traders who want flexibility in evaluation types and the option to choose between raw spreads or commission-free trading","Traders who prioritise detailed cost information and comprehensive educational resources",{"challenges":377,"spreads":101,"markets":66,"payouts":377,"platforms":101,"trust":377},{"challenges":3978,"spreads":3979,"markets":3980,"platforms":3981,"payouts":3982,"support":3983,"trust":3984},"FXIFY offers five challenge types — **Instant Funding**, **Lightning**, **One Phase**, **Two Phase**, and **Three Phase** — with account sizes from $1K to $400K and fees starting at $39.\n\nInstant Funding provides immediate access with no evaluation, an 8% trailing drawdown, and up to 90% profit split. Lightning is a 7-day evaluation with a 5% profit target, 3% daily loss, and 4% trailing drawdown. One Phase requires 10% profit with 3% daily loss and 6% trailing drawdown. Two Phase targets 10% then 5% with 4% daily loss and 10% trailing drawdown. Three Phase requires 5% per phase with 5% daily loss and 10% static drawdown.\n\nOptional add-ons include higher profit split (+20% fee), bi-weekly payouts (+5%), performance protect (+15%), and increased leverage to 50:1 (+25%). The scaling plan allows 25% account growth every 3 months for a 10% return, with accounts scaling up to $4M. FXIFY scored 9/10 for challenges.","FXIFY offers two pricing models: **raw spreads from 0 pips** with a $6 round-turn commission per lot, or **commission-free all-inclusive** spreads. The raw spread model uses FXPIG's data feed for institutional-grade liquidity.\n\nDuring testing, spreads on popular pairs like EUR/USD started as low as 0 pips during London and New York sessions, though they tend to widen during off-hours. One drawback is that FXIFY doesn't publish average spread data, so traders should use demo accounts to assess pricing.\n\nNo swap-free accounts are currently available, though FXIFY has indicated this may be added in the future. FXIFY scored 8/10 for spreads.","FXIFY provides access to **101 instruments on MT5**, **71 on MT4**, and **62 on DXTrade** across forex, indices, commodities, stocks, and crypto.\n\nForex includes 42 major, minor, and exotic pairs. Indices cover 13 global markets including S&P 500, DAX, and ASX. Commodities include crude oil (WTI/Brent), gold, and silver. Stocks (30 instruments) are exclusive to MT5, featuring Apple, Amazon, and Tesla. Crypto (7 instruments) is available on MT4 and MT5 only.\n\nDefault leverage is **30:1** for forex and gold, **10:1** for indices, and **2:1** for stocks and crypto. An add-on increases forex/gold leverage to **50:1** for an additional 25% of the challenge fee. FXIFY scored 7/10 for markets.","FXIFY offers three platforms — **MT4**, **MT5**, and **DXTrade with TradingView integration**. Platform availability varies by challenge type: MT4 is available for One Phase, Two Phase, and Three Phase only. MT5 is available for all account types. DXTrade is available for all except Lightning.\n\nMT4 provides advanced charting, EA support, and one-click trading. MT5 adds more timeframes, Depth of Market, an economic calendar, and stock/crypto access. DXTrade with TradingView offers 100+ indicators, customizable layouts, and cloud-based access.\n\nEAs are supported on MT4 and MT5 only (not DXTrade or Lightning accounts). FXIFY scored 8/10 for platforms.","Profit splits start at **80%** and can be increased to **90%** with the profit split add-on. Challenge fees are **refunded with the first profitable payout**.\n\nThe first withdrawal is available **on demand** after the first profitable live trade (Instant Funding accounts after 14 days). Subsequent withdrawals are monthly by default, or bi-weekly with the add-on. Processing takes **24-48 hours** with no minimum withdrawal amount (except $50 for Instant Funding).\n\nWithdrawal methods include bank transfers, cryptocurrency, and Deel. Accounts enter read-only mode during withdrawal processing. FXIFY regularly shares verified payout proofs across Discord and social media. FXIFY scored 9/10 for payouts.","FXIFY offers **live chat** and **email support**, accessible 24/7 during weekdays. Response times and quality have received mixed reviews, with some users reporting delays when transitioning from automated chatbot to human support.\n\nEducational resources are limited compared to other prop firms. YouTube content is minimal and lacks comprehensive tutorials. The Support Hub and FAQ section cover common questions, but traders seeking in-depth educational materials may need to look elsewhere. FXIFY scored a combined rating reflecting accessible but basic support.","FXIFY holds a **4.4/5 Trustpilot rating** from over **4,900 reviews**, with positive feedback regarding fast payouts and user-friendly trading rules.\n\nThe prop firm maintains an active **Discord server** with verified trader channels, payout proof sharing, and community discussions. FXIFY is also active on Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter.\n\nFXIFY is backed by **FXPIG**, a broker licensed by the **Vanuatu Financial Services Commission (VFSC)** under License Number 014578. While Vanuatu regulation isn't as strict as ASIC or FCA, it provides more oversight than prop firms with no broker transparency. FXIFY scored 9/10 for trust.",[3986],{"heading":3987,"body":3988},"Final Verdict on FXIFY","FXIFY offers a range of evaluation options and customisable features, which can be appealing for traders who value flexibility. However, the added costs for upgrades, such as bi-weekly payouts and increased leverage, may not suit those looking for a more straightforward or affordable funding model.\n\nThe lack of transparency around spreads and available markets could be a drawback for traders who prioritise detailed cost information and market variety. While FXIFY has a solid community presence and offers scaling options, some users may find that the limited data on trading costs makes it harder to assess the true value of the proprietary trading firm.",[3990,3993,3996,3999,4002,4005],{"q":3991,"a":3992},"Where can I find the best FXIFY deals?","You can find the best FXIFY deals on BestPropFirms.com, where we offer exclusive promo codes like PROPFIRMS15 for 15% off all FXIFY challenges.",{"q":3994,"a":3995},"Does FXIFY have futures?","Yes, FXIFY has a separate futures prop trading firm, FXIFY Futures. This program offers funded futures accounts up to $150K, with a one-step evaluation, TradingView-based charts, and real-time CME data. Unlike FXIFY's CFD-focused challenges, FXIFY Futures is tailored for traders looking to trade futures with transparent pricing and no time limits.",{"q":3997,"a":3998},"Is FXIFY prop trading firm a scam?","FXIFY is not considered a scam; it is a registered prop trading firm that offers funded accounts and has numerous verified reviews on platforms like TrustPilot, where it holds a score of 4.4 out of 5. However, some users have reported delays in account activation and withdrawals, particularly on higher-tier accounts.",{"q":4000,"a":4001},"Is FXIFY safe?","FXIFY appears safe, providing standard security measures and a community-backed reputation. It has established a presence across social media and TrustPilot, with a majority of positive reviews, especially about their payout processes. FXIFY is backed by FXPIG, a broker licensed by the Vanuatu Financial Services Commission (VFSC).",{"q":4003,"a":4004},"Which broker does FXIFY use?","FXIFY operates through FXPIG, a broker known for supporting prop firms with competitive spreads and fast execution. FXPIG provides trading platforms like MT4, MT5, and DXTrade, giving FXIFY traders access to multiple trading environments.",{"q":4006,"a":4007},"What is the profit split on FXIFY?","FXIFY's profit split starts at 80%, allowing traders to keep the majority of their profits. This can be increased to 90% by purchasing a profit-split add-on during account setup. The profit split applies to all funded accounts after passing the evaluation phase.","src/content/reviews/rev-fxify.json","72b5675f62ef3aff","rev-goat-funded-futures",{"id":4010,"data":4012,"filePath":4056,"digest":4057},{"id":4010,"propFirmId":1685,"summary":4013,"pros":4014,"cons":4021,"bestFor":4028,"notIdealFor":4029,"overallScore":1404,"categoryScores":4030,"categorySections":4031,"verdictBlocks":4039,"faq":4043,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Goat Funded Futures scores 65/100 overall. You get 100% of the first $10K in profit, and can choose between subscription-based or one-time fee models. All plans include access to 55 futures markets and advanced platforms like NinjaTrader, Quantower, and Project X, with no added costs for data or software. The futures prop firm has clear payout rules and flexible account types, but weak customer support and high reset fees limit its appeal.",[4015,4016,4017,4018,4019,4020],"Keep 100% of first $10K in profit","Access to 55 CME futures instruments","Monthly subscription or one-time fee options","Full scaling after funding","No platform or data fees","Multiple advanced trading platforms",[4022,4023,4024,4025,4026,4027],"No resets for Instant Funding accounts","Profit consistency rules on all models","Limited educational materials","High reset fees ($349 for Static)","Weak customer support quality","Mixed community trust and transparency","Experienced futures traders who want flexible evaluation models, access to advanced platforms like NinjaTrader and Quantower, and the ability to keep 100% of their first $10K in profit","Beginners who need structured education, traders who rely on active support, or those who want reset options on Instant Funding accounts",{"challenges":66,"spreads":350,"markets":350,"payouts":66,"platforms":101,"trust":31},{"challenges":4032,"spreads":4033,"markets":4034,"platforms":4035,"payouts":4036,"support":4037,"trust":4038},"GFF offers three evaluation types: EOD, Static, and Instant Funding. EOD uses monthly subscription ($99–$249/mo) with trailing EOD drawdown and mid-phase scaling. Static uses monthly subscription ($199–$349/mo) with fixed drawdown and no daily loss limits. Instant is a one-time fee ($349–$699) with trailing real-time drawdown and 3% daily cap. Consistency rules apply across all models. No resets for Instant. Scored 7/10.","Raw spread access to CME-traded instruments with no data, platform, or exchange surcharges. Per-contract commissions are not publicly disclosed but typically range $1.50–$2.50 per round turn. No differentiation across asset classes. Transparent fee structure but lacks exact commission rate disclosure. Scored 6/10.","Access to 55 tradable instruments across CME Group markets including equity indices (ES, NQ, YM + micros), metals (GC, SI + micros), energy (CL, MCL, NG), currency futures (6E, 6B, 6J), and agricultural/soft commodities (ZC, ZS, KC). Both full-size and micro contracts supported. Variable margin aligned with CME practices. Scored 6/10.","Full suite of futures platforms with no extra fees: Project X (proprietary), NinjaTrader, Quantower, Volumetrica, Volsys, ATAS, TradingView, VolBook, and Tradovate. Real-time data included. Copy trading between own accounts allowed. Algorithmic trading support not confirmed. Scored 8/10.","100% of first $10K profit kept, then 90% split scaling to 92% and 95% at GOAT Trader level. EOD/Static pay every 14 days, Instant every 10 days. Min 6 trading days per cycle. Fixed payout windows (5th–8th and 20th–23rd). Min withdrawal $500 (EOD/Static), $250 (Instant). Processed via Riseworks in 2–3 business days. Scored 7/10.","24/7 support via email, live chat, and Discord. Response times are slow with vague answers reported. Many traders report delays and unhelpful responses on Trustpilot. Discord support staff not reliably active. No tutorials, webinars, or platform walkthroughs. Only basic FAQ available.","3.8/5 Trustpilot from 120+ reviews. Not broker-backed. ~30% negative reviews citing account credential delays, poor follow-up, and unresolved escalations. Discord moderation complaints. Limited payout transparency — verified success stories are rare. Scored 5/10.",[4040],{"heading":4041,"body":4042},"Final Verdict: 65/100","Goat Funded Futures scored 65/100 in our testing. The biggest advantage is the ability to keep 100% of your first $10K in profit, paired with access to raw spreads, advanced futures platforms, and Instant Funding for those who want to skip evaluations. You can choose between flexible subscription models or a one-time fee, and funded accounts benefit from a well-structured scaling plan. Payouts are fast, transparent, and handled via Riseworks.\n\nThat said, the firm still has key weaknesses. There's no reset option for Instant accounts, education is limited, and support responses are often slow or vague. GFF also lacks transparency on fees like commissions and leverage, which could make planning harder if you're not familiar with futures. If you already understand CME trading and want fast access to funding, GFF is worth a look. For beginners or traders who value active support, other options may offer a smoother experience.",[4044,4047,4050,4053],{"q":4045,"a":4046},"What is the profit split on Goat Funded Futures?","You keep 100% of your first $10,000 in profit. After that, the split starts at 90% and can increase to 92% and eventually 95% at the GOAT Trader level. This applies across all account types — EOD, Static, and Instant Funding.",{"q":4048,"a":4049},"Does Goat Funded Futures offer Instant Funding?","Yes. The Instant Funding model requires a one-time fee ($349–$699 depending on account size) and gives you immediate access to a funded account. You need to hit a 7% profit target and complete at least 6 trades over 10 days to qualify for your first payout. There's no reset option if you breach the rules.",{"q":4051,"a":4052},"What platforms does Goat Funded Futures support?","GFF supports a full suite of futures platforms including their proprietary Project X, NinjaTrader, Quantower, Volumetrica, Volsys, ATAS, TradingView, VolBook, and Tradovate. All platforms come with real-time data and no additional fees.",{"q":4054,"a":4055},"Can you reset an Instant Funding account at GFF?","No. The Instant Funding model does not allow resets. If you breach a rule, you'll need to purchase a new plan. EOD accounts can be reset for $99 and Static accounts for $349.","src/content/reviews/rev-goat-funded-futures.json","6ab0564b09273018","rev-fxify-futures",{"id":4058,"data":4060,"filePath":4101,"digest":4102},{"id":4058,"propFirmId":1553,"summary":4061,"pros":4062,"cons":4067,"bestFor":4071,"notIdealFor":4072,"overallScore":435,"categoryScores":4073,"categorySections":4074,"verdictBlocks":4082,"faq":4086,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"FXIFY Futures ranked 1st out of 12 futures prop firms we've tested firsthand, earning a score of 88/100. It offers a one-step evaluation, high profit splits, and no time limits. You can get funded up to $150K with no recurring fees.\n\nThe FFX Platform doesn't support third-party tools like NinjaTrader, but built-in TradingView charts and real-time CME data give you everything needed to trade futures efficiently.",[4063,1568,4064,4065,4066],"Profit splits to 100%","No time limits","TradingView-based platform","Real-time CME data",[4068,4069,3972,4070],"Payouts follow a tiered system","No NinjaTrader or Rithmic","Buffer zone requirement","Serious futures traders who want high profit splits, no time limits, and transparent pricing on CME markets","Traders who prefer third-party platforms like NinjaTrader or Rithmic, or need structured educational content",{"challenges":377,"spreads":377,"markets":203,"payouts":377,"platforms":66,"trust":377},{"challenges":4075,"spreads":4076,"markets":4077,"platforms":4078,"payouts":4079,"support":4080,"trust":4081},"FXIFY Futures offers two challenge types — **Starter Plan** and **Expert Plan** — across $50K, $100K, and $150K account sizes. Both are one-step evaluations with no time limits.\n\nThe Starter Plan has a minimum of 4 trading days, 80% profit split (upgradeable to 90%), and lower monthly fees from **$89**. The Expert Plan requires 3 trading days minimum, offers 90% profit split (upgradeable to 100%), no activation fee, and higher position limits up to 15 contracts.\n\nOptional add-ons include a 10% profit split increase and daily drawdown removal (Expert only). A consistency rule limits single-day profits to 30% (Starter) or 40% (Expert) of total profits. FXIFY Futures scored 9/10 for challenges.","FXIFY Futures uses round-turn pricing covering both opening and closing trades, including regulatory fees ($0.04 per trade) and exchange-specific costs. CME Equity Futures (ES, NQ) cost **$2.80** round-turn, Micro Equity Futures **$0.74**, CME FX Futures **$3.24**, and Micro FX **$0.52**.\n\nPricing is competitive with Topstep and other leading futures prop firms, with lower fees on index futures and cost-effective micro contract rates. FXIFY Futures scored 9/10 for spreads and pricing.","FXIFY Futures provides access to a wide range of CME futures markets including **equity futures** (ES, NQ), **micro equity** (MES, MNQ), **foreign exchange** (6E, 6B), **crude oil & energy** (CL, NG), **CBOT commodities** (ZC, ZW, ZS), **COMEX metals** (GC, SI, HG), **micro metals** (MGC, SIL), and **interest rate futures** (ZN, ZB).\n\nAll markets use real-time CME data feeds. FXIFY Futures scored a perfect 10/10 for markets.","FXIFY Futures operates exclusively on its proprietary **FFX Platform**, a web-based trading system. It does not support NinjaTrader, Rithmic, or Tradovate.\n\nThe FFX Platform includes TradingView-powered charting, real-time CME data feed, bracket orders with drag-and-drop controls, and automatic contract rollovers. Level 1 data is free; Level 2 data costs **$39/month**. EAs are not currently supported but may be added in the future. FXIFY Futures scored 7/10 for platforms.","Profit splits range from **80% to 100%** depending on plan and add-ons. Payouts are available every 14 days via bank transfer or crypto through **Riseworks**. A buffer zone must be maintained before withdrawals — $500–$1,500 (Starter) or $1,000–$2,000 (Expert) depending on account size.\n\nPayouts follow a tiered system: 60% on first withdrawal, scaling to 100% from the fifth withdrawal onwards. No recurring fees after funding. KYC verification required. FXIFY Futures scored 9/10 for payouts.","FXIFY Futures provides support through **live chat** and **email**. The Discord community offers trading discussions and payout proof channels. However, formal educational resources such as webinars or courses are not available — guidance is limited to platform guides, Help Center content, and community discussions.","FXIFY Futures is linked to **FXIFY** (CFD prop firm) and **FXPIG** (regulated forex broker), which adds credibility. Trustpilot score is **3.9/5** but based on only 4 reviews, making it too early to gauge a strong reputation.\n\nThe firm maintains an active Discord server with weekly payout updates and payout proof channels. Social media presence is still developing. FXIFY Futures scored 9/10 for trust based on its backing by established firms.",[4083],{"heading":4084,"body":4085},"Final Verdict on FXIFY Futures","FXIFY Futures provides a clear path to funded futures trading with no time limits, high profit splits, and structured risk management. The FFX Platform is proprietary, which may not suit traders who prefer NinjaTrader or Rithmic, but it offers TradingView charts and real-time CME data.\n\nThe payout system is structured, with tiered withdrawals and a buffer zone, meaning traders must manage expectations when it comes to early withdrawals. However, with no recurring fees after funding, a scalable profit split, and transparent pricing, it remains a strong choice for serious futures traders.",[4087,4090,4092,4095,4098],{"q":4088,"a":4089},"What is the best brokerage to trade futures?","FXIFY Futures is the best brokerage alternative for prop traders, scoring 88/100 in our analysis for its one-step evaluation and no time limits. In comparison, Topstep, another one of the top futures prop firms, scored 83/100, making FXIFY Futures a stronger choice for traders looking for scalable payouts and transparent funding rules.",{"q":3994,"a":4091},"Yes, FXIFY offers a dedicated futures prop trading firm through FXIFY Futures, which provides funded accounts up to $150K with a one-step evaluation and no time limits. Unlike FXIFY's CFD-focused prop firm, FXIFY Futures is specifically designed for traders looking to access equity, forex, commodity, and bond futures with real-time CME data.",{"q":4093,"a":4094},"Does FXIFY pay?","Yes, FXIFY Futures processes bi-weekly withdrawals through Riseworks, provided traders meet the buffer zone requirements. The payout structure is tiered, meaning the percentage of profits available for withdrawal increases over time. Traders must pass KYC verification before receiving payouts, which can be withdrawn via bank transfer or cryptocurrency.",{"q":4096,"a":4097},"How does FXIFY payout?","FXIFY Futures pays traders through Riseworks, with bi-weekly withdrawals available 14 days after the first trade on a funded account. Payouts increase over time based on a tiered withdrawal model, starting at 60% of profits above the buffer zone and scaling up to 100% after the fifth withdrawal. Payments can be processed via bank transfer or crypto.",{"q":4099,"a":4100},"Who is the founder of FXIFY?","FXIFY was founded by a team of prop trading and brokerage professionals, though specific names have not been publicly disclosed. The firm is linked to FXPIG, a regulated forex broker, and has expanded to offer both CFD and futures trading through FXIFY Futures and FXIFY for CFD prop trading.","src/content/reviews/rev-fxify-futures.json","cded2fc4fc3de796","rev-hantec-trader",{"id":4103,"data":4105,"filePath":4148,"digest":4149},{"id":4103,"propFirmId":1846,"summary":4106,"pros":4107,"cons":4114,"bestFor":4120,"notIdealFor":4121,"overallScore":363,"categoryScores":4122,"categorySections":4123,"verdictBlocks":4131,"faq":4135,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Hantec Trader scores 75/100, making it a solid mid-tier option for traders who value clean rules, reliable payouts, and broker-backed credibility via Hantec Markets. While market depth and education are limited, and Instant Funding has tighter restrictions, the firm's clear structure and flexible challenges will suit experienced traders looking for efficient, no-nonsense funding.",[4108,4109,4110,4111,4112,4113],"Fast, flexible payouts (7, 14, or 30 days)","Backed by FCA-regulated broker (Hantec Markets)","MT4 and MT5 supported with no platform fees","Three challenge types including Instant Funding","Scaling plan up to $200K","No minimum trading days or consistency rules",[4115,4116,4117,4118,4119],"Crypto leverage fixed at 1:1","Instant Funding has stricter rules (no EAs, no weekend holds, no news)","Limited commodity coverage (only 2 instruments)","No stocks or futures available","Minimal educational content","Experienced traders who want a broker-backed prop firm with clean rules, flexible payouts, and multiple funding paths — especially those comfortable with MT4/MT5","Beginners who need structured education, US-based traders (not eligible), or those relying heavily on crypto leverage or automated strategies on Instant accounts",{"challenges":101,"spreads":350,"markets":350,"payouts":101,"platforms":101,"trust":377},{"challenges":4124,"spreads":4125,"markets":4126,"platforms":4127,"payouts":4128,"support":4129,"trust":4130},"Hantec Trader offers three program types: Express (1-step), Enhanced (2-step), and Instant Funding. Account sizes range from $5K to $200K with fees from $49 to $1,999. All three have no time limits or minimum trading days. Express uses trailing-to-static drawdown (5% daily, 6% max), Enhanced uses static drawdown (5% daily, 10% max), and Instant uses trailing-to-static (6% daily, 6% max). Scaling available up to $200K on evaluation accounts. Scored 8/10.","Raw spreads with flat commission per lot. Forex and metals at $5/lot, commodities at $1/lot, indices and crypto at $0. No platform or data feed fees. However, no average spread data is published and liquidity providers are undisclosed, limiting transparency. Scored 6/10.","Access to 5 asset classes: 40 forex pairs, 8 metals, 11 indices, 2 commodities, and 14 crypto pairs. Forex leverage at 50:1, metals 20:1, indices 15:1, commodities 15:1, crypto 1:1. No stocks or futures available. Scored 6/10.","MetaTrader 4 and MetaTrader 5 supported with no platform or data fees. Real-time pricing. EAs and copy trading allowed on Express and Enhanced only. No platform switching once challenge starts. Instant accounts cannot use EAs or copy trading. Scored 8/10.","75-90% profit split. One-time fees with no recurring costs. Payouts via bank transfer, PayPal, or crypto. Processing in 1-2 business days. Express and Enhanced: 30-day default, 14-day with add-on. Instant: 14-day default, 7-day with add-on. No minimum withdrawal amount. Buffer rule applies post-withdrawal. Scored 8/10.","24/5 support via email, live chat, and Discord. Response quality is clear and helpful with no known delays. No weekend support. Educational content limited to FAQ section only — no tutorials, webinars, or strategy guides.","Broker-backed by FCA-regulated Hantec Markets. 4.5/5 Trustpilot rating from 313+ verified reviews. No reports of payout issues or price manipulation. Active Discord community with 3,500+ members and 14,400+ Twitter followers. Community payout proof shared via Discord and social platforms. Scored 9/10.",[4132],{"heading":4133,"body":4134},"Final Verdict: 75/100","Hantec Trader is a solid prop firm if you want a rule-transparent, broker-backed firm with flexible funding options. The One Step and Two Step challenges offer scalable funding up to $200K, with no time limits or consistency requirements, ideal for traders who value control. Instant Funding is more limited, but still attractive for those who want to bypass evaluations entirely.\n\nThe prop firm delivers on payouts, platform reliability, and community engagement, backed by FCA-regulated Hantec Markets. While the lack of average spread data, limited education, and 1:1 crypto leverage hold it back slightly, the clean fee structure, responsive support, and public payout record make it one of the more trustworthy options in today's prop trading market.",[4136,4139,4142,4145],{"q":4137,"a":4138},"What is the profit split on Hantec?","Hantec Trader offers a profit split starting at 75%, which can increase to 90% based on account type and trader performance. Both the One Step and Two Step evaluations begin at 75%, with potential upgrades. Instant Funding accounts also start at 75%, and traders can unlock a 90% split with the Weekly Payout add-on. There are no profit withdrawal limits, but a buffer rule applies after each payout.",{"q":4140,"a":4141},"What is the maximum allocation for Hantec Trader?","The maximum account allocation at Hantec Trader is $200,000. You can start with any account size and scale up through the One Step or Two Step challenges. But it's important to note there is no scaling available for Instant Funding accounts. Scaling is performance-based and allows you to move to the next tier for free after meeting the required profit targets.",{"q":4143,"a":4144},"Is Hantec a good broker?","Yes, Hantec is considered a good broker. Hantec Trader is backed by Hantec Markets, an FCA-regulated forex broker. This connection adds trust and oversight to the prop firm, which is rare in the space. While Hantec Trader operates independently for funding challenges, the broker backing ensures price feeds are stable and payouts are credible.",{"q":4146,"a":4147},"Is Hantec Trader available in the US?","No, Hantec Trader is not available to US residents. This is due to regulatory and compliance restrictions related to the FCA-regulated broker backing. Traders from most other regions can sign up and participate in all three challenge types.","src/content/reviews/rev-hantec-trader.json","8c9620942474398d","rev-goat-funded-trader",{"id":4150,"data":4152,"filePath":4193,"digest":4194},{"id":4150,"propFirmId":1756,"summary":4153,"pros":4154,"cons":4160,"bestFor":4167,"notIdealFor":4168,"overallScore":197,"categoryScores":4169,"categorySections":4170,"verdictBlocks":4178,"faq":4182,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":4192,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Goat Funded Trader finished testing with a low score of 42/100, mainly due to a lack of transparency. While it offers flexible challenge types, bi-weekly payouts, and scaling opportunities, unclear funded account conditions, hidden rules, and payout complaints make it a risky choice.\n\nMany traders have reported slow execution, unexpected account breaches, and difficulty withdrawing profits. The lack of clear details on spreads, liquidity, and leverage adds to the uncertainty. If you're thinking about signing up, be ready for some headaches along the way.",[4155,4156,4157,3222,4158,4159],"Profit splits up to 100%","Multiple challenge types (1-step, 2-step, 3-step, instant)","Instant funding available","Low entry fees from $22","Scaling plan available",[4161,4162,4163,4164,4165,4166],"Multiple payout issues reported","Vague and unclear trading rules","No stock trading available","Hidden spread and leverage data","Payout delays and denied withdrawals","23% one-star TrustPilot reviews","Traders comfortable with risk who want low entry fees, multiple challenge types, and no time limits on evaluations","Traders who value transparency, reliable payouts, clear trading conditions, or need structured education and mentorship",{"challenges":350,"spreads":613,"markets":31,"payouts":613,"platforms":350,"trust":405},{"challenges":4171,"spreads":4172,"markets":4173,"platforms":4174,"payouts":4175,"support":4176,"trust":4177},"Goat Funded Trader offers One-Step, Two-Step (Goat & Standard), Three-Step, and Instant Funding accounts. Flexible with no time limits. Profit targets range from 5%–10% depending on model. Daily drawdown 3%–5%, max drawdown 6%–10%. Low entry fees starting from $22. However, strict drawdown limits and consistency rules make passing difficult. Scored 6/10.","Goat Funded Trader claims spreads as low as 0 pips but does not publish average spread data. No liquidity providers disclosed. Commission is $2.50 per lot round-turn on forex — one of the lowest in the industry. Other asset classes have no commissions but undisclosed spreads. Lack of transparency on actual trading costs is a major concern. Scored 3/10.","Access to Forex, Indices, Commodities, and Cryptocurrencies. Forex leverage up to 1:100 for Two-Step/Three-Step evaluations, 1:30 for One-Step, 1:50 for funded accounts. Crypto leverage 1:2. GFT does not confirm One-Step funded leverage and promotes scaling leverage without clear requirements. Scored 5/10.","Three platforms available: MT5 (best automation support), TradeLocker (TradingView integration), and MatchTrader (built-in analytics). No MT4 available. Strict rules on EAs — must prove ownership with source code. No hedging, no trade copying, no HFT. News trading profits capped at 1% within 2 minutes of high-impact events. Scored 6/10.","First payout after 30 days (bi-weekly available as paid add-on). Profit split starts at 80% with 100% add-on option. First two withdrawals capped at 6% of account balance. Daily withdrawal cap of $3,000. Min withdrawal $100. Processing in 2–3 business days. Payment via credit card, crypto, and bank transfer. No PayPal. Scored 3/10.","Live chat and email support available. Response times inconsistent — basic questions answered quickly but detailed account issues take longer. Support often gives unclear answers about spreads and leverage. No structured education, mentorship, or training programs. YouTube channel has interviews and basic tutorials but no in-depth strategy content. Scored 4/10.","3.4/5 TrustPilot from 3,000+ reviews. 62% five-star but 23% one-star. Major complaints include delayed/denied payouts, unexplained account breaches, execution issues, spread manipulation accusations, and unhelpful support. Discord community of 59,700+ members. While some traders report positive experiences, the volume of complaints about denied withdrawals and hidden rules raises serious concerns. Scored 2/10.",[4179],{"heading":4180,"body":4181},"Final Verdict: 42/100","Goat Funded Trader offers flexible challenge options with no time limits, low entry fees, and high potential profit splits. The Two-Step Challenge is likely the best option for most traders, as it offers a balance between achievable profit targets and reasonable drawdown limits. The Instant Funding accounts may appeal to those who want to skip the evaluation process, but they come with stricter risk rules and higher upfront costs.\n\nHowever, transparency issues are a major concern. The firm does not disclose minimum spreads, funded account leverage for One-Step traders, or clear payout processing policies. Many traders have reported payout delays, platform malfunctions, and unexpected account breaches, raising red flags about reliability.\n\nIf you value low-cost challenges, high leverage during evaluations, and bi-weekly payouts, GFT might be worth considering — but only if you are comfortable with the risks. The lack of clear trading conditions, payout restrictions, and mixed trader feedback make this a high-risk prop firm, best suited for those who are willing to accept uncertainty in exchange for potentially high rewards.",[4183,4186,4189],{"q":4184,"a":4185},"Is Goat Funded Trader legit or a scam?","Goat Funded Trader is a real prop firm, but transparency issues and payout complaints raise concerns. While some traders report smooth withdrawals, others have faced delayed or denied payouts, unexpected account breaches, and unclear trading conditions. The firm does not disclose spread data or liquidity providers, making it difficult to verify trading costs.",{"q":4187,"a":4188},"What broker does Goat Funded Trader use?","Goat Funded Trader does not use a traditional forex broker and instead operates on a simulated trading environment. This means your trades are not executed in real financial markets, but within a risk management system controlled by the firm. Unlike broker-backed prop firms, GFT does not disclose its liquidity providers or minimum spreads.",{"q":4190,"a":4191},"Does Goat Funded Trader allow expert advisors or copy trading?","You can use an EA, but must prove you own the code if requested. The firm prohibits third-party or commercially available EAs designed to pass challenges. Copy trading is completely banned — you cannot mirror trades between accounts. Violating these rules can lead to account termination and forfeited payouts.","We do not recommend Goat Funded Trader due to payout delays, unclear trading conditions, and reports of unexpected account breaches. The firm lacks transparency on spreads, liquidity providers, and funded account leverage, making it difficult to assess long-term profitability.\n\nOur testing scored Goat Funded Trader **42/100**, and we only recommend firms scoring 50/100+. For a more reliable experience with better trust and clearer policies, consider broker-backed prop firms like [DNA Funded](/reviews/dna-funded) or [Blueberry Funded](/reviews/blueberry-funded).","src/content/reviews/rev-goat-funded-trader.json","5d7dafdf82c13374","rev-ic-funded",{"id":4195,"data":4197,"filePath":4235,"digest":4236},{"id":4195,"propFirmId":1920,"summary":4198,"pros":4199,"cons":4203,"bestFor":4207,"notIdealFor":4208,"overallScore":752,"categoryScores":4209,"categorySections":4210,"verdictBlocks":4218,"faq":4222,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"IC Funded scored 79/100 during testing, placing it among the top-rated prop firms. You can choose between a one or two step challenge, but both come with profit splits starting at 75% and increasing to 80% after one month of trading (and after the first payout is processed).\n\nYou'll trade with IC Markets' pricing, including spreads from 0 pips, and use platforms like MT4, MT5, or cTrader. While scaling is capped at $500K and copy and weekend trading aren't allowed, the low costs, strong trading conditions, and structured challenges make it a solid choice.",[4200,4201,4202],"Fees from $29.75","Backed by IC Markets","MT4, MT5, and cTrader",[4204,4205,4206],"Profit split 75% - 80%","Limited scaling to 500K","No crypto trading","Traders who prioritise low trading costs, tight spreads, and broker-backed execution from IC Markets","Traders who need high profit splits, crypto trading, or scaling beyond $500K",{"challenges":101,"spreads":203,"markets":377,"payouts":377,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":4211,"spreads":4212,"markets":4213,"platforms":4214,"payouts":4215,"support":4216,"trust":4217},"IC Funded offers both **one step** and **two step** challenges. The one step has a single 10% profit target with 6% max drawdown, while the two step splits across 10% and 5% targets with a more generous 10% max drawdown.\n\nAccount sizes range from **$5,000 to $500,000** with fees starting at just **$29.75**. Both models require a minimum of 5 trading days with no maximum time limit. Profit splits start at **75%** and increase to **80%** after the first month.\n\nScaling is performance-based up to $500K total allocation. IC Funded scored 8/10 for challenges thanks to clear structure, competitive pricing, and flexibility across both options.","IC Funded provides forex spreads the same as those offered by **IC Markets' Global Raw Account**. Minimum spreads on popular forex pairs like EUR/USD are as low as **0 pips**, with an average of **0.02 pips**.\n\nCommission is a flat **$3.50 per lot** per round turn for forex, commodities, and indices. IC Funded scored 10/10 for spreads — the combination of ultra-low spreads, transparent commissions, and competitive fees makes it one of the most competitively priced prop firms.","IC Funded offers **96 trading instruments** across commodity, equity index, and forex markets. Forex pairs and Gold have up to **50:1 leverage**, indices and other commodities up to **10:1**, and equities up to **5:1**.\n\nCrypto and share trading are not available through IC Funded, though IC Markets does offer these. IC Funded scored 9/10 for markets — broad access to core instruments with consistent leverage across challenge types.","IC Funded supports **MT4**, **MT5**, and **cTrader** — three of the most popular platforms for prop trading. MT4 is strong for EA and indicator-focused traders, MT5 adds advanced order types and economic calendar, and cTrader offers Level II market depth and advanced charting.\n\nAll platforms support automated trading through Expert Advisors, though copy trading is prohibited. IC Funded scored 9/10 for platforms.","Profit splits start at **75%** and increase to **80%** after the first month of funded trading. The default payout schedule is monthly, with bi-weekly and on-demand options available (on-demand from 14 days after first trade).\n\nWithdrawals are processed via bank wire, Skrill, or crypto. Minimum net profit is **$20** for bank wire and **$150** for crypto payouts. The challenge fee is refunded with the first profit withdrawal after 30 days of trading. IC Funded scored 9/10 for payouts.","IC Funded provides **24/7 customer support** through AI-assisted live chat, with email support for more complex matters. No direct contact number is available.\n\nEducational resources include curated videos on market trends and trading strategies accessible through the client dashboard, covering platform navigation, market analysis, and broader financial topics.","IC Funded is closely connected to **IC Markets**, a well-established broker regulated by **ASIC** in Australia and **CySEC** in Europe. While IC Funded itself is not a regulated broker, the IC Markets connection provides a solid trust foundation.\n\nTrustPilot score is **2.7/5** with mixed reviews — many lower ratings come from users still in evaluation or waiting on first payouts rather than funded traders. IC Funded uses its own dedicated chat community instead of Discord, managed directly by the team. Social media presence is relatively small compared to competitors.",[4219],{"heading":4220,"body":4221},"Final Verdict on IC Funded","IC Funded is a well-priced and accessible prop firm, offering both one step and two step evaluations with fees starting from $29.75 and account sizes up to $500,000. You get access to IC Markets' tight spreads, reliable execution, and a solid platform lineup including MT4, MT5, and cTrader, along with a profit split that increases from 75% to 80% after one month of funded trading and the first payout.\n\nThe challenge structure is clear and consistent, with realistic profit targets and no maximum time limits, making it a good fit if you prefer a straightforward evaluation without unnecessary complexity. That said, scaling is capped at $500K and there's no access to crypto or share trading, which may be limiting if broader market access or higher scaling is a priority.\n\nOverall, IC Funded is a strong option if you want low trading costs, proven liquidity, and a simple path to funded trading. If higher scaling limits or a wider range of markets matter more to you, other prop firms may be a better fit.",[4223,4226,4229,4232],{"q":4224,"a":4225},"What is the evaluation process for IC Funded?","IC Funded lets you choose between a one step or two step prop challenge. The one step challenge has a single 10% profit target with 6% max drawdown, while the two step includes two phases with 10% and 5% targets and 10% max drawdown. Both require a minimum of 5 trading days with no maximum time limit. Once you meet the profit targets and follow the rules, you qualify for a funded account with profit share.",{"q":4227,"a":4228},"What is the profit split structure at IC Funded?","The profit split starts at 75% in favour of the trader and increases to 80% after the first month of trading on a funded account and after the first payout is processed.",{"q":4230,"a":4231},"What platforms are available with IC Funded?","IC Funded supports MetaTrader 4 (MT4), MetaTrader 5 (MT5), and cTrader. Each platform provides strong trading tools and features, and trading rules allow for Expert Advisors and automated trading. Copy trading is not permitted.",{"q":4233,"a":4234},"Is proprietary trading good for beginners?","Proprietary trading can be challenging for beginners due to the high-risk environment and stringent profit targets, and is generally recommended for experienced traders. However, it offers access to capital and potential profit splits without risking personal funds. Beginners should have a solid understanding of risk management, trading strategies, and market analysis before considering proprietary trading.","src/content/reviews/rev-ic-funded.json","ca176338f7efd115","rev-instant-funding",{"id":4237,"data":4239,"filePath":4276,"digest":4277},{"id":4237,"propFirmId":1978,"summary":4240,"pros":4241,"cons":4248,"bestFor":4253,"notIdealFor":4254,"overallScore":4255,"categoryScores":4256,"categorySections":4257,"verdictBlocks":4258,"faq":4262,"verified":26,"flagged":26,"flaggedWarning":4275,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 58/100, Instant Funding is an independent prop trading firm focused on instant funding accounts with no evaluation. While it offers seven account types, flexible scaling up to $1,280,000, and support for MT5, cTrader, and Match-Trader, significant concerns around pricing transparency, removed TrustPilot reviews due to guideline breaches, and trader complaints about payout disputes and rule enforcement lower its overall standing.\n\nHowever, there are positives. Platforms scored well at 8/10 with three solid options, and payouts earned 8/10 thanks to on-demand and short-cycle withdrawal options. Markets and leverage also scored 7/10, with broad CFD coverage and up to 1:100 leverage on forex pairs.",[4242,4243,4244,4245,4246,4247],"Multiple instant funding account options with no evaluation","No time limits on most challenge accounts","Up to 90-95% profit split depending on account type","Scaling up to $1,280,000 across all models","Three platform choices: MT5, cTrader, Match-Trader","Customizable add-ons for rules and profit splits",[4249,2059,4250,4251,2082,4252],"High-frequency trading strictly prohibited","Limited transparency on liquidity and spreads","Complex rules that differ across account types","Reports of denied payouts and account terminations","Traders who want instant access to funded accounts without evaluation, with multiple account types and customizable add-ons for trading flexibility","Traders looking for transparent pricing and spreads, high-frequency trading, or firms with strong trust and payout reliability track records",58,{"challenges":350,"spreads":613,"markets":66,"payouts":101,"platforms":101,"trust":613},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4259],{"heading":4260,"body":4261},"Our Final Verdict On Instant Funding","Instant Funding scored 58/100 based on a mixed performance across challenges, pricing transparency, platforms, markets, payouts, and trust. The score reflects a firm that offers flexible instant funding models and solid platform access, but loses significant points due to transparency gaps and rule enforcement concerns.\n\nOn the positive side, Instant Funding earned stronger marks for Platforms (8/10) and Payouts (8/10) thanks to support for MT5, cTrader, and Match-Trader, along with a range of on-demand and short-cycle withdrawal options. Markets and Leverage (7/10) also scored well, with broad CFD coverage and up to 1:100 leverage on forex pairs.\n\nHowever, the overall score is pulled down by Spreads and Fees (3/10) and Trust and Transparency (3/10). The firm does not publicly disclose live spread data, execution sources, liquidity providers, or whether pricing is broker-backed or fully simulated. In addition, the removal of TrustPilot reviews following guideline breaches and ongoing trader complaints about payout disputes and rule enforcement significantly impacted the trust score.\n\nChallenges (6/10) sit in the middle. Fees are competitive and the range of instant and evaluation-based models is broad, but strict consistency rules, add-on-dependent flexibility, and complex conditions reduce clarity for traders. Overall, Instant Funding operates within clearly written rules, but the lack of third-party verification and pricing transparency ultimately cap its score at the lower end of our rankings.",[4263,4266,4269,4272],{"q":4264,"a":4265},"Does Instant Funding payout?","Yes, Instant Funding does process payouts, but this is also one of the reasons the prop firm review score was lower overall. While payouts are advertised as being processed within 48 business hours via RISE or USDC crypto, a noticeable number of traders report delayed withdrawals, rejected payout requests, or account terminations tied to rule interpretation. These complaints, combined with removed TrustPilot reviews and limited public payout verification, raise concerns around consistency rather than the payout system itself.",{"q":4267,"a":4268},"How does Instant Funding work?","Instant Funding works by giving you access to simulated trading capital after paying a one-time fee, either through instant funding accounts with no evaluation or through one step and two step challenges. You trade under predefined risk rules, profit targets, and consistency limits, and if you meet the conditions, you become eligible for payouts based on the funded account's payout schedule. Profits are split between you and the firm, while breaches of drawdown or trading rules can result in account closure.",{"q":4270,"a":4271},"What is the best instant funding prop firm?","Our shortlist of the best instant funding prop firms currently ranks Blueberry Funded as the strongest option for traders who want a no-evaluation account with clearer pricing and simpler rules. FXIFY follows closely, offering a wider range of instant funding models and platforms. Both firms are backed by regulated CFD brokers, which adds an extra layer of pricing and execution transparency.",{"q":4273,"a":4274},"Is Instant Funding available for US traders?","Yes, Instant Funding is available to traders in the United States, but platform access is limited. Traders based in the US can trade through cTrader or Match-Trader, while MT5 is not supported in this region. These platforms still provide core charting, order management, and limited automation features under Instant Funding's rules. US traders can request a platform switch during a challenge for a one-time $20 fee, and standard KYC verification is required before withdrawals.","Instant Funding's TrustPilot reviews were removed due to a breach of guidelines related to potential fake reviews. Multiple traders have reported denied payouts and disputed account terminations.","src/content/reviews/rev-instant-funding.json","8bdd9d5a81df749c","rev-lark-funding",{"id":4278,"data":4280,"filePath":4317,"digest":4318},{"id":4278,"propFirmId":2103,"summary":4281,"pros":4282,"cons":4289,"bestFor":4295,"notIdealFor":4296,"overallScore":4297,"categoryScores":4298,"categorySections":4299,"verdictBlocks":4300,"faq":4304,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"Lark Funding scored 52/100 overall. It's a Canada-based prop firm offering four distinct funding models — Instant Funding, One Step, Two Step, and Three Step challenges — with account sizes from $5,000 to $200,000. While the variety of challenge options and instant funding availability are appealing, higher fees, the restrictive payout lock rule, and limited customer support hold it back.\n\nThe firm accepts EAs and news trading, but prohibits martingale, grid trading, and HFT strategies. All trading takes place in a simulated environment. For traders prioritising transparency, lower fees, and stronger support, there are better options available — but Lark Funding may suit experienced traders who are confident in their strategies and risk management.",[4283,4284,4285,4286,4287,4288],"Instant funding accounts with no evaluation required","No time limits on completing evaluations","Four distinct challenge types to match different styles","EAs and news trading allowed","Stock CFDs available (~141 options)","Leverage upgrades available at checkout",[4290,4291,4292,4293,4294,3972],"No scaling plan available","Payout lock rule reduces drawdown buffer after withdrawals","$40 flat withdrawal processing fee","No live chat or 24/7 customer support","Higher challenge fees than some competitors","Experienced traders who want flexible evaluation choices including instant funding, stock trading access, and are comfortable managing the payout lock drawdown rule","Beginners needing guidance, traders seeking low fees and transparent pricing, or those who want a scaling plan and live customer support",52,{"challenges":350,"spreads":360,"markets":350,"payouts":350,"platforms":31,"support":347,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4301],{"heading":4302,"body":4303},"Our Final Verdict On Lark Funding","Lark Funding provides a variety of challenges and a functional trading community, but its policies and lack of transparency may not suit all traders. The payout lock rule and unclear pricing structure make it harder to plan for long-term growth, while limited customer support and the absence of educational resources leave gaps for those who need guidance.\n\nFor traders prioritising transparency, lower fees, and broker-backed reliability, firms like DNA Funded and IC Funded may be better options. These firms often offer more competitive pricing, clearer trading conditions, and stronger support systems, making them a better choice for both new and experienced traders.",[4305,4308,4311,4314],{"q":4306,"a":4307},"Where is Lark Funding based?","Lark Funding is based in Canada and offers funded trading accounts through evaluation challenges. While it provides global access to various markets like forex and crypto, its higher fees and restrictive policies compared to more competitive options may be a consideration for traders.",{"q":4309,"a":4310},"Who owns Lark Funding?","Lark Funding is led by CEO Matt L and operates as a Canada-based proprietary trading firm. The exact ownership structure is not publicly disclosed. Unlike broker-backed prop firms, Lark Funding operates independently without direct ties to a brokerage, which may impact its trading conditions and transparency.",{"q":4312,"a":4313},"Does Lark Funding allow copy trading?","Lark Funding allows copy trading only between funded accounts, not during evaluation. You can copy trades across multiple funded accounts once you pass the evaluation process. Copying trades between evaluation accounts is strictly prohibited, and each evaluation must be passed individually.",{"q":4315,"a":4316},"How long does Lark Funding take to withdraw?","Lark Funding typically processes withdrawal requests within 1-3 business days via Wise or Riseworks. Payout frequency depends on the challenge type — biweekly for some accounts and monthly for others. Instant funding accounts allow on-demand payouts. All withdrawals are subject to a $100 minimum, a $40 processing fee, and the drawdown lock rule.","src/content/reviews/rev-lark-funding.json","3367ed94458c0f0d","rev-maven-trading",{"id":4319,"data":4321,"filePath":4364,"digest":4365},{"id":4319,"propFirmId":2177,"summary":4322,"pros":4323,"cons":4330,"bestFor":4337,"notIdealFor":4338,"overallScore":3747,"categoryScores":4339,"categorySections":4340,"verdictBlocks":4341,"faq":4345,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 62/100, Maven Trading scored moderately because of wider spreads and poor transparency around pricing. Although the prop firm offers multiple challenges with low fees and instant funding accounts, Maven Trading has restrictive payouts and unhelpful customer support.\n\nWhile the range of five challenge types allows for flexibility compared to other firms, significantly wider forex spreads and limited transparency may make it less ideal for active and high-frequency traders.",[4324,4325,4326,4327,4328,4329],"Fees from just $13","Five challenge types including Instant Funding and Mini","Forex, ETFs, crypto, commodities, and indices","Match-Trader, cTrader, and MT5 platforms","No minimum trading days on any challenge","Scaling plan up to $1,000,000",[4331,4332,4333,4334,4335,4336],"Significantly wide forex spreads","Limited transparency around pricing and liquidity providers","Restrictive payout policies with $10,000 cap per two cycles","Unhelpful customer support — live chat only","Minimal educational resources","No phone or email support available","Budget-conscious traders looking for diverse challenge types with low entry fees, flexible account options, and no minimum trading days","Scalpers, high-frequency traders, or those requiring tight spreads, transparent pricing, and hands-on customer support",{"challenges":66,"spreads":405,"markets":66,"payouts":350,"platforms":66,"trust":360},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4342],{"heading":4343,"body":4344},"Final Verdict on Maven Trading","Maven Trading's score of 62/100 is similar to prop firms like E8 Markets and Funded Elite. While Maven offers low-cost entry fees and flexibility between five types of evaluation challenges, the wider forex spreads and lack of transparency around pricing make it a costly choice if you're a daily or active trader.\n\nCustomer support is minimal, with only basic live chat assistance and no direct contact methods, which doesn't make it a favourable firm if you're a beginner trader in need of all the help you can get. The platform's restricted payout policies, like the $10,000 cap per cycle, can further limit potential earnings. Educational resources are also lacking, offering only a basic FAQ and blog with little to support skill development.\n\nWhile Maven has an active community and high TrustPilot rating, the lack of transparency around key elements like spreads, liquidity providers, and payment fees raises concerns for those looking for an open and fully supportive trading environment.",[4346,4349,4352,4355,4358,4361],{"q":4347,"a":4348},"Is Maven Trading a good firm?","Maven Trading is a good prop trading platform with cheap challenge fees, but it scores lower than most prop trading competitors due to high forex spreads and a lack of transparency around liquidity and spreads. While the firm offers multiple evaluation options with low fees, the restrictive payout policies and unhelpful customer support team lowers its value as a prop trading company. If you're an average prop trader who wants to test out your prop trading risk management strategies, Maven Trading is a good firm for you.",{"q":4350,"a":4351},"Is Maven Trading legit?","Yes, Maven Trading is a legitimate proprietary trading firm that has been in business since 2022 with headquarters in Vancouver, Canada. The firm is known for offering fast payouts and access to trading platforms like MT5 and cTrader. However, there have also been reports of traders complaining that Maven has a tendency to change and revert trading rules out of the blue which doesn't help Maven's reputation to stand out as a legitimate prop firm.",{"q":4353,"a":4354},"What are the best prop trading firms?","The best prop trading firms for 2026 are DNA Funded and Funded Next. DNA Funded tops the list with low challenge fees, an 80% profit split, and a solid range of markets. Funded Next is a great choice for forex trading because it has flexible evaluations, 95% profit split, and clear trading rules.",{"q":4356,"a":4357},"How does Maven Trading evaluate traders?","Maven Trading's evaluation process offers multiple trading challenges: the One-Step, Two-Step, and Three-Step challenges, as well as the Mini and the Instant Funding method. The One-Step requires you to meet an 8% profit target with a 5% trailing drawdown, while the Two-Step has a static drawdown of 8% and requires you to hit 8% in phase one and 5% in phase two. The Three-Step lets you complete three phases with a 3% profit target for each phase and a 2% daily drawdown with no time frame which makes it a good choice for beginners.",{"q":4359,"a":4360},"What are the cons of Maven Trading?","The biggest disadvantages of Maven Trading are its significantly wide forex spreads which can severely increase your trading costs. While it offers low challenge fees, the firm isn't transparent around pricing and payout structures, and the customer support is not up to standards. These factors make Maven Trading a bad choice if you're looking for scalping and high-frequency trading with tight spreads and fast execution.",{"q":4362,"a":4363},"Is Maven Trading good for beginners?","Maven Trading can be a good prop trading firm for beginners thanks to the cheap fees starting from $13 for the Mini challenge. If you don't like that challenge, there are four more types to choose from, and there are no minimum trading days, making it very flexible. However, if you're a beginner, keep in mind that the forex spreads are wider than most competitors, and they don't provide much educational resources or clarify their rules.","src/content/reviews/rev-maven-trading.json","f169399051f3b856","rev-myfundedfutures",{"id":4366,"data":4368,"filePath":4408,"digest":4409},{"id":4366,"propFirmId":2254,"summary":4369,"pros":4370,"cons":4377,"bestFor":4384,"notIdealFor":4385,"overallScore":4255,"categoryScores":4386,"categorySections":4387,"verdictBlocks":4388,"faq":4392,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 58/100, MyFundedFutures ranked 7th place out of 16 futures prop firms we tested, with our research team having a mixed trading experience. The firm's three account types cater to different types of futures traders, but restrictive payout policies, high monthly fees for some plans, and rigid profit-sharing rules dropped the firm a few places.\n\nWhile the range of futures account types allows for some flexibility compared to other firms, strict consistency rules and limited payout options may make it less ideal for active traders.",[4371,4372,4373,4374,4375,4376],"Specialises in futures trading","Keep 100% of first $10K profit","NinjaTrader, Tradovate, and TradingView platforms","Broad selection of futures contracts across all major asset classes","One-time fee option with Milestone accounts","Structured scaling plan for Starter accounts",[4378,4379,4380,4381,4382,4383],"40% consistency rule on Starter accounts","Limited payout frequency — bi-weekly on Expert plan","Minimal customer support — chat-based and FAQ only","Monthly fees accumulate over time on Starter and Expert","Buffer zone policy resets drawdown protection on Expert withdrawals","No phone support available","Experienced futures traders looking for structured growth, advanced platforms like NinjaTrader and TradingView, and flexible account types with scaling potential","Beginners, forex traders, or those prioritising frequent small payouts and hands-on customer support",{"challenges":31,"spreads":31,"markets":350,"payouts":350,"platforms":66,"trust":350},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4389],{"heading":4390,"body":4391},"Final Verdict on MyFundedFutures","MyFundedFutures focuses on futures trading, offering flexible account options, advanced platforms like NinjaTrader and TradingView, and access to a wide range of futures markets. The 100% profit retention on the first $10,000 is a clear benefit for traders aiming to maximise initial earnings.\n\nHowever, restrictive payout policies, high recurring fees for some accounts, and limited support options may not suit all traders. Milestone accounts, with their one-time fees, are a better fit for those preferring upfront costs over ongoing payments.\n\nThe firm is most suitable for experienced traders looking for structured growth in futures markets and advanced tools but may not be ideal for beginners or those prioritising frequent payouts.",[4393,4396,4399,4402,4405],{"q":4394,"a":4395},"What is MyFundedFutures?","MyFundedFutures is a futures prop trading firm that funds traders who pass its evaluation programs, enabling them to trade futures using the firm's capital rather than their own money. Traders can select from different account types — Starter, Milestone, and Expert — each with varying fees, evaluation stages, and payout options.",{"q":4397,"a":4398},"What is the difference between a sim funded account and a live funded account?","A sim funded account is a simulated trading account that allows you to practice and prove your skills without real capital exposure, whereas a live funded account involves actual capital, placing trades in the live market. Simulated accounts are typically used for evaluation stages, where you must meet performance targets before qualifying for a Live Funded Account.",{"q":4400,"a":4401},"How much is the MyFundedFutures payout?","With MyFundedFutures, you keep 100% of your first $10,000 in profits, followed by a 90/10 profit split. If you're on the Starter plan, you can request payouts every five winning days, with minimum amounts based on your account size. For the Expert plan, payouts are available every two weeks once your account meets a required buffer, with a minimum payout of $1,000.",{"q":4403,"a":4404},"What are the MyFundedFutures account sizes?","MyFundedFutures offers futures trading account sizes of $25,000, $50,000, $100,000, and $150,000. Each account size comes with specific rules for maximum position size, drawdown limits, and payout structures, allowing you to choose an account that aligns with your trading goals and risk tolerance.",{"q":4406,"a":4407},"What is the best futures prop firm?","When we tested futures prop firms in 2026, we found FXIFY Futures and FundedNext Futures were the best, overtaking Topstep. FXIFY and FundedNext are both broker-backed prop trading brands, and offer sister CFD trading challenges giving you more flexibility. They also have competitive fees, quality liquidity providers, and various addons to customise your challenges and funded accounts.","src/content/reviews/rev-myfundedfutures.json","4328e8e8fe9a9903","rev-one-up-trader",{"id":4410,"data":4412,"filePath":4450,"digest":4451},{"id":4410,"propFirmId":2308,"summary":4413,"pros":4414,"cons":4421,"bestFor":4428,"notIdealFor":4429,"overallScore":4430,"categoryScores":4431,"categorySections":4432,"verdictBlocks":4433,"faq":4437,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"OneUp Trader scored 57/100 overall and is a popular prop firm for futures trading. You can qualify for funding in as little as 10 days—or just 5 with the Express Funding option—while keeping 100% of your first $10,000 in profits and 90% after that.\n\nHowever, the futures prop firm has clear limitations. Monthly fees during the evaluation phase can add up, especially if you don't pass on the first try. Some traders have also flagged issues with strict rule enforcement and platform stability. While the evaluation is simple, the tight trailing drawdown can be a hurdle for more aggressive strategies.\n\nOneUp Trader is best suited for disciplined futures traders who value simplicity and platform variety but may not be ideal if you're looking for more asset class flexibility or a lower-cost path to funding.",[4415,4416,4417,4418,4419,4420],"100% of first $10K profit kept by trader","Simple one-step evaluation process","Over 20 supported trading platforms","Free NinjaTrader license included","No daily loss limits during evaluation","On-demand payouts with no fixed schedule",[4422,4423,4424,4425,4426,4427],"Monthly subscription fees add up during evaluation","Futures-only — no forex, crypto, or equities","Tight trailing drawdown can be challenging","$1,000 minimum withdrawal threshold","Card-only payments for challenge fees","No free educational resources","Disciplined futures traders who value a simple one-step evaluation, platform variety with 20+ options, and a generous 90% profit split with 100% of the first $10K","Traders who want forex, crypto, or equities access, prefer lower-cost evaluations, or need automation-friendly rules without strict consistency requirements",57,{"challenges":350,"spreads":31,"markets":31,"payouts":350,"platforms":66,"support":597,"trust":31},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4434],{"heading":4435,"body":4436},"Our Final Verdict On OneUp Trader","OneUp Trader is worth considering if you're focused on futures trading and want a simple, fast-track way to get funded, yet some traders have raised valid concerns.\n\nA major benefit is the one-step evaluation is beginner-friendly, with no daily loss limits and a strong 90% profit split (plus 100% of the first $10K). Platform flexibility is also a major plus, with NinjaTrader access included and over 20 options available, and the Express Funding for returning traders is a helpful feature.\n\nThat said, there are clear limitations. You're restricted to futures only—no forex, crypto, or equities—and the trailing drawdown can make the evaluation tough. The $1,000 minimum payout threshold and card-only payments may also be a downside for smaller accounts. Some experienced traders have flagged concerns about inconsistent rule enforcement and platform reliability.\n\nOverall, OneUp Trader suits disciplined futures traders who prefer a quick and straightforward path to funding, but it may not be the best fit for everyone.",[4438,4441,4444,4447],{"q":4439,"a":4440},"What broker does OneUp Trader use?","OneUp Trader is not a broker-backed prop trading firm. Instead, it partners with several liquidity providers to facilitate futures trading. While not operating under a single brokerage, more than 20 trading platforms are available for you to use, with access to NinjaTrader already provided with each challenge program.",{"q":4442,"a":4443},"Does OneUp Trader accept US clients?","Yes, they accept traders from the United States. Since OneUp Trader focuses on futures trading, it does not face the same restrictions that cover forex and CFD trading. Still, wherever you are, make sure OneUp Trader complies with your local trading regulations.",{"q":4445,"a":4446},"Is OneUp Trader legit or a scam?","OneUp Trader is a legitimate prop firm. While they offer an easy one-step evaluation challenge, fast funding options, and generous profit splits, some traders have voiced concerns about strict rule enforcement and platform stability. The firm holds a 4.7/5 TrustPilot rating from over 2,000 reviews.",{"q":4448,"a":4449},"Are EAs and copy trading allowed with OneUp Trader?","Yes, OneUp Trader allows EAs (Expert Advisors) and automated trading. Copy trading is also allowed, but only between accounts registered under the same name. Group trading, high-frequency trading, and trades lasting under 10 seconds are not permitted.","src/content/reviews/rev-one-up-trader.json","52e17a5579d8ac7a","rev-the-funded-trader",{"id":4452,"data":4454,"filePath":4496,"digest":4497},{"id":4452,"propFirmId":2383,"summary":4455,"pros":4456,"cons":4462,"bestFor":4469,"notIdealFor":4470,"overallScore":1404,"categoryScores":4471,"categorySections":4472,"verdictBlocks":4473,"faq":4477,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"With an overall score of 65/100, The Funded Trader lands in the middle of the pack. It stands out for the sheer number of challenges on offer and scaling that can reach $5 million, but it's not without issues. Support isn't 24/7, response times are often slow, and a low Trustpilot score shows the mixed reputation it has.\n\nTFT offers decent market access, scaling up to $5 million, and profit splits that reach 99% on most accounts. Platform choice is solid with MT5, cTrader, and Match-Trader available. The main drawbacks are high commissions, no published spreads, and constant rule changes.",[4457,4458,4459,4460,4246,4461],"200K challenge accounts available","Established Discord with 110,000+ members","Scaling plan up to $5 million","Profit splits up to 99% on most accounts","Seven challenge types for flexibility",[4463,4464,4465,4466,4467,4468],"Confusing challenge types with frequent rule changes","Low TrustPilot score of 3.0/5 from 22,000+ reviews","$25 fee for cTrader access","No published spread data","Higher commission fees ($4 per lot forex)","Support response times of 1–3 days","Traders who want variety in challenge structures, large account sizes up to $200K, and long-term scaling potential up to $5 million","Traders needing transparent pricing, tight spreads, fast customer support, and consistent rules that don't change frequently",{"challenges":101,"spreads":350,"markets":66,"payouts":350,"platforms":66,"trust":31},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4474],{"heading":4475,"body":4476},"Final Verdict on The Funded Trader","The Funded Trader gives you one of the widest sets of challenge options in the industry, with account scaling that can reach $5 million and three platform choices. The range of evaluations is a plus, but it can also feel confusing, as rules and pricing aren't always consistent.\n\nOn the positive side, payout splits are competitive, scaling up to 99% for most accounts, and payouts are processed in 3 to 5 business days. The main exception is the Classic challenges, which remain fixed at 80%.\n\nWhere TFT falls short is in transparency and reliability. Spreads aren't published, commission fees are higher than many competitors, and support is limited to slower response times. Add to that a mixed Trustpilot score and frequent reports of payout delays, and you're left with a prop firm that offers strong upside but comes with risks.",[4478,4481,4484,4487,4490,4493],{"q":4479,"a":4480},"What is The Funded Trader?","The Funded Trader is a prop trading firm that funds traders through evaluation challenges in forex, commodities, indices, and crypto. Account sizes range from $5,000 to $200,000, with scaling opportunities that reach up to $5 million for consistent performance. Instead of trading live capital, you trade on simulated accounts and receive profit splits based on your results, which start at 80% for Classic challenges and go as high as 99% on tiered accounts.",{"q":4482,"a":4483},"Does the funded trader use real money?","No, The Funded Trader does not use real money during its challenges or funded accounts. It doesn't matter if you are trading during the evaluation process or funded stage, all takes place on simulated accounts that mirror live market conditions. Profit splits are paid from the firm's revenue rather than direct market profits, so while you're not trading real capital, you still earn payouts based on your performance.",{"q":4485,"a":4486},"How much does the funded trader program payout?","Your payout split depends on the account type. Most challenges now use a tiered system that starts at 90% and can scale up to 99% as you complete more withdrawals. The exception is the Classic 1-Step and Classic 2-Step, which remain fixed at 80% from the start and don't scale higher.",{"q":4488,"a":4489},"What are The Funded Trader account sizes?","The Funded Trader offers account sizes ranging from $5,000 to $200,000. Smaller accounts are available on challenges like Knight and Knight Pro, while larger tiers such as Royal, Classic, and Dragon extend up to $200,000. With scaling, you can grow these accounts significantly over time, reaching a maximum of $5 million depending on the challenge type.",{"q":4491,"a":4492},"How quickly can I receive payouts from The Funded Trader?","Processing usually takes 3 to 5 business days after you submit a payout request. The timing of when you can first request a withdrawal depends on your account. For example, Knight and Knight Pro accounts allow payouts anytime once you're profitable, while Dragon accounts start after 7 days, and Royal accounts normally require 30 days unless you purchase the 14 day add-on. After the first payout, most accounts switch to 7 or 14 day cycles.",{"q":4494,"a":4495},"Can you scale your account with The Funded Trader program?","Yes, The Funded Trader program allows account scaling for traders who consistently achieve profit targets, increasing both account size and profit share potential. Eligible traders who maintain at least a 6% profit over three months can expand their account balance by 25% of the initial balance per successful scaling event. This opportunity to grow accounts helps committed traders maximise returns and reach a maximum balance of up to $1.5 million or $5 million, depending on the challenge type.","src/content/reviews/rev-the-funded-trader.json","4698ecc071ddce95","rev-the-trading-pit",{"id":4498,"data":4500,"filePath":4540,"digest":4541},{"id":4498,"propFirmId":2445,"summary":4501,"pros":4502,"cons":4509,"bestFor":4516,"notIdealFor":4517,"overallScore":2525,"categoryScores":4518,"categorySections":4519,"verdictBlocks":4520,"faq":4524,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"The Trading Pit scores 78/100, reflecting a mixed offering that includes both CFD and Futures challenges. While having both markets is uncommon, the prop firm has drawbacks that limit its appeal. Lower-tier profit splits start at 50%, which is lower than many competitors, and some traders report platform stability issues during volatility.\n\nAlthough it offers weekly payouts and multiple trading platforms, including MT4, MT5, cTrader, TradingView, and advanced futures platforms, higher trading costs and inconsistent platform performance make it less competitive for some traders. The 40% consistency rule and set minimum trading days add further constraints, though the structured challenge types across CFDs, Futures, and Stocks provide flexibility for traders who want access to multiple asset classes under one roof.",[4503,4504,4505,4506,4507,4508],"CFDs, Stocks, and Futures challenges available","Weekly payouts with fast 1 business day processing","Wide range of markets including 46 forex pairs","Multiple platform choices including MT4, MT5, cTrader, and TradingView","4.2/5 Trustpilot rating from 700+ reviews","Structured challenge types for different trading styles",[4510,4511,4512,4513,4514,4515],"Small range of crypto markets","Set minimum trading days across all challenges","High commission fees ($5 per lot forex, 0.20% crypto)","Profit splits start at 50% for Classic accounts","40% consistency rule limits single-day profits","$129 activation fee on Futures challenges","Traders who want access to both CFD and Futures markets, structured challenges with transparent rules, and multiple platform choices including advanced futures platforms","Traders looking for higher starting profit splits, low crypto trading costs, or firms without consistency rules and minimum trading day requirements",{"challenges":377,"spreads":66,"markets":377,"payouts":101,"platforms":101,"trust":350},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4521],{"heading":4522,"body":4523},"Our Final Verdict On The Trading Pit","The Trading Pit stands out with its CFD and Futures challenges, offering a unique alternative to many forex-focused prop firms. With funding up to $250,000, weekly payouts, and a choice between one-phase and two-phase evaluations, it provides flexibility for different trading styles. The platform selection is also strong, with access to MT4, MT5, cTrader, TradingView, and advanced futures trading platforms.\n\nHowever, there are some drawbacks. Profit splits for lower-tier accounts start at 50-60%, which is lower than some competitors. Some traders have also reported platform stability issues during high volatility. Additionally, trading costs are mixed — while forex spreads are competitive, crypto commissions and futures market data upgrades may be a concern for cost-conscious traders.\n\nOverall, The Trading Pit is a solid choice for traders who want access to both CFDs and Futures, transparent funding models, and a growing community. If you prioritize weekly payouts and structured challenges, it could be a great fit.",[4525,4528,4531,4534,4537],{"q":4526,"a":4527},"What broker does The Trading Pit use?","The Trading Pit is not a broker-backed prop firm, but partners with different online brokers for liquidity and execution. For cTrader CFD trading, Tickmill is used as the liquidity provider. Other platforms may have different broker arrangements, but The Trading Pit does not operate under a single brokerage. Instead, it integrates with multiple providers to facilitate trading across CFDs and Futures.",{"q":4529,"a":4530},"Does The Trading Pit accept US clients?","The Trading Pit accepts clients from the United States for Futures Challenges only. CFD, Crypto, and Stock Challenges are not currently offered to US traders, but the firm has stated plans to expand these options in the future. Canadian residents face the same restrictions, with only Futures Challenges available at this time.",{"q":4532,"a":4533},"Is The Trading Pit legit or a scam?","The Trading Pit is a legitimate prop firm and not a scam, but has some drawbacks, earning a 78/100 score from Best Prop Firms. While it offers CFD and Futures challenges, weekly payouts, and funding up to $250K, some traders have raised concerns about platform stability during volatility and lower-tier profit splits starting at 50%.",{"q":4535,"a":4536},"What is The Trading Pit's profit split?","The Trading Pit's profit split ranges from 50% to 80%, depending on the challenge type and account tier. Prime challenges offer a fixed 80% split, while Classic challenges start at 50% and scale up to 80% as traders progress. Lower-tier accounts have smaller splits, which some traders find less competitive compared to the top prop firms.",{"q":4538,"a":4539},"Does The Trading Pit allow EAs and copy trading?","The Trading Pit allows EAs (Expert Advisors) on all challenges but only permits copy trading on Futures accounts. CFD challenges do not support copy trading, while Futures traders can use it on both Prime and Classic models, with a limit of up to five linked accounts.","src/content/reviews/rev-the-trading-pit.json","cc63b6d6caeb7420","rev-the5ers",{"id":4542,"data":4544,"filePath":4585,"digest":4586},{"id":4542,"propFirmId":2510,"summary":4545,"pros":4546,"cons":4553,"bestFor":4559,"notIdealFor":4560,"overallScore":2525,"categoryScores":4561,"categorySections":4562,"verdictBlocks":4570,"faq":4574,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142,"youtubeUrl":4584},"The 5%ers scored 78/100 in our 2026 real-money stress test. They aren't the flashiest prop firm out there, and their manual backend processes can be slow, but their trading conditions are elite. During our live spread test, USD/JPY held steady at 0.0 pips, and even during a US unemployment claims release, spreads only widened to 1 pip — while other firms blew out to 4+ pips. The scaling plan is arguably the best in the industry: hit specific milestones and your account doubles, eventually reaching $4 million with a 100% profit split and a monthly salary of up to $10,000. If you value tight spreads and a clear path to scaling over a fancy dashboard, The 5%ers are a top-tier choice.",[4547,4548,4549,4550,4551,4552],"Elite spread stability — 0.0 pips on USD/JPY in testing","$4 per round turn FX commissions (vs $7 industry avg)","$4M scaling plan with 100% profit split","Monthly salary at $350K ($4K) and $500K ($10K)","4.9/5 TrustPilot score — exceptionally high","EAs and weekend holding allowed",[4554,4555,4556,4557,4558],"Dashboard P&L doesn't update in real-time","News trading rules manually enforced with delays (up to a week)","Bootcamp requires mandatory stop-loss on every trade","30-day inactivity rule closes accounts","Profit split starts at 50% on Bootcamp/Hypergrowth","Experienced traders who value institutional-grade spreads, a structured scaling path to $4M, and the rare perk of a monthly salary — especially intraday scalpers who need tight spreads during news events","Traders who want a slick, real-time dashboard experience or who rely heavily on bracket strategies around news releases. Also not ideal if you need a high profit split from day one (Bootcamp starts at 50%)",{"challenges":101,"spreads":101,"markets":66,"payouts":101,"platforms":66,"trust":377},{"challenges":4563,"spreads":4564,"markets":4565,"platforms":4566,"payouts":4567,"support":4568,"trust":4569},"The 5%ers offer three distinct evaluation models: Bootcamp (3-step, low-cost entry from $95), High Stakes (2-step, 1:100 leverage, from $39), and Hyper Growth (1-step with account doubling, from $260). Each caters to different risk appetites. The scaling plan is exceptional — accounts can reach $4M with a 100% profit split, and traders receive monthly salaries at higher funding tiers ($4K at $350K, $10K at $500K). The 5%ers scored 8/10 for challenges.","We scored The 5%ers 8/10 for pricing. FX commissions are $4 per round turn — significantly cheaper than the $7 industry average. During our live test, USD/JPY held at 0.0 pips, and during a US unemployment claims release, spreads only widened to 1 pip while competitors blew out to 4+ pips. Indices have zero commission. Metals, crypto, and commodities use a percentage-based commission formula. The 5%ers scored 8/10 for spreads.","The 5%ers offer CFDs across five asset classes: FX, Metals, Indices, Crypto, and Other Commodities. Leverage varies significantly by program — High Stakes offers up to 1:100 on FX, while Bootcamp and Hyper Growth max out at 1:30. Crypto leverage is limited (1:2 on High Stakes, 1:0.6 on others). No consistency rules are applied. The 5%ers scored 7/10 for markets.","The 5%ers support MetaTrader 5 and MatchTrader. US-based clients typically must use MatchTrader due to MetaQuotes restrictions. During testing, the dashboard P&L didn't update in real-time — often showing profit when MT5 showed drawdown. Always rely on your trading terminal as the source of truth. The 5%ers scored 7/10 for platforms.","Bootcamp and Hyper Growth start with a 50% profit split, scaling to 100%. High Stakes starts at 80%, also scaling to 100%. Minimum payout is $150, processed bi-weekly. Withdrawal methods include Rise (2% fee), Crypto (2% fee), Bank Transfer (3% fee), and HUB Credits (no fee). The 5%ers scored 8/10 for payouts.","The 5%ers provide support during business hours via live chat and email, with an active Discord community. While not 24/7, the support team is responsive to account and platform issues. Educational resources are available through the community channels.","The 5%ers hold a 4.9/5 TrustPilot rating — exceptionally high for the prop firm industry. Founded in 2016, they are one of the longest-running prop firms. They use commercial liquidity providers, which generally results in smoother fills and less 'stop-hunting.' The 50,000+ trader community and consistent payout history add to their credibility. The 5%ers scored 9/10 for trust.",[4571],{"heading":4572,"body":4573},"Final Verdict: 78/100","The 5%ers are a \"trader's prop firm.\" They aren't the flashiest, and their manual backend processes can be slow, but their trading conditions are elite. If you value tight spreads and a clear path to scaling over a fancy dashboard, they are a top-tier choice for 2026.\n\nThe scaling plan is genuinely exceptional — not just because of the $4M ceiling, but because of the salary component at $350K and $500K funding levels. Few firms in the industry offer this kind of safety net for funded traders.\n\nThe main drawbacks are the dashboard lag (always rely on MT5 for real-time P&L) and the manual enforcement of news trading rules, which caused a profitable trade of mine to be disqualified nearly a week after the fact. These backend issues are the primary reason the overall score sits at 78 rather than higher.\n\nFor experienced traders who can manage their risk, understand the rules, and don't need a polished UI to feel confident, The 5%ers deliver where it matters most: execution, spreads, and a genuine path to professional-level funding.",[4575,4578,4581],{"q":4576,"a":4577},"Does The 5%ers allow EAs?","Yes, automated trading and EAs are allowed on all account types, provided they are not used for arbitrage or high-frequency botting that exploits the demo environment. The EA must set a Stop Loss on every position and must not copy trades from other persons' signals, perform tick scalping, or use emulators. Accounts found using EAs that violate these rules will be canceled, banned, and not refunded.",{"q":4579,"a":4580},"Can I trade news at The 5%ers?","Yes, news trading is permitted on Hyper Growth and Bootcamp programs, but bracket strategies (placing pending orders on both sides of a news release) are prohibited. On the High Stakes program, executing orders 2 minutes before until 2 minutes after high-impact news is prohibited. Be aware that news trading rules may be manually enforced with delays.",{"q":4582,"a":4583},"How does the $4M scaling work?","On the Hyper Growth and Bootcamp plans, every time you hit a 5–10% profit target (depending on the stage), the firm doubles your capital. Once you hit the $2.5M mark, your profit share moves to 100%. At $350K funding, you start receiving a $4,000 fixed monthly salary. At $500K, that increases to $10,000/month. The maximum account size is $4 million.","https://www.youtube.com/embed/1otayPx_z1s","src/content/reviews/rev-the5ers.json","60eb821a05a21730","rev-think-capital",{"id":4587,"data":4589,"filePath":4631,"digest":4632},{"id":4587,"propFirmId":2566,"summary":4590,"pros":4591,"cons":4598,"bestFor":4603,"notIdealFor":4604,"overallScore":2188,"categoryScores":4605,"categorySections":4606,"verdictBlocks":4614,"faq":4618,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"ThinkCapital scores 76/100 as a broker-backed prop firm offering account sizes up to $200K and fees from $39. With three evaluation challenges, up to 90% profit splits, and platforms like MT5 and ThinkTrader, it balances competitive trading conditions with reliable bi-weekly payouts.\n\nThinkCapital is a solid choice among broker-backed prop trading firms, offering competitive evaluation challenges and the flexibility of account sizes up to $200,000. Its three challenge types cater to traders of varying skill levels, from one-step evaluations for simplicity to multi-step processes for more advanced traders. With up to 90% profit splits, affordable fees starting at $39, and reliable bi-weekly payouts, it's well-suited for those seeking a straightforward path to funded trading.",[4592,4593,4594,4595,4596,4597],"Broker-backed prop firm","Bi-weekly and weekly payout options","Three challenge types to suit different styles","TradingView integration via ThinkTrader","Scaling plan up to $1.5M","Competitive fees starting from $39",[4599,4600,4601,4602],"Crypto is the only payout method","Smaller trading community","US traders restricted to ThinkTrader only","EA support requires paid add-on","Traders seeking a broker-backed prop firm with flexible challenge types and competitive pricing from $39","Traders who need bank transfer payouts or those requiring MT5 access from the US",{"challenges":377,"spreads":377,"markets":377,"payouts":377,"platforms":377,"trust":600},{"challenges":4607,"spreads":4608,"markets":4609,"platforms":4610,"payouts":4611,"support":4612,"trust":4613},"ThinkCapital offers three challenges — **Lightning** (1-step), **Dual Step** (2-step), and **Nexus** (3-step) — with account sizes from $5K to $200K and fees starting at just **$39**.\n\nThe Lightning Challenge is the simplest route with a **10% profit target**, **3% daily loss limit**, **6% max loss**, and conservative **1:30 leverage**. Dual Step requires **8% in Phase 1** and **5% in Phase 2** (13% total) with **1:100 leverage**, while Nexus is the most demanding with **18% total** across three phases at **1:100 leverage**.\n\nThe scaling plan increases account balance by **20% every 3 months** for traders achieving 10% total profit, allowing growth from up to $300K combined capital to a maximum of **$1.5 million**. Add-ons include EAs (+25%), 90% profit split (+25%), news trading (+25%), weekly payouts (+25%), and reduced targets (+10%). ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for challenges.","ThinkCapital does not publish average spreads, but observed spreads during testing showed **ThinkTrader EUR/USD starting at 0.8 pips**, widening to 2.5+ pips for minor pairs. MT5 offers tighter raw spreads.\n\nMT5 charges a **$4 per lot per side commission** ($8 round-trip) on forex and precious metals, with commission-free trading on indices, commodities, and crypto. ThinkTrader charges **no commission** on any asset class but has wider spreads to compensate.\n\nWhile MT5's commission is slightly above the $3–$3.50 per side industry average, the flexibility to choose between raw spreads (MT5) and commission-free trading (ThinkTrader) gives traders options to suit their strategy. ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for spreads.","ThinkCapital provides access to **forex**, **indices**, **commodities** (gold, silver, oil), and **cryptocurrencies** across both MT5 and ThinkTrader platforms.\n\nLeverage varies by challenge type and platform. For the Lightning Challenge, forex is **1:30**, indices **1:5**, commodities **1:10–1:20**, and crypto **1:1–1:2**. Dual Step and Nexus challenges offer higher leverage: forex **1:100**, indices **1:15**, commodities **1:15–1:30**, and crypto **1:1–1:2**.\n\nThinkTrader offers higher leverage on precious metals (up to 1:30 for Dual Step/Nexus) compared to MT5 (1:15), making it more appealing for commodities traders. ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for markets.","ThinkCapital offers two platforms — **MT5** and **ThinkTrader** with TradingView integration. MT5 is the industry standard with advanced charting, multi-asset capabilities, and EA support (add-on required). ThinkTrader combines a user-friendly interface with professional-grade TradingView tools.\n\n**Important:** US-based traders cannot use MT5 due to regulatory restrictions and are limited to ThinkTrader. Both platforms support desktop, web, and mobile access.\n\nThinkTrader's TradingView integration provides professional charting, real-time collaboration tools, and an intuitive interface suitable for both beginners and experienced traders. ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for platforms.","Profit splits start at the default rate with the potential to increase to **90%** through the profit split add-on, available for Dual Step and Nexus challenges. Payouts follow a **bi-weekly schedule** (every 14 days from first trade), with a **weekly payout add-on** available.\n\nAll payouts are processed within **3 business days**. Crypto withdrawals typically appear within **24–48 hours** after processing. Currently, **cryptocurrency is the only payout method**, though bank transfers are expected to be available in the future.\n\nThere is no minimum payout limit, though profits must exceed $100 to cover transaction fees. ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for payouts.","ThinkCapital provides customer support through **live chat**, **email**, and a **contact form**. Live chat offers instant assistance for urgent queries, while email and the contact form handle non-urgent requests.\n\nThe firm's **YouTube channel** features over **100 videos** covering topics from risk management and platform tutorials to interviews with successful traders and trading psychology. This library serves as a comprehensive educational resource for traders at all levels.\n\nChallenge fees range from **$39 to $949** depending on account size and challenge type, payable via cryptocurrency or credit/debit cards. ThinkCapital scored 9/10 for support.","ThinkCapital has a **Trustpilot rating of 4.3/5** from **500+ reviews**, with 78% awarding five stars. Users praise transparent rules, fast payouts, and responsive support. The firm responds to critical feedback within 24 hours.\n\nThe **Discord community** has **11,700 members** with channels for trade psychology, general questions, and trading ideas. On **X (Twitter)**, ThinkCapital has **17,800+ followers** with regular updates on trading rules and features.\n\nWith approximately **12,100 monthly Google searches** and **141,681 global website visits** (March 2025), ThinkCapital ranks 29th by search volume and 32nd by traffic among prop firms. Over **10,000 funded traders** currently use the platform. ThinkCapital scored 9.5/10 for trust.",[4615],{"heading":4616,"body":4617},"Final Verdict on ThinkCapital","ThinkCapital is a solid choice among broker-backed prop trading firms, offering competitive evaluation challenges and the flexibility of account sizes up to $200,000. Its three challenge types cater to traders of varying skill levels, from one-step evaluations for simplicity to multi-step processes for more advanced traders.\n\nWith up to **90% profit splits**, affordable fees starting at **$39**, and reliable bi-weekly payouts, it's well-suited for those seeking a straightforward path to funded trading. The platforms — MT5 and ThinkTrader — provide access to advanced tools and a range of asset classes including forex, commodities, indices, and cryptocurrencies.\n\nHowever, payout options are currently limited to cryptocurrency, and the trading community is smaller compared to competitors. US-based traders are restricted to ThinkTrader as MT5 is unavailable in the region. Despite these drawbacks, ThinkCapital scores highly for its transparency, accessible trading conditions, and responsive customer support.",[4619,4622,4625,4628],{"q":4620,"a":4621},"Does ThinkCapital take US clients?","Yes, ThinkCapital accepts clients from the United States and US territories, but they are limited to using the ThinkTrader platform. MetaTrader 5 (MT5) is unavailable to US traders due to regulatory restrictions, making ThinkTrader the primary option for accessing ThinkCapital's trading tools and features.",{"q":4623,"a":4624},"Is ThinkCapital safe or a scam?","ThinkCapital is a legitimate prop trading firm with a Trustpilot score of 4.3 out of 5 stars, reflecting positive feedback on its transparency, fast payouts, and responsive customer support. With clear trading conditions and reliable customer support, ThinkCapital is considered safe for traders seeking funded account opportunities.",{"q":4626,"a":4627},"What are the latest user reviews for ThinkCapital?","Recent user reviews for ThinkCapital are largely positive, with many users praising its user-friendly interface, integration with TradingView, and reliable payout processes. Traders highlight prompt customer support and transparent trading rules as notable strengths. Some reviews mention quick payouts within three business days.",{"q":4629,"a":4630},"How much does ThinkCapital cost?","ThinkCapital's challenge fees range from $39 for the Nexus $5K account to $949 for Lightning and Dual Step $200K accounts. The Nexus challenge offers the most affordable entry point, while Lightning and Dual Step are priced identically across all account sizes from $5K to $200K.","src/content/reviews/rev-think-capital.json","55463579b51ef353","rev-topstep",{"id":4633,"data":4635,"filePath":4680,"digest":4681},{"id":4633,"propFirmId":2624,"summary":4636,"pros":4637,"cons":4644,"bestFor":4650,"notIdealFor":4651,"overallScore":3091,"categoryScores":4652,"categorySections":4653,"verdictBlocks":4661,"faq":4665,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Topstep scored 83/100 in our 2026 testing, placing 3rd on our list of the 10 best futures prop firms. While FXIFY Futures and FundedNext Futures ranked higher due to lower fees and faster scaling, Topstep is still a solid choice thanks to its reputation, wide platform selection, and futures-only focus. Its evaluation has no time limits, and funded traders earn a 100% profit split on the first $10,000, then 90% after that. Monthly data fees in the Live Funded Account can add to your costs and dropped the firm's overall rating a few points, but Topstep's score reflects its clear rules, consistent payout model, and platform flexibility.",[4638,4639,4640,4641,4642,4643],"100% profit split on first $10K","Commission-free on TopstepX","Profit withdrawals processed daily","Huge platform selection (15+ options)","No time limits on Trading Combine","155,000+ member Discord community",[4645,4646,4647,4648,4649],"$150K maximum funding limit","$99/month NinjaTrader fee in Live Funded","Only futures markets available","$135/month per exchange data fees in Live Funded","3.6/5 Trustpilot score lower than newer competitors","Futures traders who want an established, reputable firm with broad platform support and a generous 100% profit split on first $10K","Forex or CFD traders — Topstep is futures-only. Also not ideal for traders who want low ongoing costs, as exchange data fees add up in the Live Funded stage",{"challenges":66,"spreads":66,"markets":101,"payouts":377,"platforms":203,"trust":377},{"challenges":4654,"spreads":4655,"markets":4656,"platforms":4657,"payouts":4658,"support":4659,"trust":4660},"Topstep offers a two-step evaluation process for futures traders. Step 1 is the Trading Combine ($49–$149/month), a simulated environment with profit targets and risk limits. Step 2 is the Express Funded Account ($149 activation fee), where traders earn real profits. Finally, the Live Funded Account provides access to real capital with a 100% profit split on the first $10K, then 90% after that.\n\nThe Trading Combine has no time limits. Profit targets are $3,000 (50K), $6,000 (100K), and $9,000 (150K). A consistency target ensures no more than 50% of profits come from one day. The scaling plan limits position sizes: 5 lots ($50K), 10 lots ($100K), 15 lots ($150K). Topstep scored 7/10 for challenges.","Topstep exclusively operates within futures markets, meaning there are no spreads. However, multiple layers of commissions and fees apply depending on platform, exchange, and challenge stage.\n\nTopstepX charges no commission fees ($0.04 + exchange fees per round turn), making it the most cost-effective option. Other platforms range from $1.52 to $2.04+ per round turn. In the Live Funded Account, traders pay $135/month per exchange for professional data, plus optional Level 2 Depth of Market data at $39/month. Reset fees are $49–$149 depending on account size. Topstep scored 7/10 for spreads/pricing.","Topstep provides access to 32 different futures markets across forex, equity indices, oil & gas, precious metals, and agricultural commodities.\n\nForex futures include 8 products (6A, 6B, 6E, 6J, 6S and micros). Equity futures cover 9 products including E-mini S&P 500, Micro E-mini S&P, E-mini NASDAQ, and Micro Bitcoin/Ether. Oil & gas includes crude oil, natural gas, and heating oil. Precious metals cover gold, silver, and copper with micro variants. Agricultural futures include corn, wheat, soybeans, and livestock. Maximum position sizes scale with account: 5 lots ($50K), 10 lots ($100K), 15 lots ($150K). Topstep scored 8/10 for markets.","Topstep offers a huge variety of trading platforms, both free and paid. Free options include TopstepX (commission-free), Quantower, Tradovate, TradingView, and T4. Paid options include NinjaTrader (free during Combine, $99/month in Live Funded), R|Trader Pro, ATAS OrderFlow, MotiveWave, VolFix, Bookmap, and more.\n\nPlatforms connect via different data feeds: Rithmic (low-latency), CQG (wide access), CTS (reliable execution), and Sim2Funded (TopstepX exclusive). Platform selection at the Combine stage affects ongoing costs — switching between data feeds requires starting a new Combine. Topstep scored 10/10 for platforms.","Topstep traders keep 100% of the first $10,000 in profits, then 90% after that. Payouts can be requested after achieving 5 non-consecutive winning days ($200+ each). Initially, up to 50% of account balance can be withdrawn per request. After 30 winning days, 100% balance access is unlocked.\n\nWithdrawal methods include Wise (1–3 days), ACH (1–3 days), Wire Transfer (3–5 days), and International SWIFT (5–10 days). Monthly fees are paid via Visa, Mastercard, Amex, Discover, or PayPal. Inactive accounts are closed after 30 days. Topstep scored 9/10 for payouts.","Topstep provides 24/7 customer support via live chat, email, WhatsApp, and a direct helpline. TopstepTV on YouTube (120,000+ subscribers) streams daily live trading sessions with expert analysis, coaching, and guest appearances.\n\nAdditional educational resources include blogs, newsletters, podcasts, interactive webinars, and group coaching sessions. Content covers trading psychology, market analysis, and strategy development. Topstep offers one of the strongest educational packages among futures prop firms.","Topstep holds a 3.6/5 Trustpilot rating from over 13,000 reviews. Positive reviews highlight strong support and educational tools, while negative feedback mentions occasional technical issues. Topstep collaborates with established brokerages like Plus500 and NinjaTrader.\n\nThe Discord community has 155,000+ members with channels for market discussion, platform support, coaching, and community events. Social media presence includes 39K Facebook followers, 81.4K Twitter/X followers, and 25K LinkedIn followers. Topstep scored 9/10 for trust.",[4662],{"heading":4663,"body":4664},"Final Verdict on Topstep","Topstep is a strong option for futures traders looking for a structured, well-supported path to funding, and placed third out of all the futures firms we tested. However, if you're looking to focus primarily on forex trading, there are better-suited firms such as IC Funded or FundedNext, as Topstep specializes purely in futures markets.\n\nOne of the key features of Topstep is the 100% profit share on your first $10,000, which is more generous than most competitors. After that, the 90/10 split is still competitive. Keep in mind that market data fees can add up quickly, especially in the Live Funded Account, where traders must cover the costs themselves.\n\nThe evaluation process is clear and manageable, with no time limits to complete the Trading Combine, allowing traders to progress at their own pace. This, combined with the flexibility in trading platforms, makes Topstep an attractive option for futures traders who prioritize risk management and consistent profitability.\n\nOverall, Topstep is a solid option for anyone looking at trading futures, with the prop firm offering a high profit share and flexible platform choices. Though, it's important to factor in the additional costs and fees involved.",[4666,4668,4671,4674,4677],{"q":4406,"a":4667},"FXIFY Futures is the best futures prop firm based on our firsthand testing, scoring 88/100. FundedNext Futures scored 84/100 and Topstep scored 83/100, placing second and third. We reviewed over a dozen futures prop firms, comparing key factors like payout structure, platform access, challenge flexibility, and overall value.",{"q":4669,"a":4670},"What are the requirements to get funded by Topstep?","To get funded by Topstep, traders must pass the Trading Combine, meeting profit targets and staying within risk limits. For a $50K account, the profit target is $3,000, and the maximum loss limit is $2,000. Traders must also demonstrate consistency, ensuring profits are not overly concentrated in one day. After passing the Combine, traders move to an Express Funded Account, where they must complete five profitable trading days to qualify for the Live Funded Account.",{"q":4672,"a":4673},"What are the requirements to pass the Topstep Trading Combine?","To pass the Topstep Trading Combine, traders must meet specific profit targets while staying within risk limits. For a $50K account, the profit target is $3,000, while for a $100K account, it's $6,000. Traders must also avoid exceeding the maximum loss limit (e.g., $2,000 for a $50K account). Additionally, traders must demonstrate consistent performance by ensuring no more than 50% of profits come from one trading day.",{"q":4675,"a":4676},"How much do Topstep traders make?","Topstep traders can make 100% of their first $10,000 in profits, then 90% on all earnings after that. This profit split is competitive, especially for futures traders. Earnings depend on account size, trading performance, and risk management. For example, with a $50K account, traders must hit a $3,000 profit target.",{"q":4678,"a":4679},"Is Topstep a proprietary trading firm?","Yes, Topstep is a proprietary trading firm that funds traders with its own capital, allowing them to trade financial markets without risking personal funds. In return, the firm takes a portion of the trader's profits through a profit split. Topstep evaluates traders through their Trading Combine challenge, focusing on risk management and consistent profitability.","src/content/reviews/rev-topstep.json","186ece76ff3eb900","rev-trade-the-pool",{"id":4682,"data":4684,"filePath":4721,"digest":4722},{"id":4682,"propFirmId":2676,"summary":4685,"pros":4686,"cons":4693,"bestFor":4700,"notIdealFor":4701,"overallScore":66,"categoryScores":4702,"categorySections":4703,"verdictBlocks":4704,"faq":4708,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":240},"Trade The Pool is a US stock prop firm offering access to 12,000+ real equities and ETFs using exchange data from NASDAQ, NYSE and CBOE. It scored 70/100 in testing thanks to clear rules and deep market coverage, but its strict volume limits and lack of automation during the evaluation won't suit every style.\n\nThe firm is operated by Five Percent Online Ltd (The 5%ers), but this branch focuses on US stock markets and exchange-traded funds only, rather than forex, crypto or commodity CFDs. You get four one-step challenges across day and swing accounts, giving you a choice between intraday rules or multi-day holding.\n\nIt isn't broker-backed, but you still get real exchange data, clear risk limits, and access to more than 12,000 tradeable symbols. The trading rules can feel strict at first, yet they're consistent, which helps anyone who prefers a straightforward evaluation without hidden conditions.",[4687,4688,4689,4690,4691,4692],"Access to 12,000+ US stocks and ETFs","Direct exchange data from NASDAQ, NYSE and CBOE","Transparent risk management structure","Overnight and weekend holds on swing accounts","One-step evaluation across all challenge types","Scaling plan with proportional account growth",[4694,4695,4696,4697,4698,4699],"Volume limits restrict size on thin tickers","No automation allowed during evaluations","Simulated environment only with no broker backing","Consistency rule affects trade distribution","Single platform (TraderEvolution only)","No refund on challenge fees","Manual stock and ETF day traders who want real exchange data, deep US equity coverage, and a straightforward one-step evaluation","Scalpers, algorithmic traders, or multi-asset traders who need tighter costs, automation, or platform flexibility beyond TraderEvolution",{"challenges":101,"spreads":66,"markets":101,"payouts":350,"platforms":350,"support":350,"trust":66},{"challenges":3132,"spreads":3132,"markets":3132,"platforms":3132,"payouts":3132,"support":3132,"trust":3132},[4705],{"heading":4706,"body":4707},"Our Final Verdict On Trade The Pool","Trade The Pool ends up at 70/100 because it does a lot right, especially around stock access, real exchange data and simple one-step evaluations. Those strengths push up its overall score and make it a solid choice if you want a realistic US equities environment without the usual CFD limitations.\n\nIt doesn't score higher because trading costs add up on high-volume styles, payouts aren't the most flexible, and you're limited to a single platform with no automation during evaluations. Those factors pull down the Spreads, Platforms and Payouts categories.\n\nOverall, TTP suits manual stock and ETF traders who want depth, clarity and real data. It's less ideal for scalpers, algo traders or multi-asset traders who need tighter costs or more platform options. If you're focused on US equities and trade manually, pick the day or swing challenge that matches how long you like to hold positions and you'll settle in easily.",[4709,4712,4715,4718],{"q":4710,"a":4711},"Is Trade the Pool legit?","Yes, Trade The Pool is considered legitimate as a stock and ETF prop firm with a clear rule set and transparent risk management. It operates under Five Percent Online Ltd, the same company behind The 5%ers, and uses real exchange data from NASDAQ, NYSE and CBOE, which helps keep pricing and executions consistent with the underlying markets. The prop trading program runs entirely in a simulated environment, so it isn't a brokerage, but its rules, evaluation criteria and funded account structure are fully published and easy to verify.",{"q":4713,"a":4714},"Is there a prop firm with as much stock access as Trade the Pool?","Very few prop firms offer the same stock and ETF access as Trade The Pool. Most stock prop trading firms rely on CFD-style feeds with a few hundred synthetic tickers, while TTP gives you more than 12,000 real US-listed stocks and ETFs with exchange data from NASDAQ, NYSE and CBOE. That includes penny stocks, small caps, sector ETFs and leveraged products, which is wider than what most prop firms offer.",{"q":4716,"a":4717},"Does Trade the Pool pay out?","Yes, Trade The Pool pays funded traders on a 14-day cycle once the account has at least $300 in profit. Payouts are processed after you close all open positions and the risk team completes a quick review. Payments are sent through the same processors used for initial challenge fee payments, including major credit cards, PayPal and regional methods like SEPA or iDeal.",{"q":4719,"a":4720},"Can I use Interactive Brokers with Trade the Pool?","No, you cannot use the Interactive Brokers platform with Trade The Pool. Your only option is TraderEvolution, which is their in-house equities platform built around real exchange data. Even though Trade The Pool uses pricing from NASDAQ, NYSE and CBOE, all trading must happen inside their own environment because the evaluation and funded stages run on simulated accounts rather than a live brokerage.","src/content/reviews/rev-trade-the-pool.json","c01f396d363adbe6","rev-tradeday",{"id":4723,"data":4725,"filePath":4734,"digest":4735},{"id":4723,"propFirmId":2822,"summary":4726,"pros":4727,"cons":4730,"bestFor":4732,"notIdealFor":4733,"verified":110,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":1273},"TradeDay is a futures prop firm offering funded accounts up to $250K with competitive evaluation requirements and multiple platform options.",[4728,4729,3164],"Up to $250K funded accounts","100% profit split potential",[4731,3594],"Limited track record","Futures traders wanting large account sizes","Traders seeking forex or CFD markets","src/content/reviews/rev-tradeday.json","98c1cf8dcc263b49","rev-tradeify",{"id":4736,"data":4738,"filePath":4783,"digest":4784},{"id":4736,"propFirmId":2750,"summary":4739,"pros":4740,"cons":4747,"bestFor":4754,"notIdealFor":4755,"overallScore":4756,"categoryScores":4757,"categorySections":4758,"verdictBlocks":4766,"faq":4770,"verified":26,"flagged":110,"methodologyVersion":3104,"lastReviewedAt":142},"Tradeify scored 82/100 when our research team tested and reviewed the popular US futures prop firm. As well as being broker-backed and offering Tradovate, TradingView and NinjaTrader, instant futures funding is also available. The funding options are flexible, and payouts are fast once you're verified. We marked it down for ongoing monthly fees that can add up, email-only support, and basically non-existent education. If you already know what you're doing, it's a clean setup.",[4741,4742,4743,4744,4745,4746],"Instant funding futures trading","Fast profit payouts (24–72 hours)","Real exchange access (CME, CBOT, COMEX, NYMEX)","No hidden trading fees","Strong Discord community (~30,000 members)","Three distinct funding models",[4748,4749,4750,4751,4752,4753],"Strict payout rules and consistency caps","No weekend trading on any model","No phone support — email only","High fees for add-ons (Level 2 data, Order Flow+)","Minimal educational materials","Monthly billing continues until manually cancelled","Experienced futures traders who want real exchange access, multiple funding paths, and fast payouts — especially intraday scalpers comfortable with Tradovate or TradingView","Beginner traders who need education and hand-holding, or traders who rely on EAs, copy trading, or weekend holding. Also not ideal if you're in a restricted country",82,{"challenges":101,"spreads":66,"markets":101,"payouts":101,"platforms":377,"trust":377},{"challenges":4759,"spreads":4760,"markets":4761,"platforms":4762,"payouts":4763,"support":4764,"trust":4765},"Tradeify runs three futures funding models: Advanced (1-step, intraday trailing drawdown, monthly fees from $69), Growth (1-step, EOD trailing drawdown, monthly fees from $139), and Lightning (instant funding, one-time fees from $349). All models have trailing drawdowns but differ in risk parameters and fee structures. Scored 8/10 for challenges.","Tradeify charges a flat $1.29 per side ($2.58 round turn) across all asset classes. Exchange and regulatory fees vary by contract — Micro Bitcoin can cost $8+ round trip while Micro Ether is around $2.83. Level 1 data is free; Level 2 costs $16–$41/month extra. Scored 7/10 for pricing.","Full access to regulated US futures markets through CME, CBOT, COMEX, and NYMEX via Tradovate. Indices, currencies, metals, energies, agriculturals, and crypto futures available. Contract limits based on account size (5–15 standard contracts). EUREX available as paid add-on. Scored 8/10 for markets.","Three platforms supported: Tradovate (web/mobile, default), TradingView (charting-focused, via Tradovate backend), and NinjaTrader (desktop only, advanced automation). All execution routes through Tradovate. Scored 9/10 for platforms.","90% profit split. Payouts via Rise Pay and Plane Payouts. Requires 10 trading days and 5 profitable days over $200 before first withdrawal. Lightning minimum $1,000 withdrawal. Consistency rules cap daily profit at 35% (Advanced/Growth) or 20% (Lightning). Scored 8/10 for payouts.","Email-only support during business hours Mon–Fri. Website chatbot redirects to manual support. No phone support, no priority tiers. No formal education, tutorials, or onboarding content.","4.7/5 Trustpilot rating from 1,800+ verified reviews. ~90% five-star reviews. Active Discord community with ~30,000 members. Broker-backed via Tradovate with real exchange access. Extensive restricted countries list. Scored 9/10 for trust.",[4767],{"heading":4768,"body":4769},"Final Verdict: 82/100","Tradeify is a strong pick for futures traders who want real exchange access, multiple funding options, and a clean setup. The challenges are well-defined, with clear risk rules and decent flexibility depending on how you trade. Payouts are quick, and platform access is solid, especially if you're already comfortable with Tradovate or TradingView.\n\nIt's less beginner-friendly though. Support can be slow, there's no real education, and once you're funded, there's no room for error. Add-on fees and strict payout rules can trip up newer traders.",[4771,4774,4777,4780],{"q":4772,"a":4773},"Is Tradeify a legit futures prop firm?","Yes, Tradeify is a legitimate futures prop firm offering real exchange access through CME, CBOT, COMEX, and NYMEX via Tradovate. They've built a strong presence with over 1,800 verified reviews on Trustpilot and a 4.7 out of 5 rating, along with an active Discord community of nearly 30,000 traders. Payouts are processed fast using third-party providers, and rules are clearly outlined on their website.",{"q":4775,"a":4776},"How much is Tradeify per month?","Tradeify's monthly costs depend on the challenge type and account size. The Advanced Challenge starts at $69 per month, while the Growth Challenge ranges from $139 to $339. The Lightning Challenge is a one-time payment model starting at $349 with no ongoing fees. Keep in mind, billing continues until you cancel it manually, even if you fail the challenge. Add-ons like Level 2 data or premium tools are charged separately.",{"q":4778,"a":4779},"Where is Tradeify located?","Tradeify is a US-based futures prop firm that partners with Tradovate for brokerage and execution. All trading is done through regulated US exchanges, and their backend infrastructure is tied into the CME Group. Their platform access and payout services are aligned with US market hours and compliance rules.",{"q":4781,"a":4782},"What countries are eligible for Tradeify?","Most countries can join Tradeify, but some regions are restricted due to broker and compliance rules. You can sign up from the USA, UK, Australia, and most of Europe. However, countries like Afghanistan, North Korea, Russia, and much of Africa and the Middle East are fully blocked. Others, including China, Canada (Ontario), UAE, and South Korea, can access Sim Funded accounts but not Live Funded status.","src/content/reviews/rev-tradeify.json","6f8ee61368f9df05","blog",["Map",4787,4788,4979,4980,207,5167,5335,5336,4795,5442,5603,5604,2465,5781,5950,5951,6044,6045,1975,6211,6393,6394,6501,6502,5127,6573,6621,6622,6699,6700,2470,6782,6943,6944,7068,7069,9,7163,7291,7292,7376,7377,6546,7501,6400,7584,7684,7685,7758,7759],"australia",{"id":4787,"data":4789,"body":4821,"filePath":4822,"digest":4823,"rendered":4824,"legacyId":4978},{"title":4790,"excerpt":4791,"category":4792,"tags":4793,"coverImage":4797,"author":4798,"authorImage":4799,"publishedAt":1273,"featured":110,"readingTimeMinutes":104,"youtubeVideoId":4800,"featuredFirms":4801},"Best Prop Firms in Australia","We tested dozens of the top prop trading firms to find the best challenges to become a funded trader in 2026. Our firsthand testing focuses on areas like challenges and rules, fees and spreads, profit splits and scaling, market access and leverage, and trading platform options. Here's our final list of the 10 best prop firms.","Regional",[4794,4795,4796],"Australia","forex","funded accounts","/images/guides/Australia brokers.png","Noam Korbl","https://www.bestpropfirms.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/noam-korbl-300x280-1.png","dZ7gorgnMvU",[4802,4804,4806,4808,4810,4812,4815,4817,4819],{"slug":728,"descriptor":4803},"Best Prop Firm For Australian Traders",{"slug":584,"descriptor":4805},"Profit Share Scales to 100%",{"slug":332,"descriptor":4807},"1,100+ Financial Markets",{"slug":1599,"descriptor":4809},"Instant Funding Prop Firm",{"slug":1392,"descriptor":4811},"Good TradingView Prop Firm",{"slug":4813,"descriptor":4814},"thinkcapital","Low Challenge Fees",{"slug":1917,"descriptor":4816},"Top Forex Prop Firm",{"slug":1550,"descriptor":4818},"Best Futures Prop Firm",{"slug":1002,"descriptor":4820},"Good Scaling Plan","## What Are The Best Prop Firms In 2026?\n\nProp trading lets you trade with a firm's capital, so you're not risking your own money. In exchange, you split your profits with the firm. With more and more prop firms popping up, you now have options with lower entry fees and higher profit splits. We reviewed the best prop firms, focusing on things like low challenge fees, access to different markets, fair profit-sharing models, and transparent trading rules.\n\n---\n\n## 1. DNA Funded — Best Prop Firm For Australian Traders\n\nDNA Funded ranked 1st place in our list of the best prop firms, earning a top score of 97/100 for its low challenge fees from $49, flexible one- and two-step evaluations, and 80%–90% profit splits. Backed by DNA Markets, it offers tight spreads and uses the TradeLocker platform. You get access to over 800 markets including forex, stocks, and crypto, making it a strong option whether you're just starting out or scaling up.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/dna-funded-logo.png\" alt=\"DNA Funded logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">DNA Funded\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Best Prop Firm For Australian Traders\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.9 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/dna-funded\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://partners.dnafunded.com/click?campaign_id=1&ref_id=30\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\" />\u003C/svg>\n    Visit DNA Funded\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">25% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS25\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Fees from $49 and unique addons\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Low commission $5 roundturn\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Forex, crypto, stocks, and more\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>No MT4 or MT5\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Scaling plan TBC\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>No instant funding\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n### Why DNA Funded is #1 Best Prop Firm\n\nBased on our analysis of the top prop firms worldwide, we found DNA Funded to be the best prop firm overall with a score of 97/100.\n\nThe Australian-based prop firm is backed by regulated broker DNA Markets (ASIC AFSL 514425), offering traders access to institutional-grade conditions like tight spreads, fast execution, and low trading costs. It stands out for its flexible one-step and two-step challenges, competitive fees, and profit splits of up to 90%.\n\nWith TradeLocker integrated with TradingView, access to 800+ markets, and trading rule sets that align with forex broker compliance standards, DNA Funded offers the most complete setup we've tested.\n\nUse PROPFIRMS25 to get 25% off challenge fees, making it cheaper to get started!\n\n### Prop Challenges and Accounts\n\nDNA Funded offers three challenge types, catering to various trading styles:\n\n- **Single Helix (1-step challenge):** Account sizes from $5,000 to $200,000. Fees start at $59, with a 10% profit target and no time limits, making it ideal for swing traders and those focused on longer-term strategies.\n- **Double Helix (2-step challenge):** Account sizes also range from $5,000 to $200,000, with fees starting at $49. Phase 1 requires a 10% profit target, while Phase 2 lowers it to 5%, with flexible trading days.\n- **Rapid Challenge (1-step challenge):** Designed for more experienced traders with account sizes ranging from $10,000 to $100,000, and fees from $99. This challenge requires a 5% profit target to be met within 10 days, with a stricter drawdown limit, making it suitable for scalpers or high-frequency traders.\n\n| DNA Funded Account Type | Challenge Fees | Account Sizes | Early Payout (14→7 Days) Addon | Profit Split Increase (80%→90%) Addon |\n|-------------------------|---------------|---------------|-------------------------------|--------------------------------------|\n| **Single Helix (1 Step)** | $59 - $1,451 | 5K - 200K | Yes | No |\n| **Double Helix (2 Step)** | $49 - $1,295 | 5K - 200K | No | Yes |\n| **Pro Challenge** | $99 - $714 | 10K - 100K | Yes | Yes |\n\nAfter passing the evaluation process of your choosing, you will receive a certificate of recognition as funded traders do when completing the challenge firsthand.\n\n### Markets and Leverage\n\nDNA Funded provides access to over 800 forex, commodities, indices, stocks, and crypto markets (with restrictions on crypto in the Pro Challenge).\n\nLeverage varies by challenge type and asset. Forex is capped at 1:50 on Double Helix and 1:30 on Single Helix and Pro Challenge. Commodities and indices are fixed at 1:10, stocks at 1:5 following a recent reduction from 1:10, and crypto is 1:2 but only available on Single and Double Helix.\n\n| Asset Class | Single Helix | Double Helix | Pro Challenge |\n|------------|-------------|-------------|--------------|\n| **Forex** | 1:30 | 1:50 | 1:30 |\n| **Commodities** | 1:10 | 1:10 | 1:10 |\n| **Indices** | 1:10 | 1:10 | 1:10 |\n| **Stocks** | 1:5 | 1:5 | 1:5 |\n| **Crypto** | 1:2 | 1:2 | Not Allowed |\n\n### Trading Platforms\n\nAll trading is done through **TradeLocker**, which comes fully integrated with TradingView. This setup is ideal for manual traders who want advanced charting, one-click execution, and a clean web-based interface. However, automated trading and EAs are not supported.\n\nDNA Funded keeps its trading rules simple and in line with broker-backed standards. All accounts follow daily and overall drawdown limits based on the challenge type, and a daily profit cap of 40% now applies. This means you can only count up to 40% of your payout target in one trading day, which helps support steady, consistent trading.\n\nAutomated trading and expert advisors (EAs) are not allowed. You can copy trades between your own accounts, but not from others. News trading is allowed, but you'll need to avoid opening or closing positions within 10 minutes of high-impact news. Weekend trading is also permitted.\n\n### Trust and Community\n\nDNA Funded is backed by DNA Markets, a well-known ASIC-regulated broker (AFSL 514425), ensuring tight spreads and reliable execution. While DNA Funded is still new, its connection to DNA Markets boosts its credibility hugely.\n\nThe prop firm is also developing an active trading community through its Discord channel, offering a space for traders to connect and share insights.\n\n### Our Verdict on DNA Funded\n\nDNA Funded is the best prop trading firm for 2026 even in the early stages of launch thanks to its flexible challenges, low fees, and an 80% – 90% profit share. Backed by DNA Markets, it provides reliable market access across forex, commodities, indices, stocks, and crypto. You can read our full evaluation on our [DNA Funded review](/reviews/dna-funded) page.\n\nWith a user-friendly platform like TradeLocker and growing community support, DNA Funded is the best prop firm for both new and experienced traders looking for a new challenge to become a funded trader.\n\n---\n\n## 2. BrightFunded — Profit Share Scales to 100%\n\nBrightFunded earned our #2 spot with a score of 95/100, thanks to its industry-leading profit share that scales up to 100%, a well-structured two-step evaluation, and access to three top trading platforms. Based in the Netherlands, BrightFunded stands out for its transparent rules, wide market coverage, and a scaling plan with no cap — making it an excellent choice for Australian traders looking to grow their funded accounts over time.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/brightfunded-logo.png\" alt=\"BrightFunded logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">BrightFunded\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Profit Share Scales to 100%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">100%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.7 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/brightfunded\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://brightfunded.com?affiliateId=rsBbtrzYQSyr3RcHYHQT5w\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\" />\u003C/svg>\n    Visit BrightFunded\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Profit share scales up to 100%\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Wide market access with forex, indices, crypto\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Unlimited scaling plan with no cap\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>No MT4 platform available\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>No instant funding option\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Minimal educational resources\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n### More About BrightFunded\n\nBrightFunded scored 95/100 in our review for its strong combination of high payouts, flexible rules, and multiple platform choices. What sets it apart is the profit share that starts at 80% and scales all the way to 100% through their loyalty program — one of the highest in the industry.\n\nThe firm runs a two-step evaluation with an 8% profit target in Phase 1 and 5% in Phase 2. The daily drawdown is capped at 5% and the maximum drawdown at 10%, with a minimum of 5 trading days required per phase. There are no maximum time limits, so you can trade at your own pace.\n\n### Challenge Fees and Account Sizes\n\nBrightFunded offers account sizes from $5,000 to $200,000, all through their two-phase evaluation:\n\n| Account Size | Challenge Fee | Phase 1 Target | Phase 2 Target | Daily DD | Max DD |\n|-------------|--------------|----------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| **$5,000** | $55 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n| **$10,000** | $95 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n| **$25,000** | $195 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n| **$50,000** | $295 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n| **$100,000** | $495 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n| **$200,000** | $975 | 8% | 5% | 5% | 10% |\n\nAll challenge fees are refundable with the 100% Refund add-on (10% surcharge). BrightFunded also offers optional add-ons like bi-weekly or weekly payouts to customise your experience.\n\n### Markets and Leverage\n\nBrightFunded provides access to forex, indices, commodities, and crypto markets. Leverage varies by asset class:\n\n| Asset Class | Leverage |\n|------------|---------|\n| **Forex** | Up to 1:100 |\n| **Indices** | Up to 1:20 |\n| **Commodities** | Up to 1:20 |\n| **Crypto** | Up to 1:5 |\n\nThe higher forex leverage at 1:100 is a notable advantage over many competitors, giving traders more flexibility to manage positions across currency pairs.\n\n### Trading Platforms\n\nBrightFunded supports three industry-leading platforms, catering to a range of trading styles:\n\n- **MT5 (MetaTrader 5):** The industry standard with expert advisor support, multi-asset capabilities, and advanced order types. Ideal for traders who rely on automated strategies.\n- **cTrader:** Known for its clean interface, fast execution, and advanced charting. A favourite among manual traders and scalpers for its depth of market data and intuitive layout.\n- **DXTrade:** A web-based platform offering TradingView-style charting with a simple, modern interface. Great for traders who prefer browser-based access without installing software.\n\n### Trading Rules\n\nNews trading is unrestricted during the evaluation phase, with a 10-minute window restriction on funded accounts during major events. Weekend holding is allowed, and hedging is permitted within a single account. Expert advisors are supported on MT5. Copy trading from external sources is not allowed.\n\n### Trust and Community\n\nBrightFunded holds a **4.7/5 on Trustpilot**, reflecting strong trader satisfaction. The firm has built an active community of over 16,000 members on Discord, providing a space for traders to share strategies, tips, and payout certificates. Customer support is available via live chat and email, with generally fast response times reported by users.\n\nBrightFunded regularly shares payout certificates from funded traders, adding transparency and credibility to their payout process.\n\n### Our Verdict on BrightFunded\n\nBrightFunded is a standout prop firm for Australian traders who want to maximise their earnings through a profit share that scales to 100%. With three solid platforms, competitive challenge fees, and an unlimited scaling plan, it offers excellent long-term growth potential. The two-step evaluation is straightforward with fair targets, and the high forex leverage at 1:100 gives traders more room to work with. You can read our full evaluation on our [BrightFunded review](/reviews/brightfunded) page.\n\nWhile there's no instant funding option and MT4 isn't available, BrightFunded makes up for it with strong payouts, a growing community, and reliable trading conditions.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Blueberry Funded — 1,100+ Financial Markets\n\nBlueberry Funded ranks as the 3rd best prop firm thanks to its range of challenges and accounts, low fees, and strong broker backing. You can choose between instant funding for immediate access to capital or structured evaluations through one and two step challenges. Across all account types and platforms, trading conditions stay transparent with raw spreads from 0.1 pips, profit splits up to 90%, and access to over 1,100 financial markets.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/blueberry-funded-logo.png\" alt=\"Blueberry Funded logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Blueberry Funded\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">1,100+ Financial Markets\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">3.8 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/blueberry-funded\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://blueberryfunded.com/?utm_source=affiliate&ref=1457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\" />\u003C/svg>\n    Visit Blueberry Funded\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Low challenge fees from $25\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Scaling up to $2 million\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>MT4, MT5, DXTrade, TradeLocker\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Limited educational resources\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Fewer payment options\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Higher spreads on some forex pairs\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n### More About Blueberry Funded\n\nBlueberry Funded is a prop trading firm that came in 3rd place in our rankings with a score of 93/100. This is because they've developed one of the most versatile setups among the top prop firms, giving you the choice between instant access and structured evaluation processes. Each challenge follows clear, rule-based conditions with defined drawdown limits and payout structures.\n\n### Prop Challenges and Accounts\n\nBlueberry Funded offers everything from instant accounts to two-step challenges:\n\n- **Instant Lite & Instant Elite:** No evaluation required. You trade funded capital immediately with fixed trailing drawdowns. Lite is tighter for short-term strategies, while Elite gives more room for longer trades.\n- **Rapid Challenge:** A single-phase evaluation designed for faster traders who want quick feedback and short timeframes.\n- **One Step Challenge:** A straightforward, single-phase model suited to confident traders who prefer a clear target and static drawdown.\n- **Two Step Challenge:** A traditional two-phase evaluation for those who prefer structure and gradual progression.\n- **Prime Challenge:** A slightly stricter version of the Two Step challenge, built for consistency-focused traders.\n\nThis great range of account options make Blueberry one of the few prop firms offering both instant funding and multiple evaluation processes, without overcomplicating the rules.\n\n### Markets and Leverage\n\nBlueberry Funded gives access to over 1,100 instruments across six asset classes, with conditions and leverage varying slightly by challenge type.\n\n| Asset Class | Details | Leverage |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| **Forex** | Available across all programs, spreads from 0.1 pips | Up to 1:50 (Elite/Two Step/Prime) · 1:30 (Lite/One Step/Rapid) |\n| **Indices** | 14 global markets incl. US30, NAS100, GER30 | 1:10 |\n| **Commodities** | 17 products incl. gold, silver, oil, natural gas | 1:10 |\n| **Crypto** | 52 pairs incl. BTC/USD, ETH/USD — 24/7 on MT5 & TradeLocker | 1:2 |\n| **Stocks** | 1,000+ US stock CFDs (Stock Challenge & Instant Elite) | 1:10 |\n| **Synthetics** | 12 volatility-based indices (Synthetic Challenge only) | 1:30 |\n\nThe market coverage is broad enough for diversified trading across forex, commodities, and equities, while maintaining sensible leverage that supports steady, controlled performance.\n\n### Trading Platforms\n\nBlueberry Funded offers four trading platforms:\n\n- **MetaTrader 4 (MT4):** Best for forex traders, with strong support for Expert Advisors (EAs) and advanced charting tools.\n- **MetaTrader 5 (MT5):** Offers additional features like Depth of Market (DOM) and multi-threaded backtesting for more advanced traders.\n- **DXTrade:** A browser-based platform, which, while flexible, lacks the advanced features of MT4 and MT5, making it less ideal for active traders.\n- **TradeLocker:** A newer platform known for its clean interface and user-friendly layout. It's accessible via web and mobile, and is especially useful for traders who want a modern, simplified trading experience without the heavier footprint of MT4/MT5.\n\n### Trust and Community\n\nBlueberry Funded's partnership with Blueberry Markets, a regulated Australian broker (ASIC AFSL 535887), provides confidence in its pricing and operational integrity. The firm is also a founding member of The Prop Association, a group promoting transparency and trader protection across the industry.\n\nIts growing Discord community now includes more than 30,000 members, offering daily updates, payout confirmations, and peer discussion for both new and funded traders.\n\nBlueberry has also begun publishing verified payout proofs, showing consistent payment reliability as the program continues to expand.\n\n### Our Verdict on Blueberry Funded\n\nBlueberry Funded scored 93/100 overall which came down to accessible pricing, professional trading conditions, and a clear selection of challenges for every experience level. Whether you want instant access to capital or prefer to earn funding through structured evaluations, the options are well balanced with fair trading rules.\n\nWith regulatory backing, strong platform coverage, and transparent costs, it's by far one of the most complete prop trading firms currently available.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FXIFY — Instant Funding Prop Firm\n\nFXIFY ranked 4th overall, but it holds 1st place on our instant funding prop firm list. You can start with up to $50,000 in capital instantly, scale to $4 million, and keep up to 90% of your profits. Prefer to go through an evaluation? FXIFY also offers One Step, Two Step, and Three Step challenges.\n\nBacked by FXPIG, FXIFY combines tight pricing, fast execution, and an active Discord community for added support.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/fxify-1-1-1-1.png\" alt=\"FXIFY logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">FXIFY\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Instant Funding Prop Firm\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp c