\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Allows Expert Advisors (EAs)\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Up to 95% profit split\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Strict daily loss limits\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Only 10 crypto markets\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>cTrader/Match-Trader cost $25\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"prop-firm-details-2\">Prop Firm Details\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>FundedNext provides access to 10 crypto markets including BTC/USD, ETH/USD, and XRP/USD. All crypto trades are commission-free with a fixed 2:1 leverage cap.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Traders can use EAs on MT4 and MT5, but automation is not supported on cTrader. This makes FundedNext a strong choice for crypto scalpers and algo traders using MetaTrader.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process-2\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>FundedNext offers three crypto-compatible challenges:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stellar One Step:\u003C/strong> 10% profit target, 3% daily / 6% overall loss. 15% profit share during the challenge, 95% when funded.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stellar Two Step:\u003C/strong> Two-phase model with 8% and 5% targets. Includes 15% profit share during the challenge and 95% when funded.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stellar Lite:\u003C/strong> Two-step option with lower entry fees and tighter rules. No profit share during the challenge, but 95% once funded.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>All models are time-unlimited and allow for challenge add-ons like no minimum trading days or extended loss limits.\u003C/p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003Ctable>\u003Cthead>\u003Ctr>\u003Cth>Feature\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Stellar (1-Step)\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Stellar (2-Step)\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Stellar Lite\u003C/th>\u003C/tr>\u003C/thead>\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Challenge Phases\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>1 Phase\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>2 Phases\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>2 Phases\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Account Sizes\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>6K - 200K\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>6K - 200K\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5K - 100K\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Audition Fees\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$65 - $1,099\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$59 - $999\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$32 - $399\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Leverage\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>30:1\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>100:1\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>100:1\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Commission\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$7\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Profit Target\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>8%, 5%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>8%, 4%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Maximum Daily Loss\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>3%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>4%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Maximum Overall Loss\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>6%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>8%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Time Limit\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>No Time Limit\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>No Time Limit\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>No Time Limit\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Challenge Phase Profit Share\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>15%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>15%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>N/A\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Funded Profit Split\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>95%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>95%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>95%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>Minimum Trading Days\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>2\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"payments-and-payouts-2\">Payments and Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Withdrawals are available every 14 days for most models, and every 21 days for Stellar Lite. You can withdraw via crypto, Deel, or bank transfer.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Minimum Payout:\u003C/strong> $20\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Crypto Payouts:\u003C/strong> Only option if under $50\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Evaluation Fee:\u003C/strong> Fully refunded after your first funded withdrawal, with an added 20% bonus using the PROPFIRMS code\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platforms-2\">Trading Platforms\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>You can trade crypto on FundedNext using:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>MT4 &#x26; MT5:\u003C/strong> EA support, free access\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>cTrader:\u003C/strong> Manual trading only, $25 platform fee, not available for accounts above $100K\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Match-Trader:\u003C/strong> Web-based with mobile access, $25 fee, also unavailable above $100K\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>TradingView is available via MT5 for advanced charting.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"support-and-trust-2\">Support and Trust\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>With a Trustpilot rating of 4.6/5 stars and an active community across Telegram and Discord, FundedNext maintains a strong reputation.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The prop firm’s strong educational resources, including webinars and a detailed dashboard, ensure traders have the support needed to succeed.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"final-verdict-2\">Final Verdict\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>FundedNext is a top choice for crypto traders seeking high profit splits, commission-free trading, and strong platform variety. With three challenge types, bi-weekly payouts, and a large active community, it strikes a great balance for both manual and algorithmic crypto trading.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"4-blueberry-funded--good-crypto-prop-firm-for-eas\">4. Blueberry Funded — Good Crypto Prop Firm for EAs\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Blueberry Funded is a strong option if you want EA-friendly crypto trading with 24/7 access and low fees starting from $32.50. With four challenge types and support for 52 crypto markets, you can choose between structured or rapid evaluations to match your trading pace.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Use promo code PROPFIRMS20 to get 20% off your challenge, so you can get started with lower upfront costs.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/blueberry-funded-logo.png\" alt=\"Blueberry Funded logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Blueberry Funded\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Good Crypto Prop Firm for EAs\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">3.8 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/blueberry-funded\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://blueberryfunded.com/?utm_source=affiliate&#x26;ref=1457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    Visit Blueberry Funded\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros &#x26; Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>52 cryptocurrency markets\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Commission free crypto trading\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Scaling up to $2 million\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Strict drawdown rules\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Limited payment options\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Minimal educational resources\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"prop-firm-details-3\">Prop Firm Details\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Blueberry Funded scored 93/100 during testing, and ranked in 4th place on our list of the best crypto prop firms. You can trade 52 crypto pairs, one of the best selections available, including BTC/USD, ETH/USD, SOL/USD, and XRP/USD. Leverage is capped at 1:2 for all challenge types. Crypto is commission-free, and spreads are competitive — EUR/USD averages 0.2 pips and BTC/USD remains tightly priced.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You can use Expert Advisors (EAs) on MT4 and MT5, which is ideal for crypto algo traders. TradeLocker is also available for browser-based access, with stocks and crypto supported natively.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Their scaling model increases capital by 25% every 3 months, with a maximum simulated allocation of $2 million.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process-3\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Blueberry Funded offers four challenge types suited to different strategies:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>One Step Challenge:\u003C/strong> 10% profit target, 6% drawdown, no time limit.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Two Step Challenge:\u003C/strong> 10% and 5% targets across two phases, with 10% drawdown and 1:50 leverage.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Rapid Challenge:\u003C/strong> 5% target within 7 days, 3% daily and 4% total trailing drawdown.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stock Challenge:\u003C/strong> 10% and 6% targets with stricter drawdown and trading hour limits (crypto not included here).\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>All challenges provide 80% profit splits initially, upgradeable to 90%.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"payments-and-payouts-3\">Payments and Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>You can pay for challenges via credit card or cryptocurrency, with fees ranging from $32.50 to $1,100 depending on account size and model.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Profit payouts are processed every 14 days via RiseWorks, with a minimum withdrawal of $100. Payouts are available in USDC or USDT, and crypto accounts are treated the same as forex in terms of rules and withdrawal eligibility.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platforms-3\">Trading Platforms\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Blueberry Funded supports four platforms:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>MetaTrader 4 (MT4):\u003C/strong> EA support, advanced charting, great for scalping bots.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>MetaTrader 5 (MT5):\u003C/strong> Access to stocks + crypto, DOM, more indicators.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>DXTrade:\u003C/strong> Basic, browser-based, fewer tools.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>TradeLocker:\u003C/strong> Clean UI, mobile support, stocks and crypto enabled.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>For crypto traders, MT5 and TradeLocker offer the best blend of automation, usability, and market access.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"support-and-trust-3\">Support and Trust\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Support is available 24/5 via live chat and email, with a helpful Discord community of over 27,000 members. Blueberry Funded is backed by Blueberry Markets, an ASIC-regulated broker, and became a founding member of The Prop Association in 2025.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The firm currently holds a TrustPilot rating of 4.1/5, and offers consistent payouts and transparent rules, though some traders cite strict news trading restrictions as a downside.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"final-verdict-3\">Final Verdict\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Blueberry Funded is one of the top crypto prop firms for EA users, offering commission-free access to 50+ pairs and 24/7 trading. With four challenge types, low fees, platform variety, and strong scaling potential, it’s a well-rounded choice for both manual and automated crypto traders.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"5-funded-prime--meme-coins-and-crypto-markets\">5. Funded Prime — Meme Coins and Crypto Markets\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>If you want crypto plus something a bit different, Funded Prime is worth a look. You get standard crypto pairs in the regular one and two step challenges, and a separate Meme Coin Challenge where tokens like PEPE, WIF, and TRUMP run at 10:1 leverage with no exchange or wallet setup. Pricing tracks Eightcap Challenges’ live feed (a top forex broker). EAs are allowed on all challenges and payouts are fast, so you can test both systematic and discretionary ideas without juggling prop firms.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You can drop your upfront fees by 25% by using the promo code PROPFIRMS25.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/fundedprime-logo.png\" alt=\"Funded Prime logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Funded Prime\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Meme Coins and Crypto Markets\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">— \u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cspan class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-slate-300 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 cursor-not-allowed whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/span>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"http://fundedprime.com/?linkId=lp_213737&#x26;sourceId=bestpropfirms&#x26;tenantId=fundedprime\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    Visit Funded Prime\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">25% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS25\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros &#x26; Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Meme Coin Challenge 10:1 leverage\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Broker backed pricing via Eightcap Challenges\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>EAs allowed on both platforms\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Standard crypto capped at 1:1\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>No MT4 or MT5\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>No live chat support\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"prop-firm-details-4\">Prop Firm Details\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Funded Prime scored 80/100 thanks to keeping things simple with account sizes between $5K and $200K and fees from $35 to $1,235. The base profit split is 80%, and you can bump this up to 90% with the Profit Booster add-on. There’s also an option to speed up your first payout with the Early Payout add-on.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process-4\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>You can choose from four evaluation models depending on what you want to trade.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>One Step:\u003C/strong> Single evaluation with 5% daily and 10% overall loss limits.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Two Step:\u003C/strong> Same limits as One Step, but split across two phases. Funded accounts on this model qualify for weekly payouts.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stock Challenge:\u003C/strong> A one step model restricted to equities, with 1:5 leverage.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Meme Coin Challenge:\u003C/strong> Built for higher-volatility trading, with 10:1 leverage on tokens like PEPE and TRUMP, no daily loss cap, and a 5% trailing drawdown. It’s the only model where weekend trading is allowed.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>A few extra rules matter for crypto traders. Standard crypto pairs like BTC and ETH are capped at 1:1 leverage, which feels restrictive compared to other firms. If you want more flexibility, the Meme Coin Challenge is where you’ll find it, since leverage jumps to 10:1.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>News trading is only open on Two Step accounts, while elsewhere you’ll need to respect a 10 minute buffer around announcements.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"payments-and-payouts-4\">Payments and Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Withdrawals are straightforward once you’ve cleared KYC. The minimum withdrawal is $100, and approved requests are usually processed in one to two days. The first payout comes after 14 days on One Step, Stock, and Meme Coin accounts, but it’s cut to 7 days on the Two Step.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Daily profit caps are in place — 30% of a payout cycle’s total, or 40% for meme coin accounts — so you’re pushed toward consistency instead of banking everything on a single spike.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platforms-4\">Trading Platforms\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>You’ll be trading on either DXTrade or TradeLocker, both of which allow Expert Advisors and automation.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>DXTrade:\u003C/strong> Available on One Step and Two Step challenges. It’s stable, lightweight, and fits well if you run algorithmic setups.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>TradeLocker:\u003C/strong> Available across all challenges, including crypto and meme coins. It integrates directly with TradingView, making it easier to handle technical analysis and execute trades from your charts.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"support-and-trust-4\">Support and Trust\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Support is still basic, offered through a ticket system and a searchable FAQ. There’s no live chat yet, but responses are generally quick. Funded Prime launched in 2023 and uses pricing from Eightcap Challenges, so even though trading is simulated, spreads and execution track closely with live conditions.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Its Discord and X communities are active and growing, and payouts during our testing came through quickly.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"final-verdict-4\">Final Verdict\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>For crypto, Funded Prime’s edge is the Meme Coin Challenge and EA-friendly platforms. Standard crypto leverage is conservative at 1:1, but the 10:1 meme model and quick payouts make it a good fit if you want a focused crypto lane and a sandbox for higher-volatility tokens — without leaving a broker-backed environment.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"how-to-compare-crypto-prop-trading-firms\">How To Compare Crypto Prop Trading Firms\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>At Best Prop Firms, we use a data driven approach to shortlist proprietary trading firms, focusing on the factors that matter most to traders. Our methodology covers a wide range of criteria to ensure accurate and unbiased recommendations:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Challenge Structures:\u003C/strong> We assess the flexibility and fairness of evaluation processes, including profit targets, drawdown limits, and the variety of funding options available.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Trading Costs:\u003C/strong> Spreads, commissions, and other fees are compared to identify firms offering competitive trading conditions.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Market Access and Platforms:\u003C/strong> Firms are rated based on the financial instruments they offer, forex, crypto, indices, and more, and the quality of platforms like MT4, MT5, or TradingView.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Profit Payouts and Payments:\u003C/strong> We prioritise firms with frequent and flexible payout schedules, higher profit splits, and reasonable withdrawal policies.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Reputation, Trust, and Support:\u003C/strong> Trust scores, customer reviews, and the availability of reliable support are key factors in our evaluations.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>This standardized process of reviewing prop firms ensures traders find firms that suit their trading strategies, experience, and goals.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"risk-management-for-prop-traders\">Risk Management for Prop Traders\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Risk management is essential for successful proprietary trading, especially in volatile markets like cryptocurrencies. Key tools for risk management include stop-loss orders to limit potential losses and take-profit orders to lock in gains when targets are reached. These tools help remove emotion from trading decisions and ensure a disciplined approach to exits.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Position sizing is equally important. A common strategy is risking no more than 1–2% of your account balance on a single trade. This keeps losses manageable and supports long-term profitability. For cryptocurrencies, where volatility is higher, keeping position sizes smaller and using lower leverage is a good way to mitigate risk. Leverage amplifies both potential profits and losses, so you should use it carefully. Many prop firms cap leverage for crypto trading at 1:2, providing moderate exposure while limiting risk.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The risk-to-reward ratio is another fundamental aspect of risk management. Targeting a ratio of at least 1:2, where the potential profit is double the risk, allows traders to remain profitable even with lower win rates. Coupling this with diversified trades across different instruments further spreads risk. Lastly, adherence to a well-defined trading plan is crucial. This plan should outline entry and exit points, risk limits, and strategies for different market conditions. Avoiding emotional reactions, such as revenge trading, and sticking to your plan will improve consistency and results.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"faqs\">FAQs\u003C/h2>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"whats-the-best-crypto-prop-firm\">What’s the best crypto prop firm?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The best cryptocurrency proprietary trading firm is BrightFunded, offering 5:1 leverage and over 40 crypto pairs to trade during the evaluation process, as well as with a live funded account. The prop firm is also ranked second in the prop firm list for 2026 thanks to its well rounded offering with profit splits up to 100% and a unique loyalty program.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>While DNA Funded is the best prop firm in terms of execution and flexibility, firms like DNA Funded and Blueberry Funded also provide solid options for experienced crypto traders.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"what-is-a-crypto-proprietary-trading-firm\">What is a crypto proprietary trading firm?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>A crypto proprietary trading firm funds traders to trade cryptocurrencies using the firm’s capital, allowing traders to keep a share of the profits. These prop firms offer evaluation challenges to assess your trading skills before being granted funded trader status, or instant funding programs for more experienced traders. You can trade a range of markets during challenges such as Bitcoin and Ethereum traded as CFDs, spot assets, or futures.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"which-prop-firms-allow-crypto-trading\">Which prop firms allow crypto trading?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Many prop firms allow crypto trading, including BrightFunded, DNA Funded, Blueberry Funded, FundedNext, FTMO, Funded Trading Plus, City Traders Imperium and others. These prop trading firms offer access to major cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin (BTC) and Ethereum (ETH), as well as a few providing access to more unique digital coins. Many prop firms also offer commission-free trading for crypto markets, and leverage up to 1:2.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"can-you-trade-crypto-on-ftmo\">Can you trade crypto on FTMO?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Yes, you can trade cryptocurrencies on FTMO, but the selection is limited to 10 pairs, such as BTC/USD and ETH/USD. The firm offers capped leverage at 1:1 for standard accounts and 1:3.3 for Swing accounts, making it less flexible compared to competitors. While FTMO’s structured evaluation process and scaling plan to $2 million are appealing, other firms, like DNA Funded or Blueberry Funded, provide a broader range of crypto trading options and more competitive features.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"what-are-the-top-rated-crypto-prop-trading-firms-for-experienced-traders\">What are the top-rated crypto prop trading firms for experienced traders?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Experienced traders should opt for prop firms like DNA Funded, Blueberry Funded, and FundedNext for crypto trading. DNA Funded is considered the best prop firm overall with a competitive 90% profit splits and crypto-focused challenges, while Blueberry Funded and FundedNext both offer high profit splits and automated trading features.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>More experienced CFD traders may also be interested in the best instant funding prop firms, which allow you to skip the evaluation process altogether and fast track to funded trader status.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"what-are-the-best-crypto-prop-trading-firms-for-beginner-traders\">What are the best crypto prop trading firms for beginner traders?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Crypto prop trading isn’t ideal for beginners due to the complexity, high-risk, and volatility of cryptocurrency markets. If you are new to online trading, you should approach it cautiously and develop your trading experience first through demo accounts. For those determined to start, BrightFunded offers account sizes starting at $10,000 with a straightforward 2-step challenge and manageable profit targets.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"which-prop-firm-is-the-most-trusted\">Which prop firm is the most trusted?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>DNA Funded is the most trusted prop firm, earning a top score of 97/100 in our evaluations. Partnered with DNA Markets, an ASIC-regulated broker, it provides institutional-grade trading conditions, spreads starting at 0 pips, and transparent policies. Its flexible challenges, customizable payouts up to 90%, and reliable trading platforms like TradeLocker enhance trustworthiness.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>As the best broker backed prop firm, DNA Funded ensures secure and transparent trading, setting it apart in the prop trading industry.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"what-is-the-best-prop-firm-to-trade-futures\">What is the best prop firm to trade futures?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The best futures prop firm is Topstep, which scored 89/100 in our analysis. Topstep provides a flexible three-step evaluation process, allowing traders to progress at their own pace without time limits. With a 100% profit split on the first $10,000 and 90% thereafter, Topstep offers competitive payouts. Its platform options, including NinjaTrader and commission-free TopstepX, cater to diverse trading styles, making it ideal for futures traders at all levels.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"about-propfirms\">About PropFirms\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>PropFirms is dedicated to helping traders find the best proprietary trading firms to suit their needs. Our team of researchers evaluates prop firms based on critical factors such as account options, trading platforms, profit splits, and evaluation processes.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>By providing transparent, data-driven comparisons, we aim to simplify the decision-making process for traders of all experience levels. Whether you’re exploring instant funding options or multi-step challenges, our detailed prop firm reviews ensure you have the insights to make informed choices.\u003C/p>",{"headings":5204,"localImagePaths":5318,"remoteImagePaths":5319,"frontmatter":5320,"imagePaths":5333},[5205,5208,5211,5214,5217,5220,5223,5226,5227,5230,5231,5234,5236,5238,5240,5241,5243,5244,5247,5249,5251,5253,5254,5256,5257,5260,5262,5264,5266,5267,5269,5270,5273,5275,5277,5279,5281,5283,5284,5287,5290,5291,5294,5297,5300,5303,5306,5309,5312,5315],{"depth":879,"slug":5206,"text":5207},"what-are-the-best-prop-firms-for-crypto-trading","What Are The Best Prop Firms For Crypto Trading?",{"depth":879,"slug":5209,"text":5210},"crypto-prop-firm-comparison-table","Crypto Prop Firm Comparison Table",{"depth":879,"slug":5212,"text":5213},"the-5-best-crypto-prop-firms-we-tested-in-2026","The 5 Best Crypto Prop Firms We Tested in 2026",{"depth":879,"slug":5215,"text":5216},"1-brightfunded--best-crypto-prop-trading-firm-overall","1. BrightFunded — Best Crypto Prop Trading Firm Overall",{"depth":158,"slug":5218,"text":5219},"prop-firm-details","Prop Firm Details",{"depth":158,"slug":5221,"text":5222},"evaluation-process","Evaluation Process",{"depth":158,"slug":5224,"text":5225},"payments-and-payouts","Payments and Payouts",{"depth":158,"slug":4844,"text":4845},{"depth":158,"slug":5228,"text":5229},"support-and-trust","Support and Trust",{"depth":158,"slug":5051,"text":5052},{"depth":879,"slug":5232,"text":5233},"2-dna-funded--top-broker-backed-crypto-prop-firm","2. DNA Funded — Top Broker Backed Crypto Prop Firm",{"depth":158,"slug":5235,"text":5219},"prop-firm-details-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5237,"text":5222},"evaluation-process-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5239,"text":5225},"payments-and-payouts-1",{"depth":158,"slug":4864,"text":4845},{"depth":158,"slug":5242,"text":5229},"support-and-trust-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5068,"text":5052},{"depth":879,"slug":5245,"text":5246},"3-fundednext--crypto-prop-firm-with-high-profit-split","3. FundedNext — Crypto Prop Firm with High Profit Split",{"depth":158,"slug":5248,"text":5219},"prop-firm-details-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5250,"text":5222},"evaluation-process-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5252,"text":5225},"payments-and-payouts-2",{"depth":158,"slug":4884,"text":4845},{"depth":158,"slug":5255,"text":5229},"support-and-trust-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5083,"text":5052},{"depth":879,"slug":5258,"text":5259},"4-blueberry-funded--good-crypto-prop-firm-for-eas","4. Blueberry Funded — Good Crypto Prop Firm for EAs",{"depth":158,"slug":5261,"text":5219},"prop-firm-details-3",{"depth":158,"slug":5263,"text":5222},"evaluation-process-3",{"depth":158,"slug":5265,"text":5225},"payments-and-payouts-3",{"depth":158,"slug":4916,"text":4845},{"depth":158,"slug":5268,"text":5229},"support-and-trust-3",{"depth":158,"slug":5098,"text":5052},{"depth":879,"slug":5271,"text":5272},"5-funded-prime--meme-coins-and-crypto-markets","5. Funded Prime — Meme Coins and Crypto Markets",{"depth":158,"slug":5274,"text":5219},"prop-firm-details-4",{"depth":158,"slug":5276,"text":5222},"evaluation-process-4",{"depth":158,"slug":5278,"text":5225},"payments-and-payouts-4",{"depth":158,"slug":5280,"text":4845},"trading-platforms-4",{"depth":158,"slug":5282,"text":5229},"support-and-trust-4",{"depth":158,"slug":5113,"text":5052},{"depth":879,"slug":5285,"text":5286},"how-to-compare-crypto-prop-trading-firms","How To Compare Crypto Prop Trading Firms",{"depth":879,"slug":5288,"text":5289},"risk-management-for-prop-traders","Risk Management for Prop Traders",{"depth":879,"slug":4935,"text":4936},{"depth":158,"slug":5292,"text":5293},"whats-the-best-crypto-prop-firm","What’s the best crypto prop firm?",{"depth":158,"slug":5295,"text":5296},"what-is-a-crypto-proprietary-trading-firm","What is a crypto proprietary trading firm?",{"depth":158,"slug":5298,"text":5299},"which-prop-firms-allow-crypto-trading","Which prop firms allow crypto trading?",{"depth":158,"slug":5301,"text":5302},"can-you-trade-crypto-on-ftmo","Can you trade crypto on FTMO?",{"depth":158,"slug":5304,"text":5305},"what-are-the-top-rated-crypto-prop-trading-firms-for-experienced-traders","What are the top-rated crypto prop trading firms for experienced traders?",{"depth":158,"slug":5307,"text":5308},"what-are-the-best-crypto-prop-trading-firms-for-beginner-traders","What are the best crypto prop trading firms for beginner traders?",{"depth":158,"slug":5310,"text":5311},"which-prop-firm-is-the-most-trusted","Which prop firm is the most trusted?",{"depth":158,"slug":5313,"text":5314},"what-is-the-best-prop-firm-to-trade-futures","What is the best prop firm to trade futures?",{"depth":879,"slug":5316,"text":5317},"about-propfirms","About PropFirms",[],[],{"title":5169,"excerpt":5170,"category":5171,"tags":5321,"author":4798,"authorImage":4799,"publishedAt":1273,"featured":110,"coverImage":5175,"readingTimeMinutes":5176,"youtubeVideoId":4800,"featuredFirms":5322},[207,5173,4796,5174],[5323,5324,5325,5326,5327,5328,5329,5330,5331,5332],{"slug":584,"descriptor":5179},{"slug":728,"descriptor":5181},{"slug":1392,"descriptor":5183},{"slug":332,"descriptor":5185},{"slug":1241,"descriptor":5187},{"slug":1002,"descriptor":5189},{"slug":1278,"descriptor":5191},{"slug":642,"descriptor":5193},{"slug":2380,"descriptor":5195},{"slug":244,"descriptor":5197},[],"crypto.md","etf",{"id":5335,"data":5337,"body":5352,"filePath":5353,"digest":5354,"rendered":5355,"legacyId":5441},{"title":5338,"excerpt":5339,"category":5171,"tags":5340,"author":4798,"authorImage":4799,"publishedAt":240,"featured":110,"readingTimeMinutes":5176,"youtubeVideoId":5344,"featuredFirms":5345},"Best Prop Firms for ETFs (Verified Testing 2026)","There are only three realistic options for ETF prop trading right now. Most prop firms don't offer proper access to exchange traded funds, and many only provide index CFDs instead. We tested and compared the best prop firms for ETFs based on symbol range, platforms, fees, and funded account rules.",[5341,5173,4796,5342,5343],"ETFs","exchange traded funds","ETF trading","oIPQPwGXGac",[5346,5348,5350],{"slug":932,"descriptor":5347},"Best ETF Prop Challenges",{"slug":2673,"descriptor":5349},"Biggest Range of ETFs",{"slug":2442,"descriptor":5351},"Automated ETF Trading Strategies","## Who Are the Best Prop Firms for ETFs?\n\nThere are only three realistic options for ETF prop trading right now, with Eightcap Challenges, Trade the Pool and The Trading Pit. Most prop firms don't offer proper access to any exchange traded funds (ETFs), and many only provide index CFDs instead, so your choice is far narrower than it is prop trading forex, crypto or futures.\n\nOur shortlist of top prop firms to offer ETFs includes:\n\n1. **Eightcap Challenges** — Best ETF Prop Challenges\n2. **Trade the Pool** — Biggest Range of ETFs\n3. **The Trading Pit** — Automated ETF Trading Strategies\n\nIf you are looking to trade ETFs through a prop firm, your decision comes down to how many ETF symbols you need, which platform you prefer, and whether you want a traditional evaluation or a short-session challenge format.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Eightcap Challenges — Best ETF Prop Challenges\n\nEightcap Challenges scored 89/100 in our testing thanks to its combination of ETF access, trading platform options, and the range of evaluation options available. You can choose a one step challenge, a two step challenge, or a short-session Day Trader challenge that runs for 1 to 8 hours on a fixed $10k balance. Each format suits a different approach, whether you trade broad ETFs like SPY and QQQ, focus on sector rotation, or use fast intraday signals.\n\nEightcap Challenges is a regulated broker that also offers trading challenges under the same brand, which is different from most proprietary trading firms that run their funding programs separately from their brokerage operations. For ETF traders, this matters because the challenges use the same data, spreads and execution environment as Eightcap Challenges' live brokerage. You're trading ETFs, indices and other asset classes on a setup that already handles these markets daily, so the pricing and behaviour feel familiar and consistent.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/eightcap-logo-1.png\" alt=\"Eightcap Challenges logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Eightcap Challenges\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Best ETF Prop Challenges\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.0 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/eightcap\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://challenges.eightcap.com?campaign_id=1&ref_id=622\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\" />\u003C/svg>\n    Visit Eightcap Challenges\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Huge range of ETFs\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Short challenges 1-8 hours\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Clear trading rules\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Day Trader TradeLocker only\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Some ETFs not on MT5\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>No extended hours ETF trading\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\nEightcap Challenges scored 89/100 in our testing and is the strongest choice for ETF traders wanting a challenge and funded account with stable execution, a growing ETF list, and competitive fees. Unlike many prop firm setups, Eightcap Challenges sits on a broker-grade infrastructure, which means spreads, data, and fills tend to behave more consistently across ETFs, indices, forex and crypto. The challenge options cover both long-form evaluations and fast, single-session challenges, giving you more control over how you want to approach funding.\n\n### Evaluation Process\n\nEightcap Challenges offers three challenge types, a traditional one and two step challenge, plus a unique day trading challenge where you can pick a super short trading window between 1hr – 8hr.\n\n| Feature | One-Phase Day Trader | Two-Phase Day Trader | Fast Day Trader (1–8 Hour) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Account Size Range** | $10,000 – $200,000 | $10,000 – $200,000 | Fixed $10,000 simulated balance |\n| **Fee Range** | $119 – $1,299 | $99 – $1,199 | $5 – $250 |\n| **Evaluation Process** | One Step | Two Step | 1, 2, 4 or 8-hour |\n| **Profit Target** | 10% | 10% / 8% | Varies by stake & multiplier |\n| **Max Daily Loss** | 4% | 5% | Fixed dollar drawdown |\n| **Max Total Loss** | 8% | 10% | Fixed dollar limit based on chosen stake |\n| **Minimum Trading Days** | 5 | 3 per step | N/A |\n| **Profit Split** | 80% | 80% | Instant payout based on 2x, 5x or 10x multiplier |\n\n**One Step Challenge**\n\nIn the one step challenge, you choose an account size between $10,000 and $200,000 and trade until you either reach the 10% profit target or breach the 4% daily loss or 8% total loss. You only need a minimum of five trading days, and there's no second phase or extra review. Once you pass, you move straight into the payout stage with an 80% profit split.\n\nETF traders who run steady day-trading or short swing systems often choose this challenge because the rules are clear, the timeline is flexible, and the risk parameters don't force you to rush or oversize trades. It feels closer to a standard prop evaluation.\n\n**Two Step Challenge**\n\nThe two step evaluation process uses the same account sizes but splits the evaluation into two steps with a 10% target in Phase 1 and an 8% target in Phase 2. The drawdown is slightly wider at 5% daily and 10% total. Each phase requires at least three trading days.\n\nThis structure suits ETF traders who prefer a more traditional evaluation with more space for volatility, especially if they trade leveraged ETFs or fast-moving sector products. You still receive an 80% profit split after passing Phase 2.\n\n**Day Trader Challenge (1 to 8 Hours)**\n\nThe Day Trader challenges work differently from every other prop style model. They run on a fixed $10,000 balance, and you choose:\n\n- A time window: 1, 2, 4 or 8 hours\n- A stake: $5 to $250\n- A payout multiplier: 2x, 5x or 10x\n\nBased on your choices, the system sets a profit target and a fixed dollar drawdown. Your goal is to reach the target before the timer ends while staying inside the drawdown. If you meet the target, the payout is immediate, and you multiply your stake by the chosen factor.\n\nThis format suits ETF day-traders who focus on short volatility windows, market opens, news events or strong intraday trends on products like SPY, QQQ or sector ETFs. It's fast and high pressure, but it offers quick results and doesn't require a long evaluation period.\n\n### ETFs and Market Access\n\nEightcap Challenges offers one of the most complete ETF CFD ranges available through a challenge program, covering both US and Australian markets. The US list includes the major benchmarks most ETF traders rely on, such as SPY, QQQ, VOO, VTI and DIA, as well as a broad mix of sector ETFs, leveraged products and thematic funds. This gives traders access to the same tools used for intraday ETF momentum, volatility breakouts, and broader swing-based strategies.\n\nYou can trade:\n\n- **Index ETFs:** SPY, QQQ, IWM, VOO, VTI\n- **Sector ETFs:** XLK, XLF, XLE, XLY, XLP, XLU\n- **Leveraged ETFs:** TQQQ, SQQQ, SOXL, SOXS, LABU, LABD\n- **Commodity ETFs:** GLD, SLV, GDX, USO\n- **Bond ETFs:** TLT, HYG, LQD\n- **Thematic & growth ETFs:** ARKK, ARKG, PBW, BOTZ\n- **Australian ETFs:** ASX-listed funds covering index baskets, sustainability themes, property, and broad-market exposures\n\nThe depth of the ETF list also makes correlation-based trading straightforward. You can combine:\n\n- Index ETFs with sector ETFs for confirmation signals\n- Leveraged ETFs with their unleveraged equivalents for momentum setups\n- ETF pairs such as QQQ vs. SPY, XLF vs. XLK, IWM vs. VOO\n- ETF-FX blends, e.g., trading USD or JPY strength alongside gold or energy ETFs\n\nBecause the ETFs behave close to their underlying funds and follow normal US market liquidity patterns, we found our ETF signals transfer well from our retail charts to Eightcap Challenges' challenge accounts.\n\n### Trading Rules and Restrictions\n\nEightcap Challenges' rules are consistent across the challenge types, and the only things that change are the drawdown percentages and evaluation timelines. You can use any trading style including day trading, swing trading, news trading and algorithmic trading, and there's no unusual restrictions on holding times or trade frequency.\n\nMax leverage is 1:100 for all trading accounts which is on the higher side, but this is for forex and ETFs are limited to lower levels to reflect their risk. This encourages disciplined sizing while still giving enough flexibility in trading conditions for intraday ETF systems.\n\n### Trading Platform and Tools\n\nEightcap Challenges lets you pick between three popular and user friendly trading platforms – MetaTrader 4 (MT4), MetaTrader 5 (MT5), or TradeLocker, but it does depend on the challenge type. MT5 is the most suitable for ETF traders because it handles multi-asset layouts, custom indicators and more advanced trading tools, while MT4 remains available for traders with existing templates or systems. But, if you choose the Day Trader challenge, you'll be restricted to TradeLocker, which is designed for quick execution and simple session tracking.\n\nAll platforms offer smooth charting, stable execution and easy access to watchlists, which helps you follow several correlated ETFs at once.\n\n### Profit Payouts\n\nOnce you complete the one step or two step challenge, you get your first payout where you keep 80% of profits. Fast payouts can be expected with Eightcap Challenges, and scaling options allow you to work toward larger allocations over time.\n\nThe Day Trader challenges has a slightly different profit sharing agreement, where you receive your pay out instantly if you beat the target within your time window. This is separate from the normal funded path and is ideal for traders who want quick, session-based earnings rather than long-term accounts.\n\n### Trading Community and Support\n\nEightcap Challenges has a much stronger support and education presence than most prop trading firms. You get 24/7 customer support, detailed FAQs, a stack of educational resources, indepth trading platform tutorials and regular updates explaining new ETFs, markets and platform improvements. As an ETF trader, these updates will make it easy to keep track of new sector or thematic ETFs as they are added.\n\nYou can also expect a consistent and competitive trading experience. Eightcap Challenges has a strong reputation with a bunch of positive testimonials on Trustpilot, where they score 4.1 out of 5 stars from thousands of reviews.\n\n### Verdict on Eightcap Challenges\n\nEightcap Challenges is the best ETF prop challenge provider on our shortlist because it offers the widest mix of ETF markets, three top platforms, and three evaluation processes that cover both long-form and fast-paced trading. ETF traders can run almost any strategy, from short intraday bursts to multi-day rotations, without dealing with restrictive rules or small symbol lists. The ETF access, straightforward pricing and flexible challenge formats make Eightcap Challenges easily the most competitive ETF prop challenge available.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Trade the Pool — Biggest Range of ETFs\n\nTrade the Pool scored 70/100 in our testing and offers the broadest ETF list of any prop firm we reviewed. You can trade over 12,000 US stocks and ETFs, covering index funds, leveraged ETFs, sector products, commodities, bonds and international themes. This suits ETF traders who want direct access to a wide symbol list rather than a small CFD lineup.\n\nYou trade inside a stock-style environment with real-time data, pre-market and after-hours trading, and no PDT rule. The main trade-offs are the strict volume rules, consistency checks and relatively high profit targets, but the scale-up model and ETF depth give plenty of room for both active day traders and slower swing approaches.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/trade-the-pool-logo.png\" alt=\"Trade the Pool logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Trade the Pool\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Biggest Range of ETFs\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">70%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">7%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">From\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">12K+ ETFs\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/trade-the-pool\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Over 12,000 ETFs and stocks\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Real market data\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Scaling plan\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>One step challenge only\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Strict volume rules\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Lower profit split\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\nMost ETF traders using Trade the Pool treat it as a direct market access solution for stocks and ETFs, not as a classic CFD prop model. The platform lets you rotate through sectors, combine long ETFs with short single stocks, and use leveraged or inverse ETFs alongside core index products.\n\nThat flexibility is useful if you run basket strategies, sector rotation, or rule-based systems that need many symbols live at once. There is only one evaluation phase. You pass by hitting the profit target while following the rules, with no second-stage reset or fresh account required. Once funded, every 10% profit milestone increases both your buying power and your daily loss allowance, so your risk limits scale alongside your trading.\n\n### Evaluation Process\n\nTrade the Pool uses a single-phase evaluation but splits it into four programme types so you can pick something closer to your style: Day Trade Beginner, Day Trade Advanced, Swing Beginner, and Swing Advanced.\n\n- **Day Trade Beginner** is the simplest setup. You have unlimited time, a 6% profit target and a 4% max loss, with a relatively low minimum trade count. This suits ETF traders who day trade but prefer to build their stats slowly across many sessions without worrying about deadlines.\n- **Day Trade Advanced** keeps the same 6% target and 3% max loss but adds a 60-day limit and higher minimum positions. This version works better if you are already active in liquid ETFs such as SPY, QQQ, IWM, or sector ETFs, and are comfortable trading most days.\n- **Swing Beginner** is built around a 15% target and 7% max loss with unlimited time. It is designed for swing traders who hold ETFs overnight and across weekends, use wider stops, or build into positions in stages. This is often used by trend and rotation systems where trades can run for weeks.\n- **Swing Advanced** keeps the same 15% target and 7% max loss but adds a 100-day limit. It suits traders who still want space for multi-week moves but also like a defined evaluation window.\n\n| Trade the Pool Challenge | Day Trade Beginner | Day Trade Advanced | Swing Beginner | Swing Advanced |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Account Sizes** | $5,000 - $200,000 | $5,000 - $200,000 | $2,000 - $40,000 | $2,000 - $40,000 |\n| **Fee Range** | $59 - $1,475 | $47 - $1,100 | $87 - $1,240 | $69 - $800 |\n| **Profit Target** | 6% | 6% | 15% | 15% |\n| **Daily Pause** | 2% | 1% | 3% | 3% |\n| **Max Loss** | 4% | 3% | 7% | 7% |\n| **Minimum Positions** | 10 | 20 | 5 | 5 |\n| **Trading Period** | Unlimited | 60 days | Unlimited | 100 days |\n| **Profit Split** | 70% | 70% | 70% | 70% |\n\nAcross all four programmes, a few rules stay consistent:\n\n- Every profitable trade must move at least 10 cents.\n- Trades must be held for at least 30 seconds.\n- A consistency rule stops one large trade from generating most of the profit.\n\nYou also have to respect the stock/ETF volume rules, which cap the percentage of the previous one-minute volume you can trade. This means highly liquid ETFs are easier to scale into than smaller thematic or thinly traded products. Once you hit the profit target with valid trades, the account is checked for rule breaches and, if clean, you move straight to funded trading with the same conditions.\n\n### ETFs and Market Access\n\nTrade the Pool has the widest ETF access on this shortlist. You can trade more than 12,000 instruments, including:\n\n- Major index ETFs (SPY, QQQ, IWM, DIA, etc.)\n- Sector ETFs (XLF, XLE, XLK, XLU, XLY and others)\n- Leveraged and inverse ETFs (TQQQ, SQQQ, SOXL, SOXS, LABU, LABD, etc.)\n- Bond and fixed-income ETFs\n- Commodity and metals ETFs\n- International and regional ETFs\n- Thematic and volatility-linked funds\n\nFor ETF traders, this opens several options in one place:\n\n- Simple index-only systems using SPY, QQQ, IWM\n- Sector rotation using multiple SPDR or iShares sector ETFs\n- Leveraged ETF strategies that use smaller size but higher volatility\n- Long/short pairs such as sector vs index or ETF vs stock\n\nPre-market and after-hours access is important here, because many ETFs respond to futures movement outside the main session. You can adjust, scale, or hedge around key events while still working within the program's risk limits.\n\n### Trading Rules and Restrictions\n\nTrade the Pool applies the same core rules to ETFs and stocks. The key points ETF traders should focus on are:\n\n- **Volume rule:** You can only take a small portion of the previous one-minute volume, so you need to focus on ETFs with consistent liquidity.\n- **Halt and volatility rules:** You cannot trade a symbol while it is halted and must wait one minute after the halt is lifted. This matters for leveraged and thematic ETFs that move hard on news.\n- **8% move rule (funded):** If a symbol has moved 8% in four minutes, you cannot enter in the direction of that move in a funded account.\n- **Minimum move and time:** Every profitable trade needs at least 10 cents of movement and must be held long enough to count.\n\nThere is no PDT rule and you can use most normal trading styles: day trading, swing trading, position trading and rule-based systems. The rules are more about keeping activity realistic and preventing extreme size in thin names, which is relevant if you like small or niche ETFs.\n\n### Trading Platform and Tools\n\nAll trading is done through TraderEvolution, which is designed for stocks and ETFs. The desktop version is the best fit for serious ETF traders because it supports:\n\n- Multi-symbol watchlists and layouts\n- Fast order entry for baskets and rotations\n- Depth of market and tape-style information\n\nThe web and mobile versions help monitor positions, manage risk and exit trades when you are away from your desk, but most detailed planning is easier on the desktop platform. If you currently trade ETFs via a stock broker, the workflow will feel familiar.\n\n### Profit Payouts\n\nOnce you pass the evaluation and move to a funded account, you can request payouts every 14 days. You must close your positions before requesting a withdrawal and have at least the required minimum profit in the account.\n\nThere is also a risk buffer logic tied to your daily loss limit. As the account grows, your maximum drawdown can tighten back toward the initial starting balance. This means ETF swing traders need to plan around periods of higher volatility and think carefully about when to withdraw, so the account does not lose too much protection during rough patches.\n\n### Trading Community and Support\n\nTrade the Pool provides written guides, FAQs and program breakdowns that explain the rules, scaling process and risk model. There is also a stats and performance tracking area where you can review your trades and activity, but it's not as extensive as Eightcap Challenges Labs. Support is available via helpdesk channels, which is useful if you need clarification on volume rules or whether a specific ETF is tradable.\n\nIn terms of their reputation, the prop firm has a 4.4 out of 5 star TrustPilot score, indicating the majority of their traders are generally happy with their challenges and the lower profitability of a 70% split.\n\n### Verdict on Trade the Pool\n\nTrade the Pool is a good fit for ETF traders who care most about symbol choice and direct stock/ETF access. The single-phase evaluation, clear targets and scale-up model are straightforward, but the volume rules and higher targets require planning and patience, especially with leveraged products. If your strategy relies on a broad ETF universe, sector rotation, or building baskets across many names, Trade the Pool offers the kind of ETF coverage that is hard to match elsewhere.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Trading Pit — Automated ETF Trading Strategies\n\nThe Trading Pit scored 78/100 in our testing and sits at the more limited end of the ETF list on this page. There is only one ETF CFD available, TQQQ, plus a large set of index CFDs that many ETF traders use as proxies for major equity ETFs. The prop firm is better known for CFD and futures trading, being one of the first to offer both product types under one brand. Despite the limited ETFs, the rest of their product range is extensive and they still provide a decent trading environment.\n\nAutomated trading is allowed, weekly payouts are offered, and challenge fees start from $49. The single-ETF setup is the main drawback. The appeal comes from the platform choice, the ability to run EAs, and the option to mix ETF-style index exposure with other markets like forex, metals and crypto.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/the-trading-pit-logo.png\" alt=\"The Trading Pit logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">The Trading Pit\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Automated ETF Trading Strategies\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">80%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.2 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/the-trading-pit\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Automated trading allowed\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Good platform options\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Weekly payout option\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Low profit split\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Only one ETF\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Limited education\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\nMost ETF traders using The Trading Pit end up treating it as an index-focused environment, not a place to run broad ETF rotations. With TQQQ as the only ETF CFD, many systems shift toward US500, USTEC, DE40 and UK100 as stand-ins for SPY, QQQ or European index ETFs.\n\nThe experience then becomes about how the Prime and Classic challenges handle drawdown, profit targets and trading style. If you already trade indices on MT4, MT5 or cTrader, and just need one leveraged ETF plus index exposure, this structure can still work.\n\nChallenge fees start from $49 for smaller accounts and rise as you scale into larger Prime or Classic models. Both follow similar evaluation logic: fixed or trailing drawdowns, minimum trading days, and clear profit targets.\n\n### Evaluation Process\n\nThe Trading Pit offers three CFD challenge types that can be used for ETF trading strategies, a Classic, Prime One Step, or Prime Two Step. Fees range from around $49 into the four-figure range depending on account size and programme.\n\n- **Prime (One Step):** Prime accounts use a static max drawdown, meaning the limit stays in the same place and does not trail your equity. For ETF traders, this is the easiest structure to manage because fast moves and price gaps won't pull the drawdown tighter. You only need to hit one profit target before moving to a funded account.\n- **Prime (Two Step):** This version splits the evaluation into two smaller profit targets. ETF and index traders often prefer this if they trade gradually building systems, as you can pass with smaller, steady gains rather than hitting one larger target in a single phase.\n- **Classic (Trailing Drawdown):** Classic accounts use a trailing max drawdown, which moves upwards as your account grows. This keeps the challenge fee lower, but it is harder for ETF traders using volatile or leveraged products because any strong move against you reduces the buffer more quickly.\n\n| Challenge Type | ETF Trading Fit | Target | Drawdown | Min Days | Split | Fee Range |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Prime CFD One Step** | Straightforward swing setups | 10% | Static daily + static max | 5 | 80% | $49–$1,139 |\n| **Prime CFD Two Step** | Slower rotation strategies | 8% then 5% | Static daily + static max | 5/phase | 80% | $49–$1,139 |\n| **Classic CFD One Step** | Small-size ETF/index trading | 10% | Trailing max | 5 | 50–80% | $99–$999 |\n\nRegardless of the trading account you sign up to, the core rules of the challenge and funded accounts remain the same. You must stay within the daily and overall drawdown limits, place the required minimum trading days, and hit the profit target. If you meet all the trading goals, you advance to a funded account with similar conditions and a set payout split.\n\n### ETFs and Market Access\n\nThe Trading Pit only offers one ETF CFD: TQQQ, a triple-leveraged Nasdaq ETF. On its own, that is too narrow for most ETF rotation or portfolio strategies.\n\nTo work around that, traders typically use index CFDs as ETF substitutes, for example:\n\n- US500 as a SPY-style proxy\n- USTEC as a QQQ-style proxy\n- DE40 and UK100 as equivalents to European index ETFs\n\nThis covers a good portion of index-driven ETF strategies, especially if you rely on:\n\n- Breakout rules such as 20-day highs or lows\n- Volatility filters and ATR-based sizing\n- Trend-following rules on equity indices\n\nOutside indices and TQQQ, you also have forex, commodities, cryptocurrencies and individual equity CFDs. These can be used to hedge ETF-style index exposure or to run separate systems in parallel, but they do not replace a proper ETF list.\n\n### Trading Rules and Restrictions\n\nThe Trading Pit uses a consistent rule set across its CFD challenges, regardless of whether you focus on TQQQ, indices, forex or other markets.\n\n- Every account has a defined daily drawdown and maximum drawdown.\n- Prime challenges use a static max drawdown.\n- Classic challenges use a trailing max drawdown that follows your equity.\n- Minimum trading days apply, so you cannot pass with a single large trade.\n- News trading is allowed on Prime CFD challenges, so you can hold or open positions around macro releases, earnings-heavy sessions or key US events.\n- Automated trading is allowed on all CFD accounts, which is a plus for ETF and index traders running rules-based or EA-driven systems.\n- There is a 21-day inactivity rule, so slow strategies still need a reasonable flow of trades.\n- Scalping is allowed on Prime but not on Classic, where trades must be held longer than a minute.\n- Copy trading is not permitted on CFD accounts.\n\nOverall, the rules are clear but do not leave much room for oversized or poorly sized trades, especially when using leverage on Nasdaq products.\n\n### Trading Platform and Tools\n\nThe Trading Pit gives you the choice of MT4, MT5 and cTrader for CFD trading. All three platforms allow automated strategies, which is the main reason many systematic ETF and index traders look at this prop trading firm.\n\n- **MT5** is the most flexible if you track several indices and FX pairs at the same time. It supports more timeframes, more instruments and better multi-chart layouts.\n- **MT4** is fine for simpler systems or legacy EAs but can feel limited for complex filters.\n- **cTrader** is often chosen for its order execution and clearer depth-of-market view, which helps when trading during busy sessions on US indices or TQQQ.\n\nIf you later choose to use their futures offering, you can move to platforms like NinjaTrader, ATAS, Quantower, R|Trader Pro, Tradovate or TradingView. But for ETF-style and index CFD trading, most traders stay on MT5 or cTrader.\n\n### Profit Payouts\n\nOnce you reach the funded trader stage, profit payouts run on a regular cycle. Prime CFD accounts receive an 80% profit split every 14 days once funded. Classic CFD accounts start on a lower split of around 50 to 60% and can scale toward 80% as you move through internal funding levels.\n\nYou usually need at least $100 profit before requesting a withdrawal, and payouts are normally processed within a short window once approved. Payment options include cards, crypto and local methods depending on region.\n\nFor ETF and index traders, the key point is that once you are funded, you can build a steady withdrawal routine around the 14-day cycle.\n\n### Trading Community and Support\n\nThe Trading Pit offers standard help centre resources, FAQs and documentation explaining the rules, challenge types and platform setup. There is also customer support available via chat and email for account, platform or rules-related questions, and the prop firm has a decent reputation with a 4.4 out of 5 star TrustPilot score.\n\nYou won't find the same depth of ETF education you might see at a broker like Eightcap Challenges, but there is enough material to get started and clarify how TQQQ and index CFDs fit into the trading program.\n\n### Verdict on The Trading Pit\n\nThe Trading Pit is best viewed as an index-focused prop option with one leveraged ETF rather than a broad ETF environment. If you want to run automated or rules-based strategies on TQQQ and major indices using MT4, MT5 or cTrader, the firm can work well. If your ETF approach depends on sector rotation, multiple ETF pairs, or a long list of niche funds, the single-ETF limitation is likely to be too restrictive, and one of the other firms on this page will be a better fit.\n\n---\n\n## What Are ETFs and Why Do Traders Use Them?\n\nETFs are exchange traded funds that track a basket of stocks, sectors, bonds, commodities or themes. They trade like normal shares, but each ETF represents a full group of assets in one symbol. For traders, this makes them useful because you can take exposure to broad markets like the S&P 500, specific sectors like tech or banks, or higher-volatility products like leveraged ETFs, all without needing to trade dozens of individual stocks.\n\nETF behaviour is also predictable. Most follow their underlying futures markets, react cleanly to macro events, and move in steady volatility ranges. This makes them popular for intraday trading, breakout strategies, rotation systems and trend models.\n\nFor prop trading, ETFs sit between stocks and indices: they have strong liquidity, regular movement, and clear fundamentals, but without the extreme spikes seen in single stocks. The challenge is that only a few prop firms offer them, which is why ETF traders have fewer choices than forex or futures traders.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Management for ETF Trading\n\nETF prop trading requires tighter risk management than you might expect, because ETFs behave differently from forex pairs or crypto assets. They move in defined volatility ranges, react strongly to futures markets, and can gap overnight. At prop firms, these behaviours interact with fixed drawdown rules, minimum trade requirements and consistency checks, so your sizing and trade selection need to match the structure of the account.\n\n**1. Use liquidity as your base filter**\n\nMost prop firms limit your order size on thin products, so sticking to ETFs with strong volume (SPY, QQQ, IWM, major sector ETFs) helps you avoid slippage and rule breaks. Leveraged ETFs like TQQQ, SOXL or LABU move faster but still have strong liquidity in normal conditions, which keeps fills predictable.\n\n**2. Match position size to the ETF's volatility**\n\nETFs vary a lot in how they move. Mega-cap index ETFs barely spike intraday, while leveraged tech ETFs can move several percent in minutes. Using ATR or a volatility-based position size keeps you inside daily loss limits and helps prevent one bad entry wiping out the evaluation.\n\n**3. Plan for gaps and overnight risk**\n\nIf your prop firm allows overnight holds, you should expect gaps on any ETF tied to US equities, bonds or commodities. Swing traders should use smaller size and wider stops to keep total drawdown intact across multiple days. If your firm does not allow overnight holds, you need to manage exits around major earnings or macro events where ETFs can jump on open.\n\n**4. Use correlation to avoid oversized exposure**\n\nThree different ETFs that look like separate trades can still be the same risk. For example, holding SPY, QQQ and XLK is effectively a tech-heavy long bias. Prop firm evaluations do not adjust for correlation, so it's on you as the trader to reduce overlapping exposure. A simple rule is: avoid taking more than one position that reacts to the same index movement unless you intend to scale in.\n\n**5. Keep your trade distribution consistent**\n\nMost ETF prop firms have consistency rules that prevent one oversized trade from carrying the whole evaluation. Trading with a steady size and taking similar types of setups helps you avoid review issues when you hit the profit target. This is especially important with leveraged ETFs where the temptation to \"go big once\" is high.\n\n**6. Use simple stop logic that works across ETF types**\n\nA fixed percentage stop or an ATR-based stop usually works well across index, sector and leveraged ETFs. Keeping everything standard avoids mistakes during fast sessions. ETF traders who balance rules with volatility awareness tend to pass evaluations more naturally than those who treat ETFs like forex pairs.\n\n---\n\n## FAQs\n\n### How do ETF prop firms evaluate traders for funding?\n\nETF prop firms evaluate traders by checking whether they can reach the profit target without breaking the drawdown or trading rules. After that, firms review position sizing, trade frequency, holding times and the consistency of results. ETF traders also need to follow symbol-specific rules, especially on volume, leverage and minimum movement. Once all conditions are met, the account is approved and you receive your funded trading account.\n\n### Do prop trading firms really pay out?\n\nYes, the best prop trading firms with strong reputations do pay out, but only if you follow the rules, keep positions closed at payout time, and meet the profit minimums. ETF traders need to be aware of buffer rules, drawdown resets and payout cycles, as these can affect timing. Most firms pay through common methods such as bank transfer, crypto or payment processors. Choosing firms with clear, simple payout terms reduces the risk of delays or disputes.\n\n### What's the minimum trading day rule?\n\nThe minimum trading day rule sets the lowest number of days you must place at least one trade during the evaluation. This prevents traders from passing with a single oversized position. Most ETF prop firms use a requirement between 3 and 10 trading days depending on the challenge type. For ETF traders, it's easy to meet these days by spreading activity across liquid ETFs like SPY, QQQ or sector funds while keeping size modest.","src/content/blog/etf.md","7a2f7eead8ce106c",{"html":5356,"metadata":5357},"\u003Ch2 id=\"who-are-the-best-prop-firms-for-etfs\">Who Are the Best Prop Firms for ETFs?\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>There are only three realistic options for ETF prop trading right now, with Eightcap Challenges, Trade the Pool and The Trading Pit. Most prop firms don’t offer proper access to any exchange traded funds (ETFs), and many only provide index CFDs instead, so your choice is far narrower than it is prop trading forex, crypto or futures.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Our shortlist of top prop firms to offer ETFs includes:\u003C/p>\n\u003Col>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Eightcap Challenges\u003C/strong> — Best ETF Prop Challenges\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Trade the Pool\u003C/strong> — Biggest Range of ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>The Trading Pit\u003C/strong> — Automated ETF Trading Strategies\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ol>\n\u003Cp>If you are looking to trade ETFs through a prop firm, your decision comes down to how many ETF symbols you need, which platform you prefer, and whether you want a traditional evaluation or a short-session challenge format.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"1-eightcap-challenges--best-etf-prop-challenges\">1. Eightcap Challenges — Best ETF Prop Challenges\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges scored 89/100 in our testing thanks to its combination of ETF access, trading platform options, and the range of evaluation options available. You can choose a one step challenge, a two step challenge, or a short-session Day Trader challenge that runs for 1 to 8 hours on a fixed $10k balance. Each format suits a different approach, whether you trade broad ETFs like SPY and QQQ, focus on sector rotation, or use fast intraday signals.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges is a regulated broker that also offers trading challenges under the same brand, which is different from most proprietary trading firms that run their funding programs separately from their brokerage operations. For ETF traders, this matters because the challenges use the same data, spreads and execution environment as Eightcap Challenges’ live brokerage. You’re trading ETFs, indices and other asset classes on a setup that already handles these markets daily, so the pricing and behaviour feel familiar and consistent.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/eightcap-logo-1.png\" alt=\"Eightcap Challenges logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Eightcap Challenges\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Best ETF Prop Challenges\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.0 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/eightcap\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://challenges.eightcap.com?campaign_id=1&#x26;ref_id=622\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    Visit Eightcap Challenges\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros &#x26; Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Huge range of ETFs\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Short challenges 1-8 hours\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Clear trading rules\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Day Trader TradeLocker only\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Some ETFs not on MT5\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>No extended hours ETF trading\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges scored 89/100 in our testing and is the strongest choice for ETF traders wanting a challenge and funded account with stable execution, a growing ETF list, and competitive fees. Unlike many prop firm setups, Eightcap Challenges sits on a broker-grade infrastructure, which means spreads, data, and fills tend to behave more consistently across ETFs, indices, forex and crypto. The challenge options cover both long-form evaluations and fast, single-session challenges, giving you more control over how you want to approach funding.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges offers three challenge types, a traditional one and two step challenge, plus a unique day trading challenge where you can pick a super short trading window between 1hr – 8hr.\u003C/p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003Ctable>\u003Cthead>\u003Ctr>\u003Cth>Feature\u003C/th>\u003Cth>One-Phase Day Trader\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Two-Phase Day Trader\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Fast Day Trader (1–8 Hour)\u003C/th>\u003C/tr>\u003C/thead>\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Account Size Range\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$10,000 – $200,000\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$10,000 – $200,000\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Fixed $10,000 simulated balance\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Fee Range\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$119 – $1,299\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$99 – $1,199\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$5 – $250\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Evaluation Process\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>One Step\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Two Step\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>1, 2, 4 or 8-hour\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Profit Target\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10% / 8%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Varies by stake &#x26; multiplier\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Max Daily Loss\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>4%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Fixed dollar drawdown\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Max Total Loss\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>8%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Fixed dollar limit based on chosen stake\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Minimum Trading Days\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>3 per step\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>N/A\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Profit Split\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>80%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>80%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Instant payout based on 2x, 5x or 10x multiplier\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>One Step Challenge\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In the one step challenge, you choose an account size between $10,000 and $200,000 and trade until you either reach the 10% profit target or breach the 4% daily loss or 8% total loss. You only need a minimum of five trading days, and there’s no second phase or extra review. Once you pass, you move straight into the payout stage with an 80% profit split.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>ETF traders who run steady day-trading or short swing systems often choose this challenge because the rules are clear, the timeline is flexible, and the risk parameters don’t force you to rush or oversize trades. It feels closer to a standard prop evaluation.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Two Step Challenge\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The two step evaluation process uses the same account sizes but splits the evaluation into two steps with a 10% target in Phase 1 and an 8% target in Phase 2. The drawdown is slightly wider at 5% daily and 10% total. Each phase requires at least three trading days.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>This structure suits ETF traders who prefer a more traditional evaluation with more space for volatility, especially if they trade leveraged ETFs or fast-moving sector products. You still receive an 80% profit split after passing Phase 2.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Day Trader Challenge (1 to 8 Hours)\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The Day Trader challenges work differently from every other prop style model. They run on a fixed $10,000 balance, and you choose:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>A time window: 1, 2, 4 or 8 hours\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>A stake: $5 to $250\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>A payout multiplier: 2x, 5x or 10x\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Based on your choices, the system sets a profit target and a fixed dollar drawdown. Your goal is to reach the target before the timer ends while staying inside the drawdown. If you meet the target, the payout is immediate, and you multiply your stake by the chosen factor.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>This format suits ETF day-traders who focus on short volatility windows, market opens, news events or strong intraday trends on products like SPY, QQQ or sector ETFs. It’s fast and high pressure, but it offers quick results and doesn’t require a long evaluation period.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"etfs-and-market-access\">ETFs and Market Access\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges offers one of the most complete ETF CFD ranges available through a challenge program, covering both US and Australian markets. The US list includes the major benchmarks most ETF traders rely on, such as SPY, QQQ, VOO, VTI and DIA, as well as a broad mix of sector ETFs, leveraged products and thematic funds. This gives traders access to the same tools used for intraday ETF momentum, volatility breakouts, and broader swing-based strategies.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You can trade:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Index ETFs:\u003C/strong> SPY, QQQ, IWM, VOO, VTI\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Sector ETFs:\u003C/strong> XLK, XLF, XLE, XLY, XLP, XLU\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Leveraged ETFs:\u003C/strong> TQQQ, SQQQ, SOXL, SOXS, LABU, LABD\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Commodity ETFs:\u003C/strong> GLD, SLV, GDX, USO\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Bond ETFs:\u003C/strong> TLT, HYG, LQD\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Thematic &#x26; growth ETFs:\u003C/strong> ARKK, ARKG, PBW, BOTZ\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Australian ETFs:\u003C/strong> ASX-listed funds covering index baskets, sustainability themes, property, and broad-market exposures\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>The depth of the ETF list also makes correlation-based trading straightforward. You can combine:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Index ETFs with sector ETFs for confirmation signals\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Leveraged ETFs with their unleveraged equivalents for momentum setups\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>ETF pairs such as QQQ vs. SPY, XLF vs. XLK, IWM vs. VOO\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>ETF-FX blends, e.g., trading USD or JPY strength alongside gold or energy ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Because the ETFs behave close to their underlying funds and follow normal US market liquidity patterns, we found our ETF signals transfer well from our retail charts to Eightcap Challenges’ challenge accounts.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-rules-and-restrictions\">Trading Rules and Restrictions\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges’ rules are consistent across the challenge types, and the only things that change are the drawdown percentages and evaluation timelines. You can use any trading style including day trading, swing trading, news trading and algorithmic trading, and there’s no unusual restrictions on holding times or trade frequency.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Max leverage is 1:100 for all trading accounts which is on the higher side, but this is for forex and ETFs are limited to lower levels to reflect their risk. This encourages disciplined sizing while still giving enough flexibility in trading conditions for intraday ETF systems.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platform-and-tools\">Trading Platform and Tools\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges lets you pick between three popular and user friendly trading platforms – MetaTrader 4 (MT4), MetaTrader 5 (MT5), or TradeLocker, but it does depend on the challenge type. MT5 is the most suitable for ETF traders because it handles multi-asset layouts, custom indicators and more advanced trading tools, while MT4 remains available for traders with existing templates or systems. But, if you choose the Day Trader challenge, you’ll be restricted to TradeLocker, which is designed for quick execution and simple session tracking.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>All platforms offer smooth charting, stable execution and easy access to watchlists, which helps you follow several correlated ETFs at once.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"profit-payouts\">Profit Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Once you complete the one step or two step challenge, you get your first payout where you keep 80% of profits. Fast payouts can be expected with Eightcap Challenges, and scaling options allow you to work toward larger allocations over time.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The Day Trader challenges has a slightly different profit sharing agreement, where you receive your pay out instantly if you beat the target within your time window. This is separate from the normal funded path and is ideal for traders who want quick, session-based earnings rather than long-term accounts.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-community-and-support\">Trading Community and Support\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges has a much stronger support and education presence than most prop trading firms. You get 24/7 customer support, detailed FAQs, a stack of educational resources, indepth trading platform tutorials and regular updates explaining new ETFs, markets and platform improvements. As an ETF trader, these updates will make it easy to keep track of new sector or thematic ETFs as they are added.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You can also expect a consistent and competitive trading experience. Eightcap Challenges has a strong reputation with a bunch of positive testimonials on Trustpilot, where they score 4.1 out of 5 stars from thousands of reviews.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"verdict-on-eightcap-challenges\">Verdict on Eightcap Challenges\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Eightcap Challenges is the best ETF prop challenge provider on our shortlist because it offers the widest mix of ETF markets, three top platforms, and three evaluation processes that cover both long-form and fast-paced trading. ETF traders can run almost any strategy, from short intraday bursts to multi-day rotations, without dealing with restrictive rules or small symbol lists. The ETF access, straightforward pricing and flexible challenge formats make Eightcap Challenges easily the most competitive ETF prop challenge available.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"2-trade-the-pool--biggest-range-of-etfs\">2. Trade the Pool — Biggest Range of ETFs\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool scored 70/100 in our testing and offers the broadest ETF list of any prop firm we reviewed. You can trade over 12,000 US stocks and ETFs, covering index funds, leveraged ETFs, sector products, commodities, bonds and international themes. This suits ETF traders who want direct access to a wide symbol list rather than a small CFD lineup.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You trade inside a stock-style environment with real-time data, pre-market and after-hours trading, and no PDT rule. The main trade-offs are the strict volume rules, consistency checks and relatively high profit targets, but the scale-up model and ETF depth give plenty of room for both active day traders and slower swing approaches.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/trade-the-pool-logo.png\" alt=\"Trade the Pool logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Trade the Pool\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Biggest Range of ETFs\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">70%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">7%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">From\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">12K+ ETFs\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/trade-the-pool\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros &#x26; Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Over 12,000 ETFs and stocks\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Real market data\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Scaling plan\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>One step challenge only\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Strict volume rules\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Lower profit split\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>Most ETF traders using Trade the Pool treat it as a direct market access solution for stocks and ETFs, not as a classic CFD prop model. The platform lets you rotate through sectors, combine long ETFs with short single stocks, and use leveraged or inverse ETFs alongside core index products.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>That flexibility is useful if you run basket strategies, sector rotation, or rule-based systems that need many symbols live at once. There is only one evaluation phase. You pass by hitting the profit target while following the rules, with no second-stage reset or fresh account required. Once funded, every 10% profit milestone increases both your buying power and your daily loss allowance, so your risk limits scale alongside your trading.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process-1\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool uses a single-phase evaluation but splits it into four programme types so you can pick something closer to your style: Day Trade Beginner, Day Trade Advanced, Swing Beginner, and Swing Advanced.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Day Trade Beginner\u003C/strong> is the simplest setup. You have unlimited time, a 6% profit target and a 4% max loss, with a relatively low minimum trade count. This suits ETF traders who day trade but prefer to build their stats slowly across many sessions without worrying about deadlines.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Day Trade Advanced\u003C/strong> keeps the same 6% target and 3% max loss but adds a 60-day limit and higher minimum positions. This version works better if you are already active in liquid ETFs such as SPY, QQQ, IWM, or sector ETFs, and are comfortable trading most days.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Swing Beginner\u003C/strong> is built around a 15% target and 7% max loss with unlimited time. It is designed for swing traders who hold ETFs overnight and across weekends, use wider stops, or build into positions in stages. This is often used by trend and rotation systems where trades can run for weeks.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Swing Advanced\u003C/strong> keeps the same 15% target and 7% max loss but adds a 100-day limit. It suits traders who still want space for multi-week moves but also like a defined evaluation window.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003Ctable>\u003Cthead>\u003Ctr>\u003Cth>Trade the Pool Challenge\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Day Trade Beginner\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Day Trade Advanced\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Swing Beginner\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Swing Advanced\u003C/th>\u003C/tr>\u003C/thead>\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Account Sizes\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$5,000 - $200,000\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$5,000 - $200,000\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$2,000 - $40,000\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$2,000 - $40,000\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Fee Range\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$59 - $1,475\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$47 - $1,100\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$87 - $1,240\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$69 - $800\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Profit Target\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>6%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>6%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>15%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>15%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Daily Pause\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>2%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>1%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>3%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>3%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Max Loss\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>4%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>3%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>7%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>7%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Minimum Positions\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>20\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Trading Period\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Unlimited\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>60 days\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Unlimited\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>100 days\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Profit Split\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>70%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>70%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>70%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>70%\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Cp>Across all four programmes, a few rules stay consistent:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Every profitable trade must move at least 10 cents.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Trades must be held for at least 30 seconds.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>A consistency rule stops one large trade from generating most of the profit.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>You also have to respect the stock/ETF volume rules, which cap the percentage of the previous one-minute volume you can trade. This means highly liquid ETFs are easier to scale into than smaller thematic or thinly traded products. Once you hit the profit target with valid trades, the account is checked for rule breaches and, if clean, you move straight to funded trading with the same conditions.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"etfs-and-market-access-1\">ETFs and Market Access\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool has the widest ETF access on this shortlist. You can trade more than 12,000 instruments, including:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Major index ETFs (SPY, QQQ, IWM, DIA, etc.)\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Sector ETFs (XLF, XLE, XLK, XLU, XLY and others)\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Leveraged and inverse ETFs (TQQQ, SQQQ, SOXL, SOXS, LABU, LABD, etc.)\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Bond and fixed-income ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Commodity and metals ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>International and regional ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Thematic and volatility-linked funds\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>For ETF traders, this opens several options in one place:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Simple index-only systems using SPY, QQQ, IWM\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Sector rotation using multiple SPDR or iShares sector ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Leveraged ETF strategies that use smaller size but higher volatility\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Long/short pairs such as sector vs index or ETF vs stock\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Pre-market and after-hours access is important here, because many ETFs respond to futures movement outside the main session. You can adjust, scale, or hedge around key events while still working within the program’s risk limits.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-rules-and-restrictions-1\">Trading Rules and Restrictions\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool applies the same core rules to ETFs and stocks. The key points ETF traders should focus on are:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Volume rule:\u003C/strong> You can only take a small portion of the previous one-minute volume, so you need to focus on ETFs with consistent liquidity.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Halt and volatility rules:\u003C/strong> You cannot trade a symbol while it is halted and must wait one minute after the halt is lifted. This matters for leveraged and thematic ETFs that move hard on news.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>8% move rule (funded):\u003C/strong> If a symbol has moved 8% in four minutes, you cannot enter in the direction of that move in a funded account.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Minimum move and time:\u003C/strong> Every profitable trade needs at least 10 cents of movement and must be held long enough to count.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>There is no PDT rule and you can use most normal trading styles: day trading, swing trading, position trading and rule-based systems. The rules are more about keeping activity realistic and preventing extreme size in thin names, which is relevant if you like small or niche ETFs.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platform-and-tools-1\">Trading Platform and Tools\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>All trading is done through TraderEvolution, which is designed for stocks and ETFs. The desktop version is the best fit for serious ETF traders because it supports:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Multi-symbol watchlists and layouts\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Fast order entry for baskets and rotations\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Depth of market and tape-style information\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>The web and mobile versions help monitor positions, manage risk and exit trades when you are away from your desk, but most detailed planning is easier on the desktop platform. If you currently trade ETFs via a stock broker, the workflow will feel familiar.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"profit-payouts-1\">Profit Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Once you pass the evaluation and move to a funded account, you can request payouts every 14 days. You must close your positions before requesting a withdrawal and have at least the required minimum profit in the account.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>There is also a risk buffer logic tied to your daily loss limit. As the account grows, your maximum drawdown can tighten back toward the initial starting balance. This means ETF swing traders need to plan around periods of higher volatility and think carefully about when to withdraw, so the account does not lose too much protection during rough patches.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-community-and-support-1\">Trading Community and Support\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool provides written guides, FAQs and program breakdowns that explain the rules, scaling process and risk model. There is also a stats and performance tracking area where you can review your trades and activity, but it’s not as extensive as Eightcap Challenges Labs. Support is available via helpdesk channels, which is useful if you need clarification on volume rules or whether a specific ETF is tradable.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In terms of their reputation, the prop firm has a 4.4 out of 5 star TrustPilot score, indicating the majority of their traders are generally happy with their challenges and the lower profitability of a 70% split.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"verdict-on-trade-the-pool\">Verdict on Trade the Pool\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Trade the Pool is a good fit for ETF traders who care most about symbol choice and direct stock/ETF access. The single-phase evaluation, clear targets and scale-up model are straightforward, but the volume rules and higher targets require planning and patience, especially with leveraged products. If your strategy relies on a broad ETF universe, sector rotation, or building baskets across many names, Trade the Pool offers the kind of ETF coverage that is hard to match elsewhere.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"3-the-trading-pit--automated-etf-trading-strategies\">3. The Trading Pit — Automated ETF Trading Strategies\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit scored 78/100 in our testing and sits at the more limited end of the ETF list on this page. There is only one ETF CFD available, TQQQ, plus a large set of index CFDs that many ETF traders use as proxies for major equity ETFs. The prop firm is better known for CFD and futures trading, being one of the first to offer both product types under one brand. Despite the limited ETFs, the rest of their product range is extensive and they still provide a decent trading environment.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Automated trading is allowed, weekly payouts are offered, and challenge fees start from $49. The single-ETF setup is the main drawback. The appeal comes from the platform choice, the ability to run EAs, and the option to mix ETF-style index exposure with other markets like forex, metals and crypto.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/the-trading-pit-logo.png\" alt=\"The Trading Pit logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">The Trading Pit\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Automated ETF Trading Strategies\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">80%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.2 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/the-trading-pit\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros &#x26; Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Automated trading allowed\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Good platform options\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Weekly payout option\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Low profit split\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Only one ETF\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Limited education\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>Most ETF traders using The Trading Pit end up treating it as an index-focused environment, not a place to run broad ETF rotations. With TQQQ as the only ETF CFD, many systems shift toward US500, USTEC, DE40 and UK100 as stand-ins for SPY, QQQ or European index ETFs.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The experience then becomes about how the Prime and Classic challenges handle drawdown, profit targets and trading style. If you already trade indices on MT4, MT5 or cTrader, and just need one leveraged ETF plus index exposure, this structure can still work.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Challenge fees start from $49 for smaller accounts and rise as you scale into larger Prime or Classic models. Both follow similar evaluation logic: fixed or trailing drawdowns, minimum trading days, and clear profit targets.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"evaluation-process-2\">Evaluation Process\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit offers three CFD challenge types that can be used for ETF trading strategies, a Classic, Prime One Step, or Prime Two Step. Fees range from around $49 into the four-figure range depending on account size and programme.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Prime (One Step):\u003C/strong> Prime accounts use a static max drawdown, meaning the limit stays in the same place and does not trail your equity. For ETF traders, this is the easiest structure to manage because fast moves and price gaps won’t pull the drawdown tighter. You only need to hit one profit target before moving to a funded account.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Prime (Two Step):\u003C/strong> This version splits the evaluation into two smaller profit targets. ETF and index traders often prefer this if they trade gradually building systems, as you can pass with smaller, steady gains rather than hitting one larger target in a single phase.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Classic (Trailing Drawdown):\u003C/strong> Classic accounts use a trailing max drawdown, which moves upwards as your account grows. This keeps the challenge fee lower, but it is harder for ETF traders using volatile or leveraged products because any strong move against you reduces the buffer more quickly.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003Ctable>\u003Cthead>\u003Ctr>\u003Cth>Challenge Type\u003C/th>\u003Cth>ETF Trading Fit\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Target\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Drawdown\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Min Days\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Split\u003C/th>\u003Cth>Fee Range\u003C/th>\u003C/tr>\u003C/thead>\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Prime CFD One Step\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Straightforward swing setups\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Static daily + static max\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>80%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$49–$1,139\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Prime CFD Two Step\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Slower rotation strategies\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>8% then 5%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Static daily + static max\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5/phase\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>80%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$49–$1,139\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>\u003Cstrong>Classic CFD One Step\u003C/strong>\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Small-size ETF/index trading\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>10%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Trailing max\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>5\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>50–80%\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>$99–$999\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Cp>Regardless of the trading account you sign up to, the core rules of the challenge and funded accounts remain the same. You must stay within the daily and overall drawdown limits, place the required minimum trading days, and hit the profit target. If you meet all the trading goals, you advance to a funded account with similar conditions and a set payout split.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"etfs-and-market-access-2\">ETFs and Market Access\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit only offers one ETF CFD: TQQQ, a triple-leveraged Nasdaq ETF. On its own, that is too narrow for most ETF rotation or portfolio strategies.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>To work around that, traders typically use index CFDs as ETF substitutes, for example:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>US500 as a SPY-style proxy\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>USTEC as a QQQ-style proxy\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>DE40 and UK100 as equivalents to European index ETFs\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>This covers a good portion of index-driven ETF strategies, especially if you rely on:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Breakout rules such as 20-day highs or lows\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Volatility filters and ATR-based sizing\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Trend-following rules on equity indices\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Outside indices and TQQQ, you also have forex, commodities, cryptocurrencies and individual equity CFDs. These can be used to hedge ETF-style index exposure or to run separate systems in parallel, but they do not replace a proper ETF list.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-rules-and-restrictions-2\">Trading Rules and Restrictions\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit uses a consistent rule set across its CFD challenges, regardless of whether you focus on TQQQ, indices, forex or other markets.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>Every account has a defined daily drawdown and maximum drawdown.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Prime challenges use a static max drawdown.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Classic challenges use a trailing max drawdown that follows your equity.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Minimum trading days apply, so you cannot pass with a single large trade.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>News trading is allowed on Prime CFD challenges, so you can hold or open positions around macro releases, earnings-heavy sessions or key US events.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Automated trading is allowed on all CFD accounts, which is a plus for ETF and index traders running rules-based or EA-driven systems.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>There is a 21-day inactivity rule, so slow strategies still need a reasonable flow of trades.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Scalping is allowed on Prime but not on Classic, where trades must be held longer than a minute.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Copy trading is not permitted on CFD accounts.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Overall, the rules are clear but do not leave much room for oversized or poorly sized trades, especially when using leverage on Nasdaq products.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-platform-and-tools-2\">Trading Platform and Tools\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit gives you the choice of MT4, MT5 and cTrader for CFD trading. All three platforms allow automated strategies, which is the main reason many systematic ETF and index traders look at this prop trading firm.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>MT5\u003C/strong> is the most flexible if you track several indices and FX pairs at the same time. It supports more timeframes, more instruments and better multi-chart layouts.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>MT4\u003C/strong> is fine for simpler systems or legacy EAs but can feel limited for complex filters.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>cTrader\u003C/strong> is often chosen for its order execution and clearer depth-of-market view, which helps when trading during busy sessions on US indices or TQQQ.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>If you later choose to use their futures offering, you can move to platforms like NinjaTrader, ATAS, Quantower, R|Trader Pro, Tradovate or TradingView. But for ETF-style and index CFD trading, most traders stay on MT5 or cTrader.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"profit-payouts-2\">Profit Payouts\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Once you reach the funded trader stage, profit payouts run on a regular cycle. Prime CFD accounts receive an 80% profit split every 14 days once funded. Classic CFD accounts start on a lower split of around 50 to 60% and can scale toward 80% as you move through internal funding levels.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You usually need at least $100 profit before requesting a withdrawal, and payouts are normally processed within a short window once approved. Payment options include cards, crypto and local methods depending on region.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>For ETF and index traders, the key point is that once you are funded, you can build a steady withdrawal routine around the 14-day cycle.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"trading-community-and-support-2\">Trading Community and Support\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit offers standard help centre resources, FAQs and documentation explaining the rules, challenge types and platform setup. There is also customer support available via chat and email for account, platform or rules-related questions, and the prop firm has a decent reputation with a 4.4 out of 5 star TrustPilot score.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You won’t find the same depth of ETF education you might see at a broker like Eightcap Challenges, but there is enough material to get started and clarify how TQQQ and index CFDs fit into the trading program.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"verdict-on-the-trading-pit\">Verdict on The Trading Pit\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The Trading Pit is best viewed as an index-focused prop option with one leveraged ETF rather than a broad ETF environment. If you want to run automated or rules-based strategies on TQQQ and major indices using MT4, MT5 or cTrader, the firm can work well. If your ETF approach depends on sector rotation, multiple ETF pairs, or a long list of niche funds, the single-ETF limitation is likely to be too restrictive, and one of the other firms on this page will be a better fit.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"what-are-etfs-and-why-do-traders-use-them\">What Are ETFs and Why Do Traders Use Them?\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>ETFs are exchange traded funds that track a basket of stocks, sectors, bonds, commodities or themes. They trade like normal shares, but each ETF represents a full group of assets in one symbol. For traders, this makes them useful because you can take exposure to broad markets like the S&#x26;P 500, specific sectors like tech or banks, or higher-volatility products like leveraged ETFs, all without needing to trade dozens of individual stocks.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>ETF behaviour is also predictable. Most follow their underlying futures markets, react cleanly to macro events, and move in steady volatility ranges. This makes them popular for intraday trading, breakout strategies, rotation systems and trend models.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>For prop trading, ETFs sit between stocks and indices: they have strong liquidity, regular movement, and clear fundamentals, but without the extreme spikes seen in single stocks. The challenge is that only a few prop firms offer them, which is why ETF traders have fewer choices than forex or futures traders.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"risk-management-for-etf-trading\">Risk Management for ETF Trading\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>ETF prop trading requires tighter risk management than you might expect, because ETFs behave differently from forex pairs or crypto assets. They move in defined volatility ranges, react strongly to futures markets, and can gap overnight. At prop firms, these behaviours interact with fixed drawdown rules, minimum trade requirements and consistency checks, so your sizing and trade selection need to match the structure of the account.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>1. Use liquidity as your base filter\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Most prop firms limit your order size on thin products, so sticking to ETFs with strong volume (SPY, QQQ, IWM, major sector ETFs) helps you avoid slippage and rule breaks. Leveraged ETFs like TQQQ, SOXL or LABU move faster but still have strong liquidity in normal conditions, which keeps fills predictable.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>2. Match position size to the ETF’s volatility\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>ETFs vary a lot in how they move. Mega-cap index ETFs barely spike intraday, while leveraged tech ETFs can move several percent in minutes. Using ATR or a volatility-based position size keeps you inside daily loss limits and helps prevent one bad entry wiping out the evaluation.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>3. Plan for gaps and overnight risk\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>If your prop firm allows overnight holds, you should expect gaps on any ETF tied to US equities, bonds or commodities. Swing traders should use smaller size and wider stops to keep total drawdown intact across multiple days. If your firm does not allow overnight holds, you need to manage exits around major earnings or macro events where ETFs can jump on open.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>4. Use correlation to avoid oversized exposure\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Three different ETFs that look like separate trades can still be the same risk. For example, holding SPY, QQQ and XLK is effectively a tech-heavy long bias. Prop firm evaluations do not adjust for correlation, so it’s on you as the trader to reduce overlapping exposure. A simple rule is: avoid taking more than one position that reacts to the same index movement unless you intend to scale in.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>5. Keep your trade distribution consistent\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Most ETF prop firms have consistency rules that prevent one oversized trade from carrying the whole evaluation. Trading with a steady size and taking similar types of setups helps you avoid review issues when you hit the profit target. This is especially important with leveraged ETFs where the temptation to “go big once” is high.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>6. Use simple stop logic that works across ETF types\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>A fixed percentage stop or an ATR-based stop usually works well across index, sector and leveraged ETFs. Keeping everything standard avoids mistakes during fast sessions. ETF traders who balance rules with volatility awareness tend to pass evaluations more naturally than those who treat ETFs like forex pairs.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"faqs\">FAQs\u003C/h2>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"how-do-etf-prop-firms-evaluate-traders-for-funding\">How do ETF prop firms evaluate traders for funding?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>ETF prop firms evaluate traders by checking whether they can reach the profit target without breaking the drawdown or trading rules. After that, firms review position sizing, trade frequency, holding times and the consistency of results. ETF traders also need to follow symbol-specific rules, especially on volume, leverage and minimum movement. Once all conditions are met, the account is approved and you receive your funded trading account.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"do-prop-trading-firms-really-pay-out\">Do prop trading firms really pay out?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Yes, the best prop trading firms with strong reputations do pay out, but only if you follow the rules, keep positions closed at payout time, and meet the profit minimums. ETF traders need to be aware of buffer rules, drawdown resets and payout cycles, as these can affect timing. Most firms pay through common methods such as bank transfer, crypto or payment processors. Choosing firms with clear, simple payout terms reduces the risk of delays or disputes.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"whats-the-minimum-trading-day-rule\">What’s the minimum trading day rule?\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>The minimum trading day rule sets the lowest number of days you must place at least one trade during the evaluation. This prevents traders from passing with a single oversized position. Most ETF prop firms use a requirement between 3 and 10 trading days depending on the challenge type. For ETF traders, it’s easy to meet these days by spreading activity across liquid ETFs like SPY, QQQ or sector funds while keeping size modest.\u003C/p>",{"headings":5358,"localImagePaths":5432,"remoteImagePaths":5433,"frontmatter":5434,"imagePaths":5440},[5359,5362,5365,5366,5369,5372,5375,5376,5379,5382,5385,5386,5388,5390,5392,5394,5396,5399,5402,5403,5405,5407,5409,5411,5413,5416,5419,5422,5423,5426,5429],{"depth":879,"slug":5360,"text":5361},"who-are-the-best-prop-firms-for-etfs","Who Are the Best Prop Firms for ETFs?",{"depth":879,"slug":5363,"text":5364},"1-eightcap-challenges--best-etf-prop-challenges","1. Eightcap Challenges — Best ETF Prop Challenges",{"depth":158,"slug":5221,"text":5222},{"depth":158,"slug":5367,"text":5368},"etfs-and-market-access","ETFs and Market Access",{"depth":158,"slug":5370,"text":5371},"trading-rules-and-restrictions","Trading Rules and Restrictions",{"depth":158,"slug":5373,"text":5374},"trading-platform-and-tools","Trading Platform and Tools",{"depth":158,"slug":5061,"text":5062},{"depth":158,"slug":5377,"text":5378},"trading-community-and-support","Trading Community and Support",{"depth":158,"slug":5380,"text":5381},"verdict-on-eightcap-challenges","Verdict on Eightcap Challenges",{"depth":879,"slug":5383,"text":5384},"2-trade-the-pool--biggest-range-of-etfs","2. Trade the Pool — Biggest Range of ETFs",{"depth":158,"slug":5237,"text":5222},{"depth":158,"slug":5387,"text":5368},"etfs-and-market-access-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5389,"text":5371},"trading-rules-and-restrictions-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5391,"text":5374},"trading-platform-and-tools-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5393,"text":5062},"profit-payouts-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5395,"text":5378},"trading-community-and-support-1",{"depth":158,"slug":5397,"text":5398},"verdict-on-trade-the-pool","Verdict on Trade the Pool",{"depth":879,"slug":5400,"text":5401},"3-the-trading-pit--automated-etf-trading-strategies","3. The Trading Pit — Automated ETF Trading Strategies",{"depth":158,"slug":5250,"text":5222},{"depth":158,"slug":5404,"text":5368},"etfs-and-market-access-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5406,"text":5371},"trading-rules-and-restrictions-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5408,"text":5374},"trading-platform-and-tools-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5410,"text":5062},"profit-payouts-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5412,"text":5378},"trading-community-and-support-2",{"depth":158,"slug":5414,"text":5415},"verdict-on-the-trading-pit","Verdict on The Trading Pit",{"depth":879,"slug":5417,"text":5418},"what-are-etfs-and-why-do-traders-use-them","What Are ETFs and Why Do Traders Use Them?",{"depth":879,"slug":5420,"text":5421},"risk-management-for-etf-trading","Risk Management for ETF Trading",{"depth":879,"slug":4935,"text":4936},{"depth":158,"slug":5424,"text":5425},"how-do-etf-prop-firms-evaluate-traders-for-funding","How do ETF prop firms evaluate traders for funding?",{"depth":158,"slug":5427,"text":5428},"do-prop-trading-firms-really-pay-out","Do prop trading firms really pay out?",{"depth":158,"slug":5430,"text":5431},"whats-the-minimum-trading-day-rule","What’s the minimum trading day rule?",[],[],{"title":5338,"excerpt":5339,"category":5171,"tags":5435,"author":4798,"authorImage":4799,"publishedAt":240,"featured":110,"readingTimeMinutes":5176,"youtubeVideoId":5344,"featuredFirms":5436},[5341,5173,4796,5342,5343],[5437,5438,5439],{"slug":932,"descriptor":5347},{"slug":2673,"descriptor":5349},{"slug":2442,"descriptor":5351},[],"etf.md",{"id":4795,"data":5443,"body":5465,"filePath":5466,"digest":5467,"rendered":5468,"legacyId":5602},{"title":5444,"excerpt":5445,"category":5171,"tags":5446,"author":4798,"authorImage":4799,"publishedAt":1273,"featured":110,"readingTimeMinutes":1764,"youtubeVideoId":4800,"featuredFirms":5448},"Best Forex Prop Firms (Verified Testing 2026)","The best forex prop trading firms give you access to larger capital, letting you trade bigger positions without using as much of your personal funds as required with a forex broker. Our review of the best prop firms looks at the top challenges and funded programs, focusing on forex trading features.",[4795,5173,4796,5447],"forex trading",[5449,5451,5453,5455,5457,5459,5461,5463],{"slug":1392,"descriptor":5450},"Best Forex Prop Firm Overall",{"slug":932,"descriptor":5452},"Day Trading Forex Challenge",{"slug":584,"descriptor":5454},"Loyalty Program for Prop Traders",{"slug":728,"descriptor":5456},"Low Commission Fees",{"slug":332,"descriptor":5458},"Scaling to $2 million",{"slug":1599,"descriptor":5460},"Good Challenge Add Ons",{"slug":1002,"descriptor":5462},"Most Trusted Prop Firm",{"slug":1278,"descriptor":5464},"Instant Funding Challenges","## What Are The Best Forex Funded Accounts?\n\nProp trading firms provide forex traders with access to capital, enabling them to trade larger amounts without using their own money. We've reviewed the best forex prop trading firms, focusing on those with low fees, a good range of forex pairs, and solid profit-sharing models to help traders make the most of their opportunities.\n\nOur list of the best prop firms for forex trading is the following.\n\n---\n\n## The 10 Best Forex Prop Firms We Tested in 2026\n\n---\n\n## 1. FundedNext — Best Forex Prop Firm Overall\n\nFundedNext is the best forex prop firm with an overall score of 92/100 thanks to its solid scaling plan, flexible challenge types, and profit splits up to 95%. Whether you want quick funding or a structured evaluation, there's an option for you.\n\nUse promo code PROPFIRMS to get a 120% refund after passing the challenge — your entire fee back, plus a 20% bonus when you make your first withdrawal.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/fundednext.png\" alt=\"FundedNext logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">FundedNext\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Best Forex Prop Firm Overall\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">95%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.5 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/fundednext\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://fundednext.com/?fpr=noam82\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14\" />\u003C/svg>\n    Visit FundedNext\n  \u003C/a>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">120% Refund — Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pros & Cons\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Pros\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Profit splits up to 95%\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>Flexible scaling plan up to $4 million\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>MT4, MT5, cTrader, and Match-Trader\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-bold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2\">Cons\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Platform fee on cTrader and Match-Trader\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Limited access to stock markets\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\"/>\u003C/svg>Requires disciplined trading\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n### Prop Firm Details\n\nFundedNext's structured scale-up model and bi-weekly payouts make it the best forex prop firm for traders focused on consistency and long-term growth. The max funding limit is $4 million, with scaling every 4 months for traders who hit 10% growth, 2 payouts, and stay profitable.\n\n### Challenges and Accounts\n\nFundedNext runs three challenge types across two core models:\n\n**Stellar One Step:** One-phase challenge, 10% profit target, low 3% daily / 6% overall loss, 15% payout during challenge, 95% funded.\n\n**Stellar Two Step:** 8% + 5% targets, 5% daily / 10% total drawdown, 15% payout during challenge, 95% funded.\n\n**Stellar Lite:** Two-step, lower-cost model, 8% + 4% targets, 4% daily / 8% overall drawdown, no payout during challenge, 95% funded.\n\nAll challenges are time unlimited, and optional add-ons include no minimum trading days, 10% drawdown, and lifetime 95% profit splits.\n\n| Feature | Stellar (1-Step) | Stellar (2-Step) | Stellar Lite |\n|---------|-----------------|-----------------|-------------|\n| Challenge Phases | 1 Phase | 2 Phases | 2 Phases |\n| Account Sizes | 6K - 200K | 6K - 200K | 5K - 100K |\n| Audition Fees | $65 - $1,099 | $59 - $999 | $32 - $399 |\n| Leverage | 30:1 | 100:1 | 100:1 |\n| Commission | $5 | $5 | $7 |\n| Profit Target | 10% | 8%, 5% | 8%, 4% |\n| Maximum Daily Loss | 3% | 5% | 4% |\n| Maximum Overall Loss | 6% | 10% | 8% |\n| Time Limit | No Time Limit | No Time Limit | No Time Limit |\n| Challenge Phase Profit Share | 15% | 15% | N/A |\n| Funded Profit Split | 95% | 95% | 95% |\n| Minimum Trading Days | 2 | 5 | 5 |\n| First Reward | 5 Business Days | Monthly | 21 Days |\n| Subsequent Rewards | 5 Business Days | Bi-Weekly | Bi-Weekly |\n\n### Profit Splits and Payouts\n\nProfit splits go up to 95%, with 15% paid during the challenge on Stellar models. Payout schedules vary by model:\n\n- **Stellar One Step:** First reward in 5 business days, then bi-weekly\n- **Stellar Two Step:** Monthly, then bi-weekly\n- **Stellar Lite:** First reward in 21 days, then bi-weekly\n- **Minimum Withdrawal:** $20 (crypto-only if under $50)\n- **Evaluation Fee:** 100% refunded with a 20% bonus on your first profit withdrawal\n\n### Markets and Leverage\n\nWith access to 83 financial instruments across forex, indices, commodities, and cryptocurrencies, FundedNext caters to traders looking for diversity in their trading options. Leverage varies by account type and asset class, providing tailored exposure to manage risk.\n\n| Asset Class | Instruments | Leverage (Varies by Model) |\n|------------|-------------|---------------------------|\n| Forex | 50 pairs | Up to 100:1 |\n| Indices | 18 indices | 5:1 - 50:1 |\n| Commodities | 5 commodities | 10:1 - 50:1 |\n| Cryptocurrencies | 10 cryptos | Fixed at 2:1 |\n\n### Trading Platforms\n\nFundedNext offers access to:\n\n- **MT4 & MT5:** Free access; EAs allowed\n- **cTrader:** $25 fee, not available on 100K+ accounts\n- **Match-Trader:** $25 fee, not available on 100K+ accounts\n\nTradingView is available through MT5 integration.\n\n### Trust and Community\n\nFundedNext has a strong presence on social media, with active communities on Discord, Telegram, and Facebook. The prop firm's excellent TrustPilot rating of 4.6 out of 5 reflects positive customer feedback, supported by high engagement across its online platforms.\n\n- **Discord:** Hundreds of thousands of members\n- **Telegram:** 46,000+ subscribers\n- **Facebook and Twitter:** High follower engagement with frequent updates\n\nThe firm's community channels provide traders with valuable insights, support, and real-time announcements.\n\n### Support and Education\n\nFundedNext provides 24/7 support via live chat and email, complemented by a comprehensive range of educational resources, including trading guides, market updates, and a YouTube channel featuring over 1,200 videos.\n\nThese resources cover essential topics like trading psychology, strategy development, and market trends, while the YouTube content offers tutorials, webinars, and valuable insights into prop trading.\n\n### Our Final Verdict on FundedNext\n\nFundedNext is the best forex prop firm in 2026 for traders who want multiple challenge options, fast withdrawals, and a realistic path to scaling. The high profit splits, wide platform support, and low entry cost on Stellar Lite make it accessible for all skill levels.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Eightcap Challenges — Day Trading Forex Challenge\n\nEightcap Challenges is the only forex prop option on this list where the challenges run directly on a regulated broker's infrastructure instead of a traditional prop setup. That means you trade using Eightcap Challenges' own raw pricing, execution feed, and trading servers, a big difference compared to prop firms that use private feeds, synthetic spreads or restricted routing.\n\nYou can choose between a simple one-step evaluation, a more structured two-step, or Eightcap Challenges' unique timed Day Trader challenge, which condenses the entire evaluation into a 1–8 hour session. If you value stability, raw pricing and clean infrastructure over marketing gimmicks, Eightcap Challenges is one of the most reliable forex prop options available.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-stretch\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-4 p-5 flex-1 min-w-0\">\n      \u003Cimg src=\"/images/logos/eightcap-logo-1.png\" alt=\"Eightcap Challenges logo\" class=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 object-contain bg-white p-1 flex-shrink-0\" />\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"min-w-0\">\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-lg font-extrabold text-slate-900 leading-tight\">Eightcap Challenges\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5\">Day Trading Forex Challenge\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-6 px-5 py-3 sm:py-5 border-t sm:border-t-0 sm:border-l border-slate-100 bg-slate-50/50 text-center\">\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Split\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-teal-600\">90%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Max DD\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">10%\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-[10px] text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wide font-medium\">Trustpilot\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">4.0 \u003Cspan class=\"text-amber-500\">★\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Ca href=\"/reviews/eightcap\" class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-lg bg-teal-500 px-4 py-2 text-xs font-semibold text-white hover:bg-teal-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap\">\n        Full Review →\n      \u003C/a>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose -mt-3 mb-6 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50/80 px-5 py-3 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3\">\n  \u003Ca href=\"https://challenges.eightcap.com?campaign_id=1&ref_id=622\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inl