v class=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n    \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M7 7h.01M7 3h5c.512 0 1.024.195 1.414.586l7 7a2 2 0 010 2.828l-7 7a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-7-7A1.994 1.994 0 013 12V7a4 4 0 014-4z\" />\u003C/svg>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"text-sm text-emerald-700 font-semibold\">20% Off -- Code:\u003C/span>\n    \u003Cspan class=\"font-mono font-bold text-xs bg-white border border-dashed border-emerald-300 px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-emerald-700 tracking-wide select-all\">PROPFIRMS20\u003C/span>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Key Crypto Features\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cul class=\"space-y-1.5 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n    \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>52 cryptocurrency markets (class-leading range)\u003C/li>\n    \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>25% scaling every 3 months (up to $2M)\u003C/li>\n    \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>80 to 90% profit splits (same rules as you scale)\u003C/li>\n    \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>24/7 commission-free crypto trading\u003C/li>\n    \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>EA support on MT4 and MT5 platforms\u003C/li>\n  \u003C/ul>\n\u003C/div>\n\nAlgorithm-focused traders who look for bigger crypto trading options will like Blueberry Funded. They also offer a 7-day challenge, with fixed 1:2 leverage to balance risk control with trading power.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Management in Crypto Prop Trading\n\nWhile it is the exciting part, crypto prop trading is not all about chasing those big profits. Risk management is what keeps a successful prop trader in the game in the long term.\n\n### Market Volatility\n\nCrypto trading is known to be very volatile, where one random tweet from some tech billionaire can send prices surging or plunging within minutes, making volatility both a blessing and a curse for crypto traders. As a result, prop trading firms have developed strategies to contain the wild price swings that often come with cryptocurrencies.\n\nThese crypto-focused firms are especially strict with position sizing. Placing a big chunk of your trading account into a single trade, regardless of how sure you are of a \"pump\", is not possible. Individual positions are usually capped at around 1% to 2%, so you will not be wiped out even if the trade goes against your plan. In extreme times of market volatility, these firms may temporarily reduce available leverage or even restrict it altogether.\n\n### Leverage and Risk Appetite\n\nLeverage in crypto proprietary trading firms could be extremely useful, but if misused, it can also be extremely dangerous. Trading firms can offer leverage starting from 1:5 to 1:10, with some offering even higher levels, allowing you to trade positions much larger than your funded account.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 px-5 py-4\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-amber-800 mb-1\">Leverage example\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed\">With a $10,000 account and 1:10 leverage, you can control a $100,000 position. This magnifies potential gains by ten times, but also losses by ten times.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\nVarious guardrails are being implemented to keep traders from taking full-on risks with leveraged trading. Cryptocurrency prop trading generally has drawdown limits of 5% to 10%, and risk-per-trade limits are also capped at around 1% to 2% per position to help in this.\n\nProp traders generally have a higher risk appetite than the average retail trader, but trading with the firm's capital, these risk guidelines can help improve trading performance in the long term by enforcing trading discipline, which is hard to develop when trading alone.\n\n### Trading Restrictions\n\nPart of the broader risk management strategy, and depending on the trading firm, trading restrictions are in place to prevent catastrophic losses when markets go on wild swings. Many firms restrict news trading, scaling, and high-frequency trading, with some outright banning them. These are some of the most unpredictable and riskiest strategies, making these rules non-negotiable, making it crucial for you to double-check what strategies are allowed and not allowed.\n\n---\n\n## Is Prop Crypto Trading Right for You?\n\nIs crypto prop trading for you? The answer to that question depends on your trading goals, experience level, and your ability to manage risk properly.\n\n### Who Benefits From Crypto Prop Trading?\n\nProp trading in general is beneficial for experienced traders who have already developed working trading strategies, but do not have the trading capital necessary to have a significant impact on their desired profit levels.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Trader Profiles Likely to Succeed\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"space-y-3\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-teal-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Skilled Traders Lacking Capital\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Traders who have the skills but not a substantial trading account will benefit from the capital a prop firm can provide.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-teal-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Risk-Averse Experienced Traders\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">With strict risk management protocols to follow and no personal funds at risk, these traders gain a psychological edge.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-teal-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Disciplined Traders\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">If you manage risks carefully, stick to the rules, and do not let emotions get the better of you, these restrictions will not feel like hindrances.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-teal-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"/>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Technical Analyst Traders\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Technical chart setups usually work better with cryptocurrencies compared to other instruments like forex, providing more trading opportunities.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n### Signing Up to a Crypto Prop Firm\n\nBefore you start prop trading and purchase a challenge, it is vital to evaluate the evaluation process, or you are risking wasting time and money.\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Pre-Signup Checklist\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"space-y-3\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-teal-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-teal-600\">1\u003C/span>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Evaluation Requirements\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">What are the profit targets? Is it a reasonable 8%, or a very ambitious 25%? What about drawdown limits? Will they close your account with a tight 5%, or do they have a lenient 10% drawdown limit?\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-teal-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-teal-600\">2\u003C/span>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Fee Structure\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">How much are the upfront fees compared to the potential funded account you can get? Will they have hidden subscription fees after getting the funded account?\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-teal-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-teal-600\">3\u003C/span>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Profit Splits and Payout Rules\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">The usual profit-sharing agreement is at 70/30, with you getting the larger share. Will you get paid weekly, monthly, or is open withdrawal allowed? Minimum amounts for withdrawal also need to be considered.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-teal-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-teal-600\">4\u003C/span>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Trading Restrictions\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Depending on the company, trading restrictions vary. Make sure these guidelines and rules align with your favourite trading strategy and style.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-teal-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-teal-600\">5\u003C/span>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Scaling Opportunities\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Do they have a system in place to upgrade your account bigger and bigger? What are the required performance metrics to level up? The top crypto prop trading firms will have a clear and transparent mechanism to reward successful traders with larger trading accounts.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\n---\n\n## FAQs\n\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 space-y-4\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5\">\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">How does prop trading work?\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed\">Prop trading lets you trade with a firm's capital instead of your own. To qualify, you must pass an evaluation challenge that tests your ability to hit profit targets and follow risk rules. If successful, you are awarded a funded account and keep a portion of the profits, often up to 90%. The firm absorbs the risk, but you must follow strict trading rules to maintain the account and qualify for scaling opportunities.\u003C/p>\n  \u003C/div>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5\">\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Is prop trading illegal?\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed\">No, prop trading is legal. Many financial firms, including independent crypto prop firms, operate within regulatory boundaries. However, not all firms are created equal. Traders should choose firms with clear terms, transparent policies, and a strong reputation (broker backed firms are considered the most trustworthy). Always review the firm's rules, compliance practices, and trader reviews to avoid scams or misleading promises.\u003C/p>\n  \u003C/div>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5\">\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">What is an example of proprietary trading?\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed\">A trader passes a $50,000 challenge and gets a funded $50,000 account. They spot a trade, risk $500 (1%), and make $1,000 in profit. With an 80% profit split, they keep $800 and the firm keeps $200. The trader did not risk personal capital, and consistent performance could lead to account scaling. This model rewards disciplined risk management while giving traders access to larger capital than they would typically have on their own.\u003C/p>\n  \u003C/div>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5\">\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2\">Can you make money as a prop trader?\u003C/p>\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed\">Yes, prop traders can earn steady income if they are consistently profitable and follow the firm's rules. Success depends on your trading strategy, discipline, and ability to manage risk, not luck. Many traders turn prop trading into a full-time career, especially with firms that offer high profit splits, low fees, and scaling opportunities. However, it is not a shortcut to wealth. Long-term results require experience, emotional control, and commitment to continuous improvement.\u003C/p>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>","src/content/blog/crypto-trading.md","cba058ab8aec488b",{"html":7312,"metadata":7313},"\u003Ch2 id=\"how-does-crypto-prop-trading-work\">How Does Crypto Prop Trading Work?\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>When you trade with a crypto prop firm, you go through an evaluation process to prove you can hit profit targets while managing risk. Once you pass, you are awarded a funded account, typically starting from $10,000 and scaling up to $100,000, $500,000, or even millions.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Unlike hedge funds or banks, prop firms do not manage client capital. They take on the risk themselves, earning from challenge fees and a share of trader profits. If you consistently perform well, your account may be scaled up for larger trades and higher earnings.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">How It Works at a Glance\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-lg bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 text-center\">\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-2xl font-black text-teal-600 mb-1\">1\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-700\">Pay a challenge fee and enter an evaluation\u003C/p>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-lg bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 text-center\">\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-2xl font-black text-teal-600 mb-1\">2\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-700\">Hit profit targets while staying within risk limits\u003C/p>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-lg bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 text-center\">\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-2xl font-black text-teal-600 mb-1\">3\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-700\">Pass evaluation and receive a funded account\u003C/p>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"rounded-lg bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 text-center\">\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-2xl font-black text-teal-600 mb-1\">4\u003C/p>\n      \u003Cp class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-700\">Trade crypto and keep up to 90-100% of profits\u003C/p>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"inside-the-evaluation-process\">Inside the Evaluation Process\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Getting funded starts with a trading challenge. You pay an upfront fee, trade in a simulated environment, and aim to meet profit goals (usually between 8% and 15%) without breaking drawdown or risk limits. There are various models, but one-step or two-step evaluation processes are the most common, with instant funding accounts becoming more and more popular too.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"bg-[#0d1b2a] px-5 py-4\">\n    \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-black text-white uppercase tracking-wide\">Example: Two-Step Challenge\u003C/p>\n  \u003C/div>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"p-5\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"space-y-4\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n        \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-teal-500 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-white\">1\u003C/span>\n        \u003C/div>\n        \u003Cdiv>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Challenge Phase\u003C/p>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">Hit profit targets while staying within daily and overall drawdown limits.\u003C/p>\n        \u003C/div>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n        \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-teal-500 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          \u003Cspan class=\"text-xs font-black text-white\">2\u003C/span>\n        \u003C/div>\n        \u003Cdiv>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Verification Phase\u003C/p>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">Prove your performance was not a fluke by maintaining similar results under potentially stricter conditions.\u003C/p>\n        \u003C/div>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n        \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-white\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n        \u003C/div>\n        \u003Cdiv>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Funded Account\u003C/p>\n          \u003Cp class=\"text-sm text-slate-600\">Only traders who pass both stages receive a funded account. This system filters out reckless or lucky traders and helps firms find those with real skill.\u003C/p>\n        \u003C/div>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"how-prop-firms-choose-traders\">How Prop Firms Choose Traders\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Prop firms are selective. Their business model relies on finding consistent, low-risk performers, not gamblers. Most use a structured boot-camp-style evaluation to separate skilled traders from the rest. Challenge fees (often starting at $50 for small accounts) serve a dual purpose: generating revenue and discouraging uncommitted applicants.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Firms raise capital internally or through investors and reinvest it into funded accounts. They also build advanced trading tools and algorithms tailored to crypto volatility, giving traders the edge they need to profit in fast-moving markets.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"crypto-only-vs-multi-asset-prop-firms\">Crypto-Only vs Multi-Asset Prop Firms\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Choosing between a crypto-only and a multi-asset prop firm depends on what you want from your trading experience: depth in one market or the ability to move across multiple.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden\">\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"p-5 border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r border-slate-200\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n        \u003Cdiv class=\"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-amber-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-amber-600\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n        \u003C/div>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-900\">Crypto-Only Firms\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Broader range of pairs (40+ coins)\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Platforms optimized for crypto volatility\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Higher crypto leverage (up to 1:10)\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>24/7 trading support\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Limited to crypto markets only\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"p-5\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n        \u003Cdiv class=\"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n          \u003Csvg class=\"h-4 w-4 text-blue-600\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M3.055 11H5a2 2 0 012 2v1a2 2 0 002 2 2 2 0 012 2v2.945M8 3.935V5.5A2.5 2.5 0 0010.5 8h.5a2 2 0 012 2 2 2 0 104 0 2 2 0 012-2h1.064M15 20.488V18a2 2 0 012-2h3.064M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n        \u003C/div>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-900\">Multi-Asset Firms\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cul class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Forex, commodities, indices, stocks + crypto\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Longer track records in traditional finance\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>More established risk management systems\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-emerald-500\" fill=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\">\u003Cpath fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Diverse payout options and scaling structures\u003C/li>\n        \u003Cli class=\"flex items-start gap-2\">\u003Csvg class=\"mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 flex-shrink-0 text-red-400\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>Fewer crypto pairs and lower crypto leverage\u003C/li>\n      \u003C/ul>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>Crypto-only prop firms are fully focused on digital assets. They tend to offer a broader range of cryptocurrency pairs, often supporting 40 or more coins, including lesser-known altcoins. Their platforms and tools are usually optimized for crypto’s unique characteristics, like high volatility and 24/7 trading. These firms may offer higher leverage on crypto positions, sometimes up to 1:10, and their support teams are typically more familiar with blockchain-specific issues.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In contrast, multi-asset prop firms offer access to a broader range of markets, including forex, commodities, indices, and stocks alongside crypto. This setup allows traders to switch between asset classes based on market conditions or personal preference. These firms often have longer track records in traditional finance, with more established risk management systems and educational resources. Their larger funding pools can also mean different scaling structures and potentially more diverse payout options.\u003C/p>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"prop-trading-rules-to-know\">Prop Trading Rules to Know\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Every crypto prop firm has its own trading rules to protect capital, and breaking them can get your challenge or funded account revoked.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"not-prose my-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm\">\n  \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3\">Common Restrictions\u003C/p>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"space-y-3\">\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Csvg class=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">News trading bans\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Some firms restrict trading during major events like halving cycles, regulation changes, or network forks.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Csvg class=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Overnight holds\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Due to high volatility, many firms disallow holding crypto positions overnight.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Csvg class=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">High-risk strategy bans\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Martingale and other aggressive strategies are often prohibited, especially when combined with leverage.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Csvg class=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Time-window limits\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">A few firms may restrict trading to certain hours or require activity during specific sessions.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n    \u003Cdiv class=\"flex items-start gap-3\">\n      \u003Cdiv class=\"flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center\">\n        \u003Csvg class=\"h-3 w-3 text-red-500\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2.5\">\u003Cpath stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12\">\u003C/path>\u003C/svg>\n      \u003C/div>\n      \u003Cdiv>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-900\">Instrument restrictions\u003C/p>\n        \u003Cp class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">Most support BTC and ETH, but availability of niche altcoins varies by firm.\u003C/p>\n      \u003C/div>\n    \u003C/div>\n  \u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Chr>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"best-crypto-proprietary-trading-firms\">Best Crypto Proprietary Trading Firms\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Each crypto prop trading firm offers its unique advantages to traders looking to dabble with or have expertise with digital assets, from bigger leverage options to firms offering a bigger selection of coins to trade. Below are the top ranked options from our list of the best cryptocurrency prop firms.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"1-brightfunded--best-crypto-prop-firm-overall\">1. BrightFunded — Best Crypto Prop Firm Overall\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>BrightFunded is the leading crypto prop firm, offering high leverage, over 40 crypto pairs, and scalable funded accounts. With profit splits reaching up to 100%, it provides a strong option for traders aiming to grow their accounts and maximize returns.\u003C